text_b_pos: I adopted her that same day and named her boots.
text_b_neg: I was afraid of large dogs.

text_a: My daughter went to Boston College from 2003 to 2007. The dorm room doors are often open. She went out for class one day. When she returned she found her camera was missing.
text_b_pos: After that she always locked her valuables away in a safe.
text_b_neg: After that she made sure to always leave other valuables lying around in her room.

text_a: Grandma was awake early. There was a smell of food coming from the kitchen. I rushed down the stairs. Then I ran into the kitchen.
text_b_pos: The kitchen was on fire.
text_b_neg: Her Gradma cooked a turkey.

text_a: Alex was five Year's old. Today was the first day of September. Alex woke up and dressed in a new and carefully selected outfit. Alex and the whole family walked out to the bus stop.
text_b_pos: The neighbour congratulated the family on their well dressed son.
text_b_neg: He fell on the ground and ruined the outfit but did not care.

text_a: It was finally time for moving day. The big yellow truck pulled into the driveway. We had all our boxes packed up. The movers got a call from their boss.
text_b_pos: They've got some emergencies and had to reschedule with us.
text_b_neg: We had so many boxes that they didn't fit into the truck.

text_a: Sue wanted a new dog to keep her company. When she went to the store, she discovered they are expensive. The employee at the store advised her to adopt instead of buy. Sue learned that adoption is much cheaper and for a greater cause.
text_b_pos: Sue will soon be able to afford to buy a dog.
text_b_neg: She's glad the employee pointed her in the right direction.

text_a: Kayla liked going to the movies with her friends. Her friends informed her that they couldn't make it this time. Kayla was upset. Kayla decided to go to the movies alone.
text_b_pos: Kayla was excited that she watched the movie with her friends.
text_b_neg: Kayla still liked the movie.

text_a: Tim slept through his alarm. When he woke up, he realized he was going to be late for class. Tim rushed out the door without breakfast. He barely made it to class on time.
text_b_pos: He would have preferred to be late.
text_b_neg: He was very hungry during the whole class.

text_a: Hill had a very big cello. One day when he was playing it, it cracked. He was sad but he got it repaired. It cost a lot of money but it was worth it.
text_b_pos: He thinks about giving his cello away.
text_b_neg: Now he can continue playing his very big cello.

text_a: Carin watched a movie about sharks. She became scared of swimming in open water. Her friends invited Carin to join them at the beach. Carin was afraid.
text_b_pos: She wouldn't go into the water.
text_b_neg: Carin is a good swimmer.

text_a: I was sent to the emergency room because I was cutting. They carried me on a bed from the ambulance, strapped in. The room they put me in was next to the nurse's station. I could hear them laughing at me through the open door.
text_b_pos: I went home soon after this.
text_b_neg: That was really cruel by them.

text_a: Billy Bangingstrom loved to bang the drum. One time, he banged it so loud his neighbors complained. Being the vindictive sort, Billy stole their wifi password. With this password, he made their computer play drum music every day.
text_b_pos: Billy's neighbors loved the drum music their computer was playing.
text_b_neg: Billy's neighbors got even angrier.

text_a: Rob wasn't supposed to have Mortal Kombat. He traded a friend at school for the game. He was playing on Saturday when his mom came into his room. She yelled in anger when she saw the game.
text_b_pos: She joined the game.
text_b_neg: He was not allowed to play any video games for the rest of the month.

text_a: Adam couldn't find his baseball hat. He looked all over the house. Adam finally found the hat in his brother's room. Adam accused his brother of stealing the hat.
text_b_pos: His brother said that the he did not use the hat.
text_b_neg: Adam was happy that his brother liked his hat.

text_a: Gavin was excited about taking a girl to the dance at school. He was in the middle of getting ready when he got a call. The dance had been cancelled due to an electrical issue. Gavin was so sad to be losing his plans for the night.
text_b_pos: He cried all night.
text_b_neg: He went to the dance.

text_a: Jose began learning the trumpet in 4th grade. He was not very good and many people made fun of him. Then, Jose practiced for two hours every single day. After two years, he was the best player in the school.
text_b_pos: He stopped playing the trumpet because his mom told him to.
text_b_neg: He was invited to hold a concert at the end of the year.

text_a: Andrew loved his father's car. Andrew's father knew that and was going to give him the car. It was Andrew's birthday. After dinner Andrew's father a took Andrew to the front yard.
text_b_pos: Andrew received a bicycle.
text_b_neg: Andrew was overwhelmed by the present.

text_a: Jordan and his girlfriend of three Year's decided to move in together. They figured since they love each other, this will be the next step. As soon as they settled in, things were going down hill. She complained about dishes, he complained about his privacy.
text_b_pos: They got married.
text_b_neg: They split soon after.

text_a: The school called early the first week. They said they were going to implement uniforms. Exasperated because I just bought clothes, I agreed. I went shopping online.
text_b_pos: I decided to move away to another city.
text_b_neg: I couldn't find the right color and decided to look in town the next day.

text_a: Antonio wanted to take an online economics course. His advisor suggested him taking the class on campus. Antonio did not take his advice. He found the class difficult and had to drop out.
text_b_pos: Antonio loved economics.
text_b_neg: Antonio wished he had listened to his advisor.

text_a: Tim was doing bad in class. He needed to do well on his midterm to try and salvage it. If he didn't there wouldn't be a way to pass. Tim messed up and failed the midterm.
text_b_pos: Tim enjoys teaching.
text_b_neg: He needs to redo class.

text_a: Eddie and Rita toured a local historic house for Valentine's day. During the tour, Eddy felt very ill, very quickly. Rita rushed him to the hospital. Eddy got an IV and medications to take home.
text_b_pos: He got better after taking them.
text_b_neg: Rita had no clue what an IV was.

text_a: Owen was an aspiring author. He had written several letters to his favorite local newspaper. One morning he was reading said paper as he ate cereal. Suddenly he noticed his own words right on the page.
text_b_pos: He was happy to see his letter printed.
text_b_neg: He continued eating cereal.

text_a: Lindsay loves music, especially concerts. She worked a boring job, but it paid for concert tickets. One day, Lindsay saw there was a job opening at a radio station. She didn't have experience, but she emphasized her love of music.
text_b_pos: She was too satisfied with her current job to resign from it.
text_b_neg: She decided to apply and ultimately got the job.

text_a: I bought a new pair of shoes. I put them on and walked outside. These shoes were very shiny today. The shine shined into a drivers eyes and he put the brakes on.
text_b_pos: The driver almost hit a pedestrian.
text_b_neg: The driver was happy.

text_a: The delivery man delivered a small package. I found out that it was my meal prep package. I opened it and started to prepare one of the dishes. The food was fresh and contained several ingredients.
text_b_pos: Then I went to McDonalds.
text_b_neg: Sadly I have no cooking skills and it still tasted bad.

text_a: Carol had a bunch of obsolete computer manuals she had no use for. She didn't want to throw them out and create more trash. Carol had an inspired idea! She and her friends built large trebuchets in their backyards.
text_b_pos: Trebuchets are the superior siege weapon.
text_b_neg: Using the trebuchet she could launch her manuals right over to her neighbors.

text_a: My ex-boss has 4 grandchildren. One of the four is autistic. His mom is convinced a special sugar-free diet will help. I saw on FB a photo of three of the kids eating ice cream.
text_b_pos: I flagged the photo as inappropriate.
text_b_neg: It looks like sugar does not cause autism.

text_a: Jana was an aspiring model. She submitted her photo to a cover girl contest. Luckily, her photo was chosen! She would appear on the cover of a magazine.
text_b_pos: Jana was very happy.
text_b_neg: Jana decided to become a photograph.

text_a: Sam was standing on a bridge over a stream. He picked up a rock and threw it in. The rock made a small splash. Sam looked for a bigger rock to throw in.
text_b_pos: He didn't throw a rock.
text_b_neg: He made a bigger splash.

text_a: Suzy was lonely so she asked her mother for a dog. Susie's mom told her no. The next day, Susie woke up and remembered it was her birthday. She heard barking.
text_b_pos: Her mother bought her the dog for her birthday gift.
text_b_neg: Susie wants a pair of shoes as her birthday gift.

text_a: Anne was covered in flour. She'd been baking cookies for hours. She wanted to bake enough to bring them to her office. Once she was done, she boxed them up.
text_b_pos: The coworkers liked the cookies.
text_b_neg: She didn't have enough flour.

text_a: Allie took her standardized test. She needed to pass. She couldn't graduate if she didn't. She looked up her score online.
text_b_pos: She was convinced everything had gone fine.
text_b_neg: She was very nervous while browsing for the results.

text_a: Lisa let her dogs outside in the backyard. All of a sudden it started raining. Lisa called her dogs back inside. When the dogs came in they started shaking.
text_b_pos: The dogs seemed really happy.
text_b_neg: Lisa went to get some towels.

text_a: John left his house to go grocery shopping. Before he made it, he saw a stray dog on the sidewalk. He stopped to check for a collar, but there was none. He took the dog home, and named him Frank.
text_b_pos: Frank seems happy he found someone to look after him.
text_b_neg: The dog ate all his groceries.

text_a: A hook salesman stood on a street corner and looked for customers. No one seemed to want to buy his goods. The salesman got an idea. He took his biggest hook and tied string to it.
text_b_pos: Still nobody wanted to buy his goods.
text_b_neg: Now the man's hooks would not blow away.

text_a: Jake was playing catch with his dog. He threw the ball too far. The dog still chased after it and got lost. Jake looked everywhere for them.
text_b_pos: The dog found a new home in a charity organisation.
text_b_neg: Jake found the dog under a tree after two hours of search.

text_a: Jane had a conference with her son Dan's teacher. Dan had 2 fights in a week and this needed to stop. The teacher explained he and another boy seemed to dislike each other. Jane wanted to know what needed to be done.
text_b_pos: Dan was put into another shool.
text_b_neg: Jane allows Dan to fight.

text_a: Kat had been practicing for weeks for the dance. She was the lead dancer in the ballet. Recently her toenail had fallen off from all her dancing. Her toe was in terrible shape, battered and bleeding.
text_b_pos: She felt sad and all her effort in vein.
text_b_neg: She was really happy about it.

text_a: Scottie is seeking help for his anger management. He can't locate a counselor that seems helpful to him. This angers Scottie. He relapses and struggles to get help.
text_b_pos: He would not feel anger anymore.
text_b_neg: He finally found someone who could help him.

text_a: Becca liked to swim. She practiced everyday for hours. She entered a contest to show her skills to others. She competed with the best in her area and won.
text_b_pos: She finally became the gold medalist and got a prize for that.
text_b_neg: She lost in the first round.

text_a: I found a job tagging adult content. It was very new and confusing. I had to view the content and make a tag that related to it. I tried several of them out.
text_b_pos: I quit my job afterwards.
text_b_neg: Eventually I got used to it.

text_a: Jeff had a huge exam next week. He knew he had to study as this would affect his final grade. Jeff was so anxious all he did was study day and night. The day of the test came and Jeff was ready.
text_b_pos: Jeff aced his test and passed with flying colors.
text_b_neg: Jeff decided his final grade wasn't that important after all.

text_a: Lisa got a new t shirt the other day. Before she wore it, she wanted it washed. Lisa decided to then put it in the washer. After it was washed she tried it on.
text_b_pos: The t-shirt didn't like that.
text_b_neg: It was too small for her.

text_a: Sam worked at a grocery store. He had forgotten a lunch at home. The store had a deli. Sam took his lunch break.
text_b_pos: He bought his lunch from the deli.
text_b_neg: He did not have anything for lunch.

text_a: Skip was a lonely man. He didn't really have anyone to call his own. One day Skip was sitting in the park. He spotted a beautiful young woman with her dog.
text_b_pos: He asked the woman if they could have a cup of coffee together.
text_b_neg: He left the park immediately.

text_a: Kristi found it hard to date with three kids. She could never find anyone who'd accept them. One day, she went with her kids to their hairdresser. The hairdresser was a nice man who liked her instantly.
text_b_pos: He asked her out on a date.
text_b_neg: He did not give her kids a haircut.

text_a: Hobbie was going to see a free concert in the city. The show was at 8 am though so he had to be up early. He took the train to the city at 4 am to be closer to the stage. When he got there, there were people waiting.
text_b_pos: He eventually made it to the front.
text_b_neg: He forgot to go to the concert.

text_a: Richard wanted to rent a cabin. The only problem is the cabin was really far away. Disregarding this problem he went ahead to schedule the trip. Once he opened his cabin he soon grew disappointed.
text_b_pos: The cabin was beautiful.
text_b_neg: The cabin was dirty.

text_a: Tom was skiing for the first time. He was going very well staying up on his skis. So he was allowed to take the T-bar up to one of the small hills. He was afraid he wouldn't be able to get off when it reached the top.
text_b_pos: But luckily he made it.
text_b_neg: He did not ski anymore.

text_a: Jody was bringing home her newest baby from the hospital. Her ten year old was the most eager to meet the baby. She had him wash up and then let him hold the baby. His favorite thing was how soft the baby was.
text_b_pos: He wanted the baby to be rougher.
text_b_neg: He kissed his brother.

text_a: Joe made a cheese sandwich. As he was about to eat, there was a knock on his door. He put his sandwich down to answer the door. When he came back, his sandwich was gone.
text_b_pos: He started crying and smashed his TV.
text_b_neg: His cat had already took it.

text_a: Gary was a horrible musician. He wanted to learn how to make beautiful music. His first lesson, he was told to mark time with his foot. He couldn't keep the beat at all!
text_b_pos: He started hating music and quit after two weeks.
text_b_neg: He loved that first lesson.

text_a: Sue always wondered why she saw things differently from her peers. She had trouble in school sometimes because of her vision. Sue decided to go to an eye doctor. The doctor told Sue that she was color blind.
text_b_pos: Sue wished she could see colors.
text_b_neg: Sue now knew why she saw things differently than her peers.

text_a: One year, my family and I drove from Missouri to Canada. We made many stops in ten states along the way. When we arrived in Canada, our truck broke down. My brother and I explored the town while my dad got the truck fixed.
text_b_pos: It was great to be back home.
text_b_neg: We found the local stripclub.

text_a: Dan found a bag of marijuana in his teenage son's bedroom. Dan went to his son's school. Dan took his son out of school early. Dan took his son to the park, where they talked at length.
text_b_pos: His son said that he would never do drugs again.
text_b_neg: Then Dan smoked the marijuhana with his son.

text_a: Jim saves up his money all winter. When summer comes he has $20,000 for a paint job on his show car He gets the paint job on his classic car. Jim enters his car in a local auto show that summer.
text_b_pos: Unfortunately he does not win.
text_b_neg: Jim is sad because he does not own a car.

text_a: Will had a birthday coming up. This was a big one - his thirtieth. Will spent the day quietly hoping his friends would surprise him. Will finished work and returned home, dejected.
text_b_pos: On the way home Will had an accident.
text_b_neg: At home all his friends were waiting with a surprise party for Will.

text_a: Jill's dog had been with her parent's for a week. It had been used to running outside. When Jill got home, she walked in the door to a mess. Jill's dog had destroyed the couch.
text_b_pos: Jill rewarded the dog.
text_b_neg: Jill gave the dog to her parents.

text_a: James recently met a woman who he really liked. They had their first date at the beach near his home. After their first date they became inseparable. He plans on proposing to her in the near future.
text_b_pos: He went on many other first dates after that.
text_b_neg: He is therefore saving up for a ring.

text_a: Ken was very lazy. He let a lot of chores pile up. Ken decided to make a list to help. After he was done, Ken lost the list.
text_b_pos: His mother called him and congratulated him.
text_b_neg: He then started a new list.

text_a: Josh worked part time at his father's friend's store. He helped his father file paperwork in the office of the store. Josh noticed ways that his boss could cut down on spending. Josh helped his boss trim down his finances.
text_b_pos: His boss raised Josh's salary.
text_b_neg: His boss was very sad.

text_a: Judy took her kids to the zoo. The kids loved to watch the elephants. The elephants were squirting water on each other. The kids laughed at the elephants.
text_b_pos: The kids hated animals.
text_b_neg: Everybody was enjoying the hot weather.

text_a: Nancy gave me a gift box. I decided to open it and see what it is. Nothing was in the box. I asked if she forgot to put the present inside.
text_b_pos: Nancy was very embarrassed and went home to get the present.
text_b_neg: Nancy told me that the present was invisible.

text_a: The girl had fun. She told her mom. Her mom took the girl to do it again. The girl appreciated that.
text_b_pos: She realised that her mother hated her.
text_b_neg: She thanked her mom with a gift.

text_a: Sonny likes to his dinner watching TV. Joanne makes dinner early so Sonny can watch his favorite show. Joanne notices the TV flickering. The TV stopped working.
text_b_pos: They called a TV guy to fix it.
text_b_neg: They watched the show while eating dinner.

text_a: Tom was at the lake with friends. They all wanted to go swimming. The water was really cold. Tom didn't want to get in.
text_b_pos: Tom got drown.
text_b_neg: Because he has a tolerance to coldness.

text_a: Bob told his son to open the gate to the driveway. His boy raced out of the car to open it. The gate was stuck. Bob's daughter got out to help.
text_b_pos: Together, Bob's children managed to pull the gate open.
text_b_neg: Bob drove away.

text_a: Jenny's mom reminded her to take out the trash when she's free. In the afternoon, Jenny came home from work. She took a nap on the couch. When her mom came home, she saw Jenny on the couch.
text_b_pos: Her mom waked her up and asked her to take out the trash right now.
text_b_neg: Her mom went back to work.

text_a: Working at Best Buy can be hard at times. Customers can be rude and loud. It can be very stressful. When I get home I enjoy the absolute silence.
text_b_pos: I am looking forward to work tomorrow.
text_b_neg: I relax and have a nice dinner.

text_a: Andy threw rocks at the abandoned building across from his house. He broke a few windows as well. One day the owners confronted him about it. He felt bad that he caused the damage and promised to stop.
text_b_pos: He had to replace the broken windows.
text_b_neg: The owner was happy about the broken windows.

text_a: I used to be employed as a Roadside Assistance Agent. The job was very rewarding at times. I was able to assist people with auto emergencies. Most of my dispatched calls were flat tires.
text_b_pos: I was able to help them very quickly.
text_b_neg: I laughed at them.

text_a: John decides to attend class today. He gets dressed and brushes his teeth. He finally walks to class. After class he buys a cheeseburger for lunch.
text_b_pos: He then threw the cheeseburger in the trash.
text_b_neg: Cheeseburger are his favourite meal.

text_a: Betty had come by Annie's home for dinner. She mentioned that she wanted to see the quilt Annie had finished. After dinner, Annie showed her the quilt. Betty complimented her on the pattern and workmanship.
text_b_pos: Betty was very impressed with her work.
text_b_neg: Betty claimed she could do much better herself.

text_a: Sean was traveling on a bus. A passenger became ill and someone started to film it. Sean felt uncomfortable and asked the woman to stop. The woman responded by yelling at him and threatening him.
text_b_pos: The bus driver threw her out of the bus.
text_b_neg: Everyone applauded her.

text_a: Jessica wakes up and wants to eat breakfast. She grabs the cereal and pours some into a bowl. She looks in the fridge for milk. There is no milk in the fridge so she can't eat her breakfast
text_b_pos: She went out to buy some milk.
text_b_neg: She went to work after her breakfast.

text_a: My 99 year old friend Ben was in WW2. Once he was with his squad at a brothel in Paris. He stayed in the lobby, as he was a married man. The prostitutes made fun of him.
text_b_pos: He got angry and the prostitutes were shocked.
text_b_neg: He really had fun that day.

text_a: Tim was very skinny. He did not have muscles like the other guys. He decided to do 50 push ups a day. It was hard work.
text_b_pos: He looked anorexic.
text_b_neg: He got muscular.

text_a: The Johnson family loved Halloween. Every year they did a different theme for their house in celebration. This year they were having difficulty in deciding a theme. They held a few family meetings to finally determine what to do.
text_b_pos: They decided to cook pasta.
text_b_neg: They settled on "Star Wars" theme.

text_a: In the past seven months I've lost around 120 pounds! It's been a really exciting time, obviously. I think the thing I'm most excited about though is clothes. I love being able to walk into a store and see my size.
text_b_pos: Many of my old clothes do not fit, so I need to buy new ones.
text_b_neg: I do not like having to buy new clothes.

text_a: Beth was having a hard time writing her term paper. She was trying to reach the word limit and coming up short. She even filled half the report with fluff. Beth eventually went online and found a relevant paper.
text_b_pos: The paper was not relevant.
text_b_neg: She had to change everyting.

text_a: I decided to make homemade hot fudge and caramel. I put the chocolate in a tub when it was done. I put a container of cream in the crockpot. When I took it out, it was caramel.
text_b_pos: I was confused.
text_b_neg: I loved caramel.

text_a: Simon and Jimmy wanted doughnuts from the farmer's market. They asked their mom to go pick some up. Their mom agreed, but only if the boys came along. The boys said they were too tired to go.
text_b_pos: So they never got the doughnuts.
text_b_neg: Jimmy went with his mom, but did not buy doghnuts.

text_a: Susie was tired of paying a lot for her cell plan. It was eating up her wallet. So she decided to pick a cheaper plan. Finally she found one for thirty dollars a month.
text_b_pos: This was even more expensive that the one she had.
text_b_neg: She decided to buy a new phone.

text_a: Spencer and Sarah wanted a baby. They tried for a few months. Sarah eventually got pregnant. She prepared herself well.
text_b_pos: Sarah was happy when the baby was born.
text_b_neg: Sarah and Spencer adopted a baby.

text_a: Terry and his friend went to the movie theater. They were planning to see a popular new release. The man at the counter told them all of the tickets were sold out. Dismayed, Terry and his friend settled on a different movie.
text_b_pos: To his surprise, Terry liked the movie.
text_b_neg: Terry and his friend decided to move to Paris.

text_a: Robin was preparing dinner for her husband. It was their fifteenth anniversary. She wanted to surprise him with a home cooked meal. While she was waiting for him to get home, the power went out.
text_b_pos: It turned out to be a candlelight dinner.
text_b_neg: She went out alone instead.

text_a: Zaddy Racks owner started leaving the door open to cool the house. Zaddy Cracks started going outside by himself. One day Zaddy Tracks couldn't be found. His owner though he had gotten lost outside.
text_b_pos: His owner was worried and organized a search party to look for him.
text_b_neg: His owner laughed and told Zaddy to stay away.

text_a: Maria was afraid of thunder. It was storming very hard outside. She hid under the dining room table and cried softly. Maria's dog heard her and crawled under the table to comfort her.
text_b_pos: The dog and her danced.
text_b_neg: He pet the dog and chilled down.

text_a: It was going to feel like it was over a hundred degrees today. I woke up wanted to go swimming and enjoy the summer day. When I got outside I realize the air was heavy and my asthma acted up. I quickly went back inside to decide if I wanted to go for a swim.
text_b_pos: I really liked the heat.
text_b_neg: In the end I stayed at home and watched TV.

text_a: Evan wanted a pair of jean shorts for the summer. He shopped around, but every store was too expensive. Then he decided to try to make his own. He carefully cut the legs off an old pair of jeans.
text_b_pos: But he made a mistake and ruined his jeans.
text_b_neg: His jeans got longer.

text_a: Jane walked her dogs along the beach everyday. One day she found a bottle with a note in it. The note showed a map to a local restaurant with a voucher for 50% ofF. It took Jane an hour to follow the map to the restaurant.
text_b_pos: If only she had a voucher for the restaurant.
text_b_neg: The food was delicious.

text_a: Rob was very hungry all day His wife started talking about how she wanted to bake a cake She wanted the cake to look like a pizza This made rob VERY hungry for real pizza
text_b_pos: Rob and his wife ordered a pizza.
text_b_neg: Rob does not like pizza at all.

text_a: All my friends are big football fans. I sometimes watch matches with them. I'm not a fan but still predict who's going to win. So far I've been really accurate.
text_b_pos: My friends don't like football.
text_b_neg: My friends are very surprised by that.

text_a: Sloane was taking an important test at school. The room was silent. Her pencil broke. The sharpener grated loudly.
text_b_pos: In the very noisy background nobody noticed what Sloane did.
text_b_neg: Everyone in the room looked at her.

text_a: Sue really wanted a new boots. But she couldn't afford them. So her friend brought her to a thrift store. Sue couldn't believe how cheap everything was.
text_b_pos: Sue went home disappointed.
text_b_neg: She ended up finding the perfect pair of boots for her.

text_a: The man had racing thoughts. He told his friends. One of his friends suggested meditation. The man tried meditation.
text_b_pos: He started to become a better cook.
text_b_neg: It took him a while but he started to get calmer.

text_a: Tony bought a grimy old bike. He blasted the frame with sand. He polished it and painted it. He showed it off to all of his friends.
text_b_pos: His friends did not like the bike.
text_b_neg: His friends were impressed by the bike.

text_a: Emily wanted to go to college and study music. She worked hard to prepare an audition piece to sing. At her audition, she sang for the professors and took a music test. The professors were impressed by her audition.
text_b_pos: They were disapointed.
text_b_neg: They praised her performance.

text_a: All of my brothers decided to play a prank on me today. They caught a bunch of bugs and hid them in my shoe. When I put on my shoes, I stepped in all of the bugs. I was so scared that I flung my shoe across the room.
text_b_pos: I bought a new pair of shoes.
text_b_neg: I thought it was a mean prank.

text_a: I got up from a nap feeling very hungry. I walked into my kitchen and began to look for a snack. Suddenly I saw a rat running through my cabinet. I closed the cabinet and quickly called an inspector.
text_b_pos: I was relieved the inspector caught the rat.
text_b_neg: Without fear I chased the rat out of the flat.

text_a: David had to go to court. He stood in front and made his vow. He was very anxious and stuttered. The judge said he was guilty.
text_b_pos: David was smiling
text_b_neg: David broke down in tears

text_a: Jordan was happy to go to Dylan's candy bar for the very first time. The entire store was filled with the most amazing goodies. Jordan immediately went over to the chocolate fountain to try it. The taste was impeccable.
text_b_pos: They both didn't really like sweets.

text_b_neg: He could not pay for the ticket, but took the train anyway.

text_a: Tom was divorced. He had a son that he wanted to keep. They were fighting for rights. Tom thought he could buy his son's love with gifts.
text_b_pos: Tom's son wanted to stay at his mother's.
text_b_neg: Tom's son loves to play.

text_a: As a reward for starting to eat healthy, I got a bad case of diarrhea. I ran to the stall at work, but there was no toilet paper. Neither of the stalls next to me had toilet paper either. I decided I had to take drastic measures to clean up.
text_b_pos: I cleaned myself making use of toilet paper and a standard technique.
text_b_neg: I had to use the water of the sink to clean the mess as well as I could.

text_a: The scientists waited for the rover to send images of Mars. The signal from the rover stopped. The rover had crashed on the surface of the planet. They discovered they were all using different units of measurement.
text_b_pos: The scientists celebrated the arrival of the signal.
text_b_neg: The scientists decided to adopt a consistent system for measurement.

text_a: Mark Anthony was an exceptional surgeon. One evening while performing a hysterectomy he noticed something. A throat lozenge was laying in inside of the patient's vaginal cavity. He looked around and noticed his assistant Kristoff looked sheepish.
text_b_pos: He let his assistnat have a rest.
text_b_neg: He let his assistant perform the hysterectomy

text_a: I had no school today since it's Veteran's Day. Therefore, I decided to go to the park with my friends. We mostly played basketball together. Eventually, it started to rain outside.
text_b_pos: Everyone went home.
text_b_neg: We stayed and danced in train rain.

text_a: Rena really wanted a new Kelly bag. She drove to the Hermes store but they did not have any. Rena was disappointed but looked online. Finally she saw the perfect pink color.
text_b_pos: Rena looked elsewhere for a different bag.
text_b_neg: Rena immediately bought the bag.

text_a: The other day my friend Rick bought a TV. He asked our friend Jeff to help him move it into his room. As they were carrying it Jeff's foot slipped on a rug. The TV went slipped and the screen shattered completely.
text_b_pos: After they finished moving the TV, Rick and Jeff started watching a movie.
text_b_neg: Rick was very sad that his TV was broken.

text_a: Today I taught my friend and how to jump rope. She figured it out very quickly. She is almost as good as me already. She makes me jump faster and higher because I want to the best.
text_b_pos: I don't like jumping rope anymore.
text_b_neg: Tomorrow my friend and I will participate in a jump contest.

text_a: Ramona went to her first horse racing event the other day. She actually found it to be quite fun. She didn't realize how fun it would be. She started betting on horses and winning.
text_b_pos: She won a fortune.
text_b_neg: She stopped liking horses.

text_a: Tammy was feeling pretty sick. She had the day off from work. Her boyfriend wanted to make her feel better. He decided to make her breakfast in bed.
text_b_pos: She was delighted.
text_b_neg: She was mad at him.

text_a: Kim was a waitress at the local breakfast joint. Every morning, she served coffee and pancakes with a smile. When she retired, the locals threw her a huge party. They brought her coffee and gave her a hole host of presents.
text_b_pos: The best thing about the presents was that people proposed her to come cook for her.
text_b_neg: She received a lot of food, enough for her to survive months.

text_a: I wanted to buy a yacht. I went on Craigslist. I found a good deal. I gave the dealer an offer he couldn't refuse.
text_b_pos: So we met and he sold the yacht to me.
text_b_neg: The dealer gave me the yacht as a present in exchange for my underwear.

text_a: Matt wanted to learn how to swim. He joined at class at the YMCA. He was nervous, but one of the instructors helped him. Eventually Matt got better at holding his breath.
text_b_pos: Matt hates water.
text_b_neg: Matt can now dive for more than two minutes.

text_a: Brenda bought a new blender. She was excited to try it at home. She plugged it in and turned it on. It did not start.
text_b_pos: Brenda wrote an angry complain.
text_b_neg: Brenda was happy and drank a coke.

text_a: Matt couldn't find a job. So he decided to beg for money. He wore dirty, old clothes and help up a sign on the street. And he made minimum wage.
text_b_pos: Teachers around the world started encouraging Matt-like behaviors.
text_b_neg: Matt is a shame for society.

text_a: Jake was playing golf with his father. Jake accidentally swung his golf club into the lake. He had to retrieve it by walking into the lake. Jake had to play the rest of the game with wet shoes.
text_b_pos: The father was proud of his son's swing.
text_b_neg: The shoes started falling apart and he had to buy a new pair.

text_a: My daughter's best friend in BC, Sara,  had a baby in June. Today Sara took photos of her baby. She dressed her up in BC clothing. Sara posted the photos on FB.
text_b_pos: Sara has three kids.
text_b_neg: I commented that the baby looks cute.

text_a: Tom was using his car's cigarette outlet. He was charging his phone with it. It stopped working. Tom realized a fuse was blown out.
text_b_pos: Tom's phone ran out of battery.
text_b_neg: Tom figured that he needed to buy a new cigarette outlet.

text_a: Elena got into a car accident. Since she was at fault, she had to pay a large amount to the victim. Nate received a phone call from Elena. She asked him to loan some money to her.
text_b_pos: Nate did not recognize her voice and hung up.
text_b_neg: Since she was a good friend Nate lend her the money.

text_a: Amber was playing hide and seek with her friends. She was 'it'. She searched high and low for where her friends were hiding. But she couldn't find any of them and gave up.
text_b_pos: She became an amazing scientist.
text_b_neg: Her paranoia kicked in and she dropped out of school.

text_a: Kelly was eager to attend her family Christmas party. But then her friend asked her for help on Christmas. He said he was volunteering at a homeless shelter and needed help! Kelly knew her time could be better spent helping others.
text_b_pos: Her family understood and supported her.
text_b_neg: Her family didn't want kelly to help strangers.

text_a: Maggie's 60th Birthday is approaching. She is fearful of growing old. Watching a commercial she sees an anti-aging cream. Maggie reaches into her purse for her credit card.
text_b_pos: She purchased the cream using the credit card.
text_b_neg: She bought a new handbag for herself.

text_a: Katherine enjoyed berets a lot. She loved wearing them as an accessory. One day, she realized she didn't have any more berets. Katherine immediately rushed to the store.
text_b_pos: Katherina bought two new berets.
text_b_neg: Katherina never wore any berets again.

text_a: Blair was visiting the museum with her family. She got caught up reading an interesting art exhibit. When she looked up she realized that her parents had left. She searched all over the museum to find them but she was lost.
text_b_pos: Blair enjoyed being alone.
text_b_neg: She was scared that they forgot her.

text_a: My coworker Sally just ended a ten-year affair. The affair ended after the man's wife threatened a divorce. Sally was sad as her man has refused to talk to her. Yesterday she posted a TBT FB post about how they used to kiss.
text_b_pos: The man was the first to like the post.
text_b_neg: The man finally talked to Sally and asked her to remove the post.

text_a: Igor was having trouble controlling his Great Dane. It pulled on the leash so hard he lost his grip on it. Igor's dog ran out into traffic. A large Greyhound bus ran straight over it.
text_b_pos: The dog died and Igor was heartbroken.
text_b_neg: The dog died and Igor was estatic.

text_a: Last week I went rappelling with my friends. At the top of the cliff I was harnessed and ready to go. I held onto the rope with fear. I was afraid I would get hurt.
text_b_pos: But I made it over without getting hurt.
text_b_neg: I was not afraid of falling.

text_a: Craig was working the whole night on a new computer program. The program would make typos and grammar disappear. He put his program up for sell on Amazon. The program sold like hotcakes for the whole month.
text_b_pos: Craig went to the swimming pool with his girlfriend.
text_b_neg: Craig became rich.

text_a: I had to fix my gutters. They were full of leaves and fell out of the roof. I climbed up on a ladder and couldn't reach. When I attempted to get higher, the ladder fell down.
text_b_pos: This was the funniest day in my life.
text_b_neg: Unfortunately I broke my leg.

text_a: Maggie decided to go out for a run. She loved running in the woods. She found it relaxing. To her dismay there was a bear.
text_b_pos: She enjoyed her running.
text_b_neg: She screamed and ran away.

text_a: Chuck watched as the number of hits diminished. Be had to work fast while maintaining quality. He struggled to come up with a story idea. Suddenly he realized that that in itself is a story idea.
text_b_pos: He enjoyed writing.
text_b_neg: He went to eat some food.

text_a: Kate and her friends had a suite at a hotel in Vegas. When they opened the door their jaws dropped. The room was decorated to look very expensive. Kate thought this was a place for a celebrity to stay.
text_b_pos: Kate loved the thought of sleeping in this suite.
text_b_neg: Kate was disappointed by the suite.

text_a: One day Henry was walking towards his mailbox. He noticed a small young kitten in the grass. Henry picked up the cat and noticed it had no tag. He asked his neighbors if they knew the cat.
text_b_pos: They were glad he found their kitten.
text_b_neg: He then abandoned the kitten on the street.

text_a: Melissa was 20 pounds overweight. She hated to workout or participate in any kind of exercise. She didn't want to give up the foods she loved. A friend suggested that she just cut down on 25% of the food she eats.
text_b_pos: They both got married.
text_b_neg: She didn't listen and now eats 25% more.

text_a: There was a boy who wanted to join the scouts. His parents were happy he wanted to. They didn't want him hanging out with the wrong kids. He joined the scouts and learned good morals.
text_b_pos: His parents were very pleasant.
text_b_neg: His parents punished him.

text_a: Tim never cooked his own food and ate at the restaurant. When a blackout affected his whole city, he was panicked. He barely had anything to eat at home. His neighbor, who was friendly, invited him in.
text_b_pos: They danced all night.
text_b_neg: He prepared dinner for him.

text_a: Robert was a running back for his whole career. When he hurt his knee he was unable to run as fast as before. His coach decided to make him a quarterback instead. Robert tried his best but just couldn't play the position well.
text_b_pos: Robert kept playing as quarterback very well.
text_b_neg: Robert retired from playing football.

text_a: Mr Qu was a famous statesman from China. He wanted to improve the quality of life in his country. He started a water quality project. He saved many lives.
text_b_pos: Mr. Qu regretted his project.
text_b_neg: Mr. Qu went on to make more wells in China.

text_a: Timmy loves floats and colors. He was excited for the parade. He got up early and got a good seat. His family accompanied him.
text_b_pos: Everyone enjoyed the parade.
text_b_neg: Timmy was bored at the parade.

text_a: Valerie played around on her boyfriend, Matt. She fell for Tim, one of the many guys she'd cheated with. She broke up with Matt and started dating Tim. Tim had no respect for her or their relationship.
text_b_pos: She was very happy.
text_b_neg: She was very regertful.

text_a: I woke up unusually early this morning. The sun was just starting to rise. In the darkness, I saw the first snowfall of the year. The huge flakes were falling slowly and beautifully.
text_b_pos: I put on my gloves and jacket and went outside.
text_b_neg: People had already built an igloo.

text_a: Jen saw a house for rent, as she was walking one day. She wrote down the number on the sign out front and decided to call. The landlord gave a great offer for rent, and Jen decided to pursue it. After submitting her paperwork, she waited to hear back.
text_b_pos: She got the house.
text_b_neg: She left for another country.

text_a: Larry was a small kid. He always got picked on. One day a bully picked him up and shook his change out. Larry had no money to eat lunch.
text_b_pos: The bully shared his lunch with him.
text_b_neg: His best friend shared his lunch with him.

text_a: The yearly family reunion for the Rollins family was very soon. Everybody always looked forward to the gathering. They usually had the reunion in a park with lots of room. The weather was beautiful for the reunion.
text_b_pos: Everybody brought food and shared it.
text_b_neg: The parents decided to stay home and watch TV.

text_a: Tina decided on going hiking with her friend Tony. They both decided on a difficult path. Upon ascension, Tina fell and cut her leg. They both decided it was too dangerous for them to continue.
text_b_pos: So they asked for helped and a helicopter came to rescue them.
text_b_neg: So they continued mountain up and completed a wonderful adventure.

text_a: Evan woke up in the middle of the night to pee. He always woke at least once. Sometimes he woke up two or three times! Finally he decided not to drink anything for five hours before bed.
text_b_pos: He began peeing more frequently.
text_b_neg: He did not wake up during the night anymore.

text_a: I wanted my own show on Oprah's network. I mapped out a short tv cooking show outline. I wrote a three minute script about food preparation. I submitted my audition tape to the OWN network.
text_b_pos: I got my own game show.
text_b_neg: I did not make it through the first round.

text_a: It was time for the Cook's to go own their annual summer vacation. All of the hotel reservations had been made. They rented a van to drive to Florida. On the drive there they learned a hurricane was eminent.
text_b_pos: They loved their summer vacation.
text_b_neg: They drove back home for safe.

text_a: A puppy named Princess was left alone for the day. It was awfully quiet, with not a person to play with. Her ears drooped to the side, and she curled up into a ball. She thought she was alone until she heard a man call.
text_b_pos: The man was standing right in front of the puppy all day already.
text_b_neg: The voice was coming from outside the window though.

text_a: Jimmy was watching cartoons. He was sitting on his couch. Jimmy was busy eating a bag of chips. He was watching his favorite show South Park.
text_b_pos: Jimmy was happy and enjoyed his free day.
text_b_neg: Jimmy was sad and wished he could do something else.

text_a: Abigail was in class when the bell for lunch rang. She suddenly remembered that she had forgotten her lunch money check. She couldn't afford any food so she went straight to sitting down. Her friend joined her soon and saw that she had no food.
text_b_pos: Abigail's friend offered to share her food.
text_b_neg: Abigail's friend laughed at her and ate everything.

text_a: John's stomach was burning. And everything he ate made it worse. But he read that bananas are a natural antacid. And eating one made him feel better.
text_b_pos: A couple of hours later his problem had completely vanished.
text_b_neg: A couple of hours later John's skin problem was over.

text_a: Kate had something stuck in her teeth. She got a piece of floss to help her. She flossed her teeth over and over again. She just couldn't get it!
text_b_pos: So she drank a bottle of beer.
text_b_neg: So she gave up.

text_a: Tori loved cake. She went to a fancy bakery to get some. She could not decide between two flavors of cake. Finally, she selected the green tea flavored cake.
text_b_pos: She enjoyed the cake very much.
text_b_neg: She was sick of its green appearance.

text_a: I wanted to save a little money at the store. I knew the kids wanted doritos. I saw a bag of doritos styled generic chips. They were only a dollar, so I bought them.
text_b_pos: Instead of giving them to the kids, I ate them myself.
text_b_neg: I threw away the doritos.

text_a: The children waited quietly in the loft of the barn. Two adults were sneaking into the entrance. The children opened fire. The adults vests buzzed.
text_b_pos: They were all dead.
text_b_neg: The children cheered in delight.

text_a: It was the 4th of July. But Tim hated loud noises. So he stayed in his room and wore ear plugs. And he wished the night would end.
text_b_pos: He had never slept so peacefully before.
text_b_neg: The sun finally rose.

text_a: Cathy wanted to plant a vegetable garden in her backyard. She shopped at a home and garden center, planning her garden. She purchased her supplies, including tools, dirt and seeds. She spread the dirt and planted the seeds, using the tools.
text_b_pos: She was dreaming of the beautiful flowers in the future.
text_b_neg: She was dreaming of the delicious vegetables in the future.

text_a: I kept trying to get my nails to grow out. As soon as they got past the tip of my fingers, they got brittle. They began to peel in layers. I was annoyed because they were also breaking.
text_b_pos: My nails grew long enough that I could apply nail polish.
text_b_neg: I then decided to cut them short.

text_a: Tim read poetry and it made him experience unique feelings. He pursued these positive feelings. He learned that language is our prison and our palace. He learned we are limited by our language.
text_b_pos: Tim hates poetry.
text_b_neg: Tim loved poetic language.

text_a: Hugo saw his friend sprain his ankle. He told his friend to drop out of the big race. His friend ignored him. So he told his trainer.
text_b_pos: The trainer had no time to take care of it.
text_b_neg: The coach came to his friend and pulled him out of the race.

text_a: Tommy was angrily staring at the clock. His mom was supposed to get him out of school so he could get a puppy. She didn't show up. After School she was parked outside waiting.
text_b_pos: Tommy was excited and ran to the car.
text_b_neg: Tommy and his mom did not find the puppy.

text_a: I placed the burrito wrap into the toaster. After several seconds, it was finished. I tried to get the wrap out of the toaster however, it got stuck. The wrap also became burnt.
text_b_pos: The wrap was delicious.
text_b_neg: I had to do another one.

text_a: Barney went on his first hunting trip. His friends helped him find a good spot to hunt. He still was unable to catch anything. On the way home his friend spotted a deer.
text_b_pos: They shot the deer together.
text_b_neg: They ran away in fear.

text_a: Joe loved to rap. He invited a couple of his friends over so they can rap. His friends came with snacks and drinks. They played a beat through Joe's speakers.
text_b_pos: After that they chilled out while drinking and eating.
text_b_neg: Joe didn't feel hungry.

text_a: It was an extremely hot day. So Jill decided to eat some ice cream. But soon after, she still felt hot. So she ate more ice cream.
text_b_pos: The day got much chillier after noon.
text_b_neg: Jill felt really sick pretty soon after.

text_a: Tim wanted to buy a new video game that was very popular. He didn't have enough money to buy the game right away. Tim was determined to earn money and did extra chores at home. Tim's mom gave him the money he earned.
text_b_pos: Tim bought the video game.
text_b_neg: Tim spent the money on clothes.

text_a: Pablo had several health issues. He learned he had a bad infection in his leg. Pablo had to have his leg amputated. He was given a prosthetic but he was nervous about using it.
text_b_pos: He was so glad he'd been given help.
text_b_neg: He felt awkward wearing the prosthetic in public.

text_a: William was allergic to cats. He went to his friend's house where there were 3 cats. Williams eyes became very itchy. William's friend gave him some allergy medicine.
text_b_pos: The medicine made it better.
text_b_neg: The cats were allergic to the medicine.

text_a: Riley was planning for his upcoming thirtieth birthday party. He decided to have a fish fry and invite his friends. He bought fish, chips, and drinks for the party. That evening, Riley and his friends cooked and ate together.
text_b_pos: Riley sang and danced all night.
text_b_neg: Riley tried to win the game.

text_a: Jan met her boyfriend at work. The relationship was going great until one day. Jan catches her boyfriend cheating on her with another girl. Jan tells her boyfriend is over.
text_b_pos: He tried winning her back by apologizing and sending flowers.
text_b_neg: Jan changed her mind and took him back two days later.

text_a: It was a beautiful and sunny day in Florida. The Smith family decided to go to the beach. They packed sun screen, towels, shovels and buckets. When they got to the beach they built a large sand castle.
text_b_pos: The kids were proud of what they did.
text_b_neg: The kids felt sorry of what they did.

text_a: Peter came home to find his dog eating a chocolate bar. Upon searching online, he learned that it was very bad for dogs. Peter panicked and rushed the dog to the vet. The vet said the dog was going to be okay.
text_b_pos: But after a few days, the dog died.
text_b_neg: The doctor prescribed one chocolate bar a day for his dog.

text_a: I woke up early in order to study. I met up with my friends at the library. We reserved a studying room on the first floor. A few hours have passed since we stayed for a while.
text_b_pos: We were really tired and decided to pause and take a rest.
text_b_neg: I forgot to bring my textbooks to the library.

text_a: On my birthday I went bowling one year. I was very nervous since I've never gone before. My mom told me that I'd do fine so I tried my best. I didn't do so great but I definitely did okay.
text_b_pos: I hated my mother.
text_b_neg: I was satisfied with myself.

text_a: Brian needed some new tennis shoes. Brian went to the store to buy new shoes. Brian found Nike shoes for $100. Brian paid the cashier and took the shoes home.
text_b_pos: Afterwards Brian thought he should have spent less than $150.
text_b_neg: Afterwards Brian regretted having spent all that money.

text_a: Morgan was sifting through the pond with her net. She loved searching for frogs! After a few minutes, she felt her net catch something. It was a giant, green frog!
text_b_pos: She was upset at the frog.
text_b_neg: She was happy.

text_a: Harry loved to ski but his family did not have very much money. Instead of skiing alot, he read alot about ski destinations. One day, his friend told him about a local contest for a ski trip. Harry put in his entry and waited anxiously for the results.
text_b_pos: Harry won the trip.
text_b_neg: Harry learned to ski.

text_a: Marvin asked his wife to prepare a dinner for his business associates. She wasn't a very good cook, so she called a restaurant. They brought her a catered meal. All the guests raved about the food.
text_b_pos: She was very proud of her cooking.
text_b_neg: She felt a bit ashamed of her lie.

text_a: Tom was a kind young child. Tom was picked on by a bully at school. Tom asked his father what to do. Tom's father taught him self defense.
text_b_pos: He refused to learn self defense.
text_b_neg: He was then never bullied anymore.

text_a: Joan had a big crush on a popular teen heart-throb. She wrote a fan letter and told her friends about it. Later, Joan told her friends she got a reply. She said the teen star wrote he fell in love with her letter.
text_b_pos: Joan was very happy about that.
text_b_neg: Joan decieded not to contact with her friend.

text_a: Anna agreed to a blind date. She met the man for dinner. She expected to dislike him. But they actually got on very well!
text_b_pos: They fought a lot.
text_b_neg: They are now together for six months.

text_a: Ken worked a lot for charities. He would volunteer his spare time rather than be paid. He got huge satisfaction from helping people. He also enjoyed looking at the donations before anyone else.
text_b_pos: He was a good person and got many thanks.
text_b_neg: Nobody liked Ken.

text_a: Mindy came to work tired after pulling an all-nighter. As soon as she sat in her box office, she fell asleep. Her boss noticed her. He knocked on her desk to wake her up.
text_b_pos: Mindy was worried that her boss would fire her for that.
text_b_neg: Her boss was happy about what she did.

text_a: Allie had very frizzy hair. She needed a treatment for it. So she decided to go and get it done. After the treatment her hair was like silk.
text_b_pos: She became bald.
text_b_neg: She never had do brush it again.

text_a: Emma wanted a dog but her husband didn't. He said Emma could foster a dog temporarily. She happily brought one home. Soon they both began to love it.
text_b_pos: They kept the dog for many years.
text_b_neg: The were looking forward to getting rid of the dog soon.

text_a: A child rolled a ball down a grassy hill. The ball kept rolling until it went halfway up the other hill nearby. Then the ball rolled back and settled in the middle of the two hills. The child himself rolled down the hill after the ball.
text_b_pos: But it hurt himself really badly.
text_b_neg: The kid would like to have a ball.

text_a: Tina saw on the television that it would be raining on Easter Day. She was worried that her children wouldn't be able to do an egg hunt. On Easter day, it was pouring down rain. When there was finally a break in the storm, she ran out to hide eggs.
text_b_pos: Tina's children were happy they could do an egg hunt.
text_b_neg: Tina's children were on vacation.

text_a: The dog backed away from the door when she saw it was raining. Her owner grabbed her by the collar. The dog found herself pushed outside into the wet garden. She ran onto the muddy grass to do her business quickly.
text_b_pos: She then ran back to the house.
text_b_neg: The dog likes to play with her owner.

text_a: Jen won two tickets to a concert. She got the night off from work. Then she invited Sally to go with her. Sally couldn't go.
text_b_pos: Jen was mad at Sally.
text_b_neg: Jen went to the concert alone.

text_a: Gina's sisters and friend were playing Spades. She was losing and didn't like it. But everyone else was having a great time. She didn't want to spoil their fun.
text_b_pos: She told her friends that she didn't like the game.
text_b_neg: So she kept playing.

text_a: Sam wanted to throw her mom a birthday party. Sam decided to keep it secret and set to planning. She called her mom on the day and asked to take her to dinner. She secretly drove her mom to the party.
text_b_pos: Sam's mom was very excited about the party.
text_b_neg: Sam's mom enjoyed her dinner.

text_a: Two actors were in competition for a spot in a dog food commercial. The director could not decide between them so he offered a solution. Whichever actor are more of the dog food would do the commercial. The actors ferociously ate the dog food until they were too full.
text_b_pos: From now on the actors only ate dog food.
text_b_neg: The actors were both too sick to do the commercial.

text_a: A bird landed on Bea's front stoop. He tweeted loudly and flapped his wings. Bea came outside to see what the racket was. When she opened the door, the bird flew inside!
text_b_pos: She kept the door open to let the bird out.
text_b_neg: She closed the door.

text_a: Alejandro has never been to a zoo. His boyfriend surprised him to a trip to the zoo on his birthday. Alejandro got to see so many animals he has never seen in person. His favorite animals were the otters and elephants.
text_b_pos: He was bored, because he had seen the animals before.
text_b_neg: It was an amazing birthday present.

text_a: Phil put a tape recorder in his shirt pocket all day. At night he shut it off and transcribed the day. He tried to put on a play using the transcription as the script. The show was a hit in the art world.
text_b_pos: That was the end for his relationship.
text_b_neg: He felt like a genius.

text_a: I found out that my friend had been lying to me. He had also stolen all of my money. When I confronted him, he said I was crazy. When he said this, I provided proof.
text_b_pos: I like spending money.
text_b_neg: We never talked again.

text_a: Mara wanted to make her own pizza. She made fresh dough and sauce. Then she sliced her own veggies and sausage. After the pizza finished baking, she tasted it.
text_b_pos: She didn't like to eat pizza.
text_b_neg: It tasted well for her first try.

text_a: The tigers were the most famous animals in the zoo. People would always stop to check them out. One day, the zoo visitors watched the tigers eat huge steaks. They ripped the meat apart.
text_b_pos: People clapped.
text_b_neg: The zoo tigers were very tame.

text_a: Aya woke early one morning to surprise her husband with a hot meal. He began work at 6AM, so usually she was only awake to say goodbye. But this morning, she made him a big hot dish of scrambled eggs. Then she woke him and smiled as he dove in - until he grimaced.
text_b_pos: There was a big piece of the shell in the egg.
text_b_neg: She slaughtered the chicken.

text_a: Joseph has always wanted a dog since he was little. For the summer, he was to take care of his grandparent's dog. He was able to play with Rover, their shepherd, on a daily basis. Joseph was upset that he couldn't take Rover home with him.
text_b_pos: He was already looking forward to next summer.
text_b_neg: At least there were many cats in the neighbourhood he lived in.
