text_a: The family adopted a child. The child fit in well with the family. The family talked about adopting another kid. There adopted child felt nervous about that.
text_b_pos: Now he has a friend with whom he can play and share his favorite toys.
text_b_neg: But as soon as he got a brother all the worries were away.

text_a: Eric's grandfather died. His greedy aunt threw away all of his grandfather's things. She only kept the money. So Eric dug through the trash filled with his grandfather's things.
text_b_pos: He started to cry because of his heartless aunt.
text_b_neg: He was sad about not finding any money.

text_a: Tom sweat more than most people. Tom's girlfriend joked about how much he sweats. Tom took 3 showers per day to counteract the sweating. Tom was a very clean person because of his hygeine.
text_b_pos: Tom's girlfriend did not want to play with him.
text_b_neg: Tom's girlfriend liked to smell him.

text_a: Jan dreamed of being a ballet dancer ever since she was a little girl. Jan began taking dance lessons at a very early age. Jan decided to audition for a local ballet academy. Jan scored the highest out of all the auditions for the academy.
text_b_pos: Jan was accepted to the ballet academy.
text_b_neg: The ballet academy decided to accpet a different dancer instead.

text_a: Jim was dismayed when the padded arm of his chair came off. He tried to put it back in place, but it wouldn't stay. He pondered what he could do about it. Jim rifled through his utility box and found some super glue.
text_b_pos: He used the glue to fix the chair.
text_b_neg: Jim glued the padded arm to the utility box.

text_a: Rita plays tennis. Her serve is terrible. Rita decided to ask for help. She hired a coach to help her.
text_b_pos: The coach did not like tennis.
text_b_neg: Rita progressed very quickly.

text_a: Our son celebrated his 27th birthday today. We took him out to a local Italian restaurant. We asked his aunt to go as well. Traffic was bad and we were delayed.
text_b_pos: His aunt ate her pizza alone.
text_b_neg: Our son had so much fun.

text_a: Stella loved to shop. One day, Stella went to the mall and bought some dresses. Of course, she then had to buy shoes to match the dresses. Next, she bought purses to match the shoes that matched the dresses.
text_b_pos: Finally, she spent all money she had.
text_b_neg: She became a rich women.

text_a: Henry is a four-year old boy who lives down the hall from us. I met Henry and his mother Julia while sitting on a bench outside. Henry and Julia were very friendly to me. I gave Henry a few toys because I liked him.
text_b_pos: Henry threw the toys at me because he didn't like me.
text_b_neg: Henry always likes to play with my toys.

text_a: Nate asked Benny who took his wallet. Benny told him that his mom had the wallet. However, Nate's mom said that she didn't have anything. Nate returned to Benny to ask if he was lying.
text_b_pos: Benny admitted to have caused the car accident.
text_b_neg: Benny admitted to have taken the wallet.

text_a: Martin wanted to learn karate. He got the idea after watching martial arts movies. However, he was quickly bored with his first lessons. His teacher lectured him, saying he was too impatient.
text_b_pos: Today is a hot day.
text_b_neg: After three years he got the black belt.

text_a: Although Colin is a white guy, Charles asked him to be his roommate. Charles, who is black, trusted Colin in the apartment. Colin, however, started stealing from Charles' room. Charles called Colin and said return my things or I'll kick your butt.
text_b_pos: Colin apologized and returned all the things, feeling awful.
text_b_neg: Colin refused and they became very good friends.

text_a: Swarthanger took a leisurely stroll down Broad St. He noticed a man on top of a ledge of a building. Swarthanger screamed and told him not to jump. He said he would buy him an ice cream cone if he didn't.
text_b_pos: Swarthanger sold his car to the man.
text_b_neg: Swarthanger bought an ice cream for him after the man came down.

text_a: Kurt cooked the burgers at the company picnic. When everyone had gotten theirs, he put one more patty on the grill. It was orange and rubbery, not at all like beef. Kurt offered a prize to whoever could guess the meat he'd used.
text_b_pos: No one got it right.
text_b_neg: His colleagues were offended.

text_a: Brad, Sally, and Mike were playing poker. Mike was winning almost every hand. Sally thought he might be cheating. She then began observing him fiddling with his sleeve.
text_b_pos: She found cards and stopped playing.
text_b_neg: Brad had pizza for dinner.

text_a: Brian has two younger brothers who do as he says. He has never been the kindest older brother. Sometimes he lies to get what he wants. His younger brothers caught him in a lie and stopped trusting him.
text_b_pos: Thirty years later, they don't speak at all.
text_b_neg: Their parents were happy that they only had two sons.

text_a: The nation was tense. Their president had just declared war. The soldiers prepared for battle. It was the first war they'd been in in decades.
text_b_pos: They didn't know whether their training had prepared them adequately.
text_b_neg: They were confident it would be a harmless skirmish.

text_a: I have been hearing this squeaking the past days at home. I can never pinpoint where it is coming from. I have been going crazy trying to figure out what it is. Finally I figured it out.
text_b_pos: The squeaking was coming from my shoes.
text_b_neg: I still do not know where squeaking is coming from.

text_a: The kitchen faucet had started to leak. Although it was fairly new, it was of poor quality. I decided to buy a better-quality faucet through mail-order. When my new faucet arrived, I replaced the old one with it.
text_b_pos: The kitchen faucet was still leaking.
text_b_neg: The kitchen faucet did not leak anymore.

text_a: Ethan was entered in a bike race. He had bought a brand new bike for the race. He practiced everyday on his street in his neighborhood. The day of the race he was very nervous.
text_b_pos: He feared he was too good for the others.
text_b_neg: He was never in a bike competition before.

text_a: Riki went to her boyfriend's house for Thanksgiving. His dad had made a huge turkey with a bunch of side dishes. Riki ate a lot more than she'd intended to. She let out a loud burp right there at the table!
text_b_pos: Her boyfriend's family laughed at her.
text_b_neg: Riki was determined to eat the entire turkey.

text_a: Graham was unhappy in his relationship. His girlfriend seemed distant and cold. He asked her what was wrong and she was unhappy as well. They both went their separate ways.
text_b_pos: Graham didn't care.
text_b_neg: Graham was relieved she felt the same way.

text_a: Shelle loves to play tennis. However, she has a horrible backhand. Everytime she plays a match she loses by one point. Shelle decided to take private lessons to help.
text_b_pos: Shelle is now a professional basket ball player.
text_b_neg: Shelle is now unstoppable at Tennis!

text_a: My husband took a shower this morning. Afterward he started to trim his beard. Just as he started, his trimmer died on him. He couldn't find a charger to get it working again.
text_b_pos: So he could not trim his bed today.
text_b_neg: He continued to trim his bed.

text_a: Eliza pretended to be sick to stay home from school. After her parents left for work, she turned on the tv. The tv didn't turn on. Eliza flickered the lights, and realized the power was out.
text_b_pos: Eliza then thought going to school would have been more fun.
text_b_neg: Eliza then decided to watch her favourite movie.

text_a: James woke up early on Sunday morning. He put on his best suit and tie for the big event. His minivan sped towards the church building. James preached his sermon to the congregation.
text_b_pos: No one listened.
text_b_neg: Everyone listened.

text_a: Ike loved to fish. He went all year long. In the winter the ice fished. He caught lots of big ones.
text_b_pos: Ike loves animals and would never harm them.
text_b_neg: He invited all of his friends for a big fish meal.

text_a: Lawrence had big dreams. He wanted to join the circus and be a clown. A lot of people told him that was crazy. Lawrence was determined to realize his dreams.
text_b_pos: Eventually he could join a circus and follow his dream of becoming a trapeze artist.
text_b_neg: After years of practice he managed to become the greatest clown ever existed.

text_a: Karen's sister was coming to town. Karen was very excited. She planned many fun activities. The day they went to the beach, it rained.
text_b_pos: They wished it snowed.
text_b_neg: They had to spent entire day indoors.

text_a: Bob opened the curtains. There were birds in the yard. They were eating his garden plants. He ran outside yelling.
text_b_pos: He chased the birds away and decided to erect a scarecrow.
text_b_neg: And the birds yelled back at him.

text_a: Today I woke up at 0500. I put on my uniform and drove to formation. It was a quick formation and the we started to exercise. We stretched, ran four miles, and the stretched again.
text_b_pos: We were very exhausted afterwards.
text_b_neg: We decided to start exercising.

text_a: Jake got hired to be an extra in a movie. He was excited about it. He told everyone he knew. He went to go see the movie opening night.
text_b_pos: No one knew about it.
text_b_neg: He felt proud.

text_a: David and Saul awoke early one morning. The gathered their gear and made their way to the small boat. The boat set sail and carried them far out into the sea. When they arrived at the site the men began to fish.
text_b_pos: David caught a bigger fish than Saul.
text_b_neg: Saul and David got into a fight and sunk the boat.

text_a: Fred has a fever. He was not able to go to work. He had to call out. His work boss was angry.
text_b_pos: He fired Fred in that very moment.
text_b_neg: He gave Fred a raise.

text_a: Sam was at his friend's wedding rehearsal. He started drinking too early. When his toast came up he was already too drunk. Sam made a lot of rude comments.
text_b_pos: Everyone was embarrassed.
text_b_neg: The bride thanked him for his comments.

text_a: Keith is on vacation in the woods with his family. He rents a nice little log cabin next to the water. One evening he hears a noise outside. He heads out to investigate at sees a huge bear!
text_b_pos: He froze on the spot.
text_b_neg: He loved it.

text_a: Ally was so excited to be able to see the pandas at the zoo. The area around their enclosure was packed. But the pandas were asleep so people moved on. But Ally waited and waited.
text_b_pos: She decided to scream to wake them up.
text_b_neg: The pandas didn't wake up until after the zoo closed.

text_a: Ed bet Frank he couldn't beat him at an ice cream eating contest. The loser would have to wear a dress to school the next day. Ed couldn't wait to see Frank embarrass himself at school! But Frank was a fierce competitor, easily beating Ed.
text_b_pos: Frank ended up wearing the dress to school.
text_b_neg: Now Ed had to wear the emarassing dress to school.

text_a: Amy was starting a work at home job. She was to attend training via an online conference. Amy followed along afraid she was misunderstanding. Finally she decided to ask a question to make sure she understood.
text_b_pos: She unmuted herself and spoke into the microphone.
text_b_neg: She raised her hand and waited to be noticed.

text_a: Lydia woke up at 3am and was hungry, but her parents were asleep. She crept out of bed and past her parents' room to the kitchen. She checked the cupboard and found some noodles. She opened the bag, cooked them in a big pot.
text_b_pos: She was not feeling like eating anymore.
text_b_neg: She went straight back to her room and enjoyed the noodles.

text_a: Yesterday at school Marcus got in trouble for wearing a skirt. The principal told Marcus that only girls could wear skirts. This made Marcus very angry. He got his peers to sign a petition to present to the principal.
text_b_pos: Some boys wore skirts to support Marcus.
text_b_neg: Marcus went home and put pants on.

text_a: Helunko Spelunko was a combat developer for a video game. He promised that in the next update, there would be a focus on PvP. He introduced a terrible open world PvP zone. Players ended up fighting more computer enemies than other players.
text_b_pos: He was proud of what he accomplished.
text_b_neg: He failed at his task.

text_a: Jack was starting kindergarten. He was scared. He had never even been to daycare. His mom walked him to the door and kissed him bye.
text_b_pos: As she left Jack looked after her missing her already.
text_b_neg: Jack was happy that his mom left.

text_a: Wanda used to be vehemently against ad blockers. She argued that they robbed websites of their revenue. Yesterday, she found out her computer was slowed down by adware. She promptly installed an ad blocker.
text_b_pos: The ad blocker further slowed her computer.
text_b_neg: She failed to see the irony.

text_a: Jenna wanted a new haircut. She had her stylist give her bangs. She hated them immediately. She started the long process of growing them out.
text_b_pos: She never went back to that stylist.
text_b_neg: She told her best friend to make bangs.

text_a: Megan was going to find out the gender of her unborn baby. She brought all of her family along for the exciting ultrasound. As the technician searched, she gasped in delight. She announced to everyone that Megan had twins in her.
text_b_pos: The day after Megan decided to name him Alfonso.
text_b_neg: Megan and her family received the news with immense happiness.

text_a: John and Lacey were long distance friends. Even though they lived far away from each other, they always talked. One day, John decided to visit Lacey and bought a plane ticket. When he saw Lacey she was uneasy about his visit.
text_b_pos: They started dating.
text_b_neg: Because Lacey was actually and old man.

text_a: I was browsing the internet when a pop-up screen appeared. It said I had a virus on my computer and gave me a number to call. Worried that I had a virus, I immediately called the number. The person who answered demanded $100 to solve my problem.
text_b_pos: I got suspicious and hung up without transfering any money.
text_b_neg: I talked to the person on the phone a long time and we became good friends.

text_a: One day, Erin decided to have a drink. It was very late at night. Nobody could drive her home. She decided to drive home herself.
text_b_pos: Erin got into an accident.
text_b_neg: Erin had another drink.

text_a: Mary was very self conscious. She always was careful of the pictures she took of herself. One day someone got a picture of there spilling a drink. It ended up in social media.
text_b_pos: Mary was happy that many people liked the photo.
text_b_neg: Mary was very embarassed.

text_a: Fred has always been worried about tasting cabbage. He heard from friends that it tastes funky. Finally he decides he must taste cabbage for himself. Fred loves the taste of cabbage!
text_b_pos: He continued to eat cabbage for his entire life.
text_b_neg: He never ate cabbage again.

text_a: Terry put on his short shorts. He went on a run around the block. A neighbor lady whistled at his legs. Terry stopped to talk to his neighbor.
text_b_pos: Terry convinced her to join for the run.
text_b_neg: The girl joked about the size of the jeans Terry was wearing.

text_a: Tally was getting ready one morning. She was trying to improve her dental habits so she began to floss. Immediately her gums were in a ton of pain. She gave up flossing and searched for a solution.
text_b_pos: She started flossing even longer the next morning.
text_b_neg: With time and practice, the bleeding went away.

text_a: This morning, I attended a training at my work office. The training focused on creating and delivering better presentations. It was very interactive. I gave a brief five minute presentation to the whole class.
text_b_pos: My presentation went horribly wrong.
text_b_neg: The training helped me give a better presentation.

text_a: In college, I heard my first opera. It was called Marriage of Figaro. The singers sang in English so we could understand the words. It was a very funny story.
text_b_pos: I never want to see opera again.
text_b_neg: I want to go hear more operas.

text_a: Rita was cooking a stew. She had used too much salt. The stew was unbearably salty. Rita couldn't eat it.
text_b_pos: Rita finished eating the salty stew.
text_b_neg: Rita gave the stew to a friend.

text_a: It was payday for Sara which meant that she could afford a new phone. When her shift ended, she rushed to the mall before it closed. Eagerly, she went straight to the shelf and grabbed the latest model. Unfortunately, she had to wait for the customer ahead of her.
text_b_pos: After half an hour, she got the phone.
text_b_neg: After seven days, she got the phone.

text_a: I tried out for the baseball team at my high school. I didn't make the team though which was disappointing. The coach said that I need to work on my swing. I have been working hard for months now and I'm getting better.
text_b_pos: I will try again next year.
text_b_neg: I will never play baseball again.

text_a: John walked over to a bus stop and sat down. A strange homeless man walked over to him. The man began to talk to John in a nonsensical way. John began to fear the man's insanity and decided to leave.
text_b_pos: John walked to the next bus stop.
text_b_neg: John asked the man to come with him.

text_a: Charlie went to the gym. He saw several of his friends. Charlie talked to his friends until the gym closed. Charlie went home without exercising at all.
text_b_pos: Charlie worked out instead at home using his own body weight.
text_b_neg: Charlie rewarded himself for the hard training with a beer.

text_a: Josh loved to go on hikes in the mountains. He was on a hike with a friend when they saw a bear. His friend was terrified but Josh knew what to do. Josh threw his hands in the air and started yelling very loudly.
text_b_pos: Josh was amazed by the bear's fur.
text_b_neg: The bear turned around and walked away.

text_a: Jordan was having a perfectly pleasant day at the beach. He was enjoying a chocolate ice cream cone. Then all of the sudden a seagull flew towards Jordan out of nowhere. The seagull grabbed Jordan's ice cream cone right out of his hand.
text_b_pos: Jordan screamed after the bird and cursed loudly.
text_b_neg: Jordan sat down and continued eating his ice cream.

text_a: Norman spent very little time outdoors. He wished very badly to change this fact. He decided to go for a hike in the woods. While walking, he heard a loud crunch under his foot.
text_b_pos: Norman has built a forest cabin.
text_b_neg: He was scared of the unknown and run away.

text_a: Eve's dog galloped into the dining room. They'd just set out a dinner buffet for guests soon to arrive. Her dog jumped on to the table and shoved its snout into the hot dogs. As her parents shouted, Eve tried to control her dog.
text_b_pos: Her dog would not stop galloping.
text_b_neg: The dog was a delicatesse in china.

text_a: The man's foot itched. He bought some cream. The cream did not help. He tried a different brand.
text_b_pos: And his hand was still itchy.
text_b_neg: The new brand was better.

text_a: Jane decided to dye her hair. She tried to do it herself. Jane wound up messing it up pretty badly. The hair looked weird and she stained her scalp.
text_b_pos: She did it again next week.
text_b_neg: She had to scrub really hard for the stains to come off.

text_a: The heater kept Laura warm while she watched Carlos sleeping. She had brought it in from the garage because it was so cold. Laura was supposed to be sleeping too. However, she couldn't sleep while Carlos was snoring.
text_b_pos: She started snoring too.
text_b_neg: She had a lot of time to think about their future together.

text_a: Lewis wanted to have children. Unfortunately, he didn't have a partner yet. He began searching online for a partner. Within only 1 month, Lewis had found someone that was perfect.
text_b_pos: Lewis was unbelievably happy.
text_b_neg: Lewis didn't want children anymore.

text_a: John wanted to win a contest. But he was not very good at math or reading. Then he found a contest he could compete in. It was a hot dog eating contest!
text_b_pos: He had never eaten a hot dog in his life.
text_b_neg: He was a master at eating hot dogs.

text_a: The corner shop had been open thirty-five years. The owner was old and tired and had put the shop up to sell. A prospective buyer came and made the owner an offer. After mulling it over the owner decided not to sell.
text_b_pos: He decided to keep the shop open.
text_b_neg: He decided to close the shop without selling.

text_a: Simon was sad because he didn't have any friends. His parents thought a puppy might cheer him up. The family went to the animal shelter to look at dogs. Simon picked out a puppy and named it Buster.
text_b_pos: Buster stayed in the shelter.
text_b_neg: Buster became his new friend.

text_a: Pete's dog ran away. He looked for him all over town. He put up flyers in all the stores. Pete's dog never came home.
text_b_pos: Pete bought a new dog instead.
text_b_neg: Finally, Pete got a cat.

text_a: Jon needed a new clock. His old one was broken. Jon went online to find one. He found a cheap one and bought it.
text_b_pos: The clock was broken after one day.
text_b_neg: Jon stayed online for hours.

text_a: The school bell rang. As Malcolm sat down at his desk, a sudden realization hit him. He had forgotten his homework. He gulped as the classroom door opened, Mrs Davids wouldn't be happy.
text_b_pos: He finished his homework the second the teacher came in.
text_b_neg: Luckily Mrs Davids gave him an exception and he should just bring it tommorrow.

text_a: Mary really enjoyed knitting. She posted a picture of a sweater she knitted on her Facebook page. She received many messages offering to pay for a sweater of hers. Mary knit about fifty sweaters in response to these requests.
text_b_pos: She ate a cookie.
text_b_neg: They were all happy with their sweaters.

text_a: I decided to make a new closet last week. I took an empty room and put in shelves. I needed a closet for my shoes. When it was finished it looked great.
text_b_pos: My shoes weren't all over the floor any more.
text_b_neg: I lost my shoes.

text_a: Gina walked into the class where detention was held. There was no teacher. She thought about turning to leave. Just then the teacher walked in.
text_b_pos: Gina had to write hundred sentences before she was allowed to leave.
text_b_neg: Now that the teacher had arrived Gina was free to leave.

text_a: The scientist worked diligently on the slab for many years. They removed each piece of matrix and polished every bit of bone. The huge slab was beautiful. Paleontologists had learned much from the fossils it contained.
text_b_pos: The even discovered a new species.
text_b_neg: The slab went on to collect dust in some random museum's storage.

text_a: I spent all night last night working on my homework. I left my homework sitting on the kitchen table. I got up early in the morning for a run. When I returned I found my dog eating my homework.
text_b_pos: When I told my teacher she was very understanding.
text_b_neg: When I told my teacher she didn't believe me.

text_a: Tina's mom promised her that she will buy take-out tomorrow. Therefore, Tina came home from work that day without eating. She found her mom resting on the sofa. Her mom is aware of what she said, but she tells Tina that she's broke.
text_b_pos: Tina felt full before falling asleep.
text_b_neg: They didn't have dinner that night.

text_a: I am a big fan of Phil Ochs. His protest songwriting is as good as Bob Dylan's. I decided to research his life. I learned that he died very young and suffered from mental illness.
text_b_pos: I think he'd have had a great career given more time.
text_b_neg: I decided to listen to more of Bob Dylan's work.

text_a: Claire wanted to stop having a monotonous boring life. She attempted to learn a new language but that wasn't enough. She took up cooking lessons but she was not satisfied. She took up yoga but that was not for her.
text_b_pos: Claire kept searching for exciting activities.
text_b_neg: Claire was not bored anymore.

text_a: Kevin was excited when he was offered a job by the gym downtown. It was far from his house, though, and he didn't have a car. Kevin went to the attic and dusted off his old ten-speed bike. It would be a long trip every day, but Kevin knew it was worth it.
text_b_pos: He never returned from the gym.
text_b_neg: He made a shit ton of money.

text_a: Amanda and her friend, Joy, were in the 7th grade. After lunch one day, they went to the bathroom. In one of the stalls was one of their old friends, Nicky. Joy convinces Amanda to throw spit balls into the stall.
text_b_pos: Their teacher found out and was very angry.
text_b_neg: Amanda told Joy that they are not friends anymore.

text_a: I am very picky about my pets. I had a dog as a child, but I was afraid of it. I got a lizard but was very bored with it. I recently returned a rabbit to the pet store because it smelled.
text_b_pos: I bought a goldfish, as this seemed to be the easiest pet to keep.
text_b_neg: I ate an insect burger.

text_a: Every year, Jason takes his partner to the same place. Despite moving away, he will book flights to the place they first met. This place was a bar in London but they'd moved to the US. This year, they arrived to find the place was shut down.
text_b_pos: They continued their journey onward to Newcastle.
text_b_neg: They were sad they'd lost a place important to their story.

text_a: Billy had gone fishing. He was hoping to catch lots of fish. He waited all morning. He caught a big fish right around noon.
text_b_pos: It was a shark and it killed Billy.
text_b_neg: He went home and ate the fish.

text_a: Yesterday we went to the museum. We viewed all the exhibits. Then we noticed we were the only ones in the museum. It had gotten very late and we got locked in the museum.
text_b_pos: The other people joined our little party and we had spent the day there.
text_b_neg: We decided to have an orgie, since there was no one around.

text_a: Jeff notices he is tired earlier and earlier these days. He isn't doing anything different in his routines. He asked some friends about it. They said to take melatonin at night to sleep better.
text_b_pos: Jeff did not want to take medicine.
text_b_neg: Jeff started making a fire.

text_a: Joey and his girlfriend were at the fair and wanted to get a drawing. The two sat down on stools while the artist began to paint them. It had seemed like forever as the two waited patiently for it to end. At the end of the session, Joey took a look at the painting.
text_b_pos: The artist did not draw anything on the painting.
text_b_neg: Joey loved the paniting very much.

text_a: Candace had lit a candle. She forgot about the candle. Candace took a nap. The candle continued to burn.
text_b_pos: Candace woke up and made breakfast.
text_b_neg: When Candace woke up, the candle had completely burned up.

text_a: Rita decided to make her own bread. She carefully made her dough, then baked it. But after ages in the oven, it still hadn't risen! Rita suddenly smacked her forehead.
text_b_pos: She remembered the next day was Tuesday.
text_b_neg: She remembered she had forgotten one incredient.

text_a: The kids woke up hungry. They wanted to eat big bowls of cereal. The mom poured the cereal into the bowls. Then they realized they had no milk!
text_b_pos: They sacrificed the cat to the elder-gods.
text_b_neg: They went to buy some.

text_a: Kelly invited Ramon to her apartment to hang out. Ramona took her upstairs to see her facialist. To Kelly's surprise, the facialist was stirring up drama. Ramona thought it was hilarious.
text_b_pos: Ramona was bored and left.
text_b_neg: Ramona liked hanging out with Kelly.

text_a: Laura's old cat had died when she was little. Laura's mom missed having a cat, and it was her mom's birthday. Laura's friend at school was moving, and had to give away her cat. Laura brought a carrier to school, brought the cat home, and hid it.
text_b_pos: When Laura's mom found the cat she was very happy.
text_b_neg: Laura's friend did not like the cat.

text_a: Aaron is an amazing artist. He stopped painting when he got a job at a factory. He said he never had time to paint. After 5 years, Aaron quit the job.
text_b_pos: He went back to being an artist.
text_b_neg: He started a career as a clown.

text_a: Angie wanted to be a lawyer. She graduated from Spelman College in 1999. After a year working from home, she went to law school in Florida. She received a call from Spelman College offering her a job.
text_b_pos: She retired later in the week.
text_b_neg: She became a professor at Spelman College.

text_a: Jeremy was writing at his desk. He heard some kind of animal shuffling around in the attic. He got up to go see what it was. In the hallway he heard a very loud thump.
text_b_pos: He went to the attic to investigate further.
text_b_neg: He went back to writing at his desk.

text_a: Buster had always loved going fast even from a young age. So his father took him to a race. From that point on he was certain that he wanted to race for a living. So he practiced racing down the streets of his town.
text_b_pos: Buster loved playing theater as a hobby.
text_b_neg: He got in a lot of trouble for traffic code violations.

text_b_pos: He got an A on his project.

text_a: John was telling me about a good book he was reading. He thought I would like it. It was a murder mystery type. I usually really like that genre.
text_b_pos: Unfortunately, I did not like this book.
text_b_neg: The book was about a romantic love story.

text_a: Ethan and Jill went to the movies. They started to get a little close. Ethan reached to grab Jill's hand. They grazed hands.
text_b_pos: Ethan didn't like Jill at all.
text_b_neg: They looked each other in the eyes and then kissed.

text_a: Missi had always had an obsession with the Great Barrier Reef. Unfortunately, she also had a fear of the water. Determined to see the reef, she enrolled in swimming lessons. Once comfortable in the water, she took diving lessons.
text_b_pos: Missi still had a fear of water.
text_b_neg: After months Missi could finally see the reef.

text_a: Carla tried to jog with her friend. Since her friend was anemic, she had trouble keeping up with Carla. After the second lap, she fell to the ground. Carla helped her do breathing exercises.
text_b_pos: After some training she grew really strong.
text_b_neg: Carla is a world-championship.

text_a: Maddie decided to push me on the ground. I got up from the ground and became furious. I told her to go fight someone her own size. However, she took it seriously and brought Tim.
text_b_pos: Tim was the same size as Maddie.
text_b_neg: Tim was much smaller than Maddie.

text_a: It was Jillian's birthday. She celebrated the day with her family. It was getting late and she hadn't received any gifts. She was a bit confused, but didn't say anything.
text_b_pos: She was happy she did not get anything.
text_b_neg: Then the bell ring and when she opened the door there was a delivery man with a gift box.

text_a: Barney was eating candy. But his teeth began to hurt. He went to the dentist. And he had a cavity.
text_b_pos: The dentist filled the cavity so that Barneys teeth wouldn't hurt anymore.
text_b_neg: Barney continued to eat candy despite the cavity.

text_a: Ricky's grandma told him to take an umbrella with him. His grandma claimed to know when it was going to rainy. Ricky laughed and left without the umbrella. As he drove, rainy began to pour from the sky.
text_b_pos: He wished to have listened to his grandma.
text_b_neg: He was happy to have followed his grandma's advice.

text_a: Kelly found out her favorite pizza place was open. She immediately ran down to see it. When she went there she loved it. She was thankful it tasted good.
text_b_pos: Kelly was now planning to go there all the time.
text_b_neg: Kelly decided not to eat there anymore.

text_a: Lex is a wrestler. Lex trains to become the best. Lex works his way to the top. Lex gets a shot to be the champ.
text_b_pos: His practice pays off as he wins the championship.
text_b_neg: He hates his hobby.

text_a: Andrew made a plate of spaghetti and walked toward the table. His mom warned him to be careful with the plate. Andrew wasn't careful and he spilled the spaghetti on the floor. His mom was upset that he didn't listen.
text_b_pos: Andrew apologized and cleaned up the mess.
text_b_neg: Andrew ate the spaghetti off the floor.

text_a: Cynthia was a customer support rep for a large company. She could only submit tickets and empathize with the callers. One day, she noticed all her the tickets were automatically deleted. Cynthia keeps answering the phone, as long as she's paid.
text_b_pos: Cynthia needed the money for her family.
text_b_neg: Cynthia did not work for the money.

text_a: The winter season in Kansas wasn't usually too bad. One year we had a blizzard followed by an ice storm. We were locked in our house for one whole week. We were very thankful that we had extra food stored for emergencies.
text_b_pos: I got bored of eating the stored food so I went to buy a pizza.
text_b_neg: Nobody went hungry during the storms.

text_a: Kevin was bored of his daily life. He wanted to do something spectacular. He tried playing sports but it wasn't his thing. He tried reading but it bored him.
text_b_pos: He had an awesome time.
text_b_neg: Kevin was a lazy piece of shit.

text_a: Jasmine loved grapefruit more than any other fruit. She ate grapefruit every morning for breakfast. One day, Jasmine woke up feeling off but she still ate her grapefruit. Later that morning, Jasmine got sick and threw up in the bathroom.
text_b_pos: She felt great.
text_b_neg: She hasn't eaten a grapefruit since.

text_a: Ann was leaving the airport after a long flight home. Her business trip had been exhausting and she was eager to sleep. But then she heard a nearby lady crying! The lady had lost her keys and couldn't get home.
text_b_pos: Ann called a doorlock service for the lady.
text_b_neg: Ann was happy the lady cried.

text_a: Jim is thrilled when he graduates law school and passes the bar. Jim is not thrilled when the only job he can find is waiting tables. It takes him six months to find a job in the legal profession. But Jim meets his future wife while he's working at the restaurant.
text_b_pos: Jim felt unlucky to work at the restaurant.
text_b_neg: Jim felt lucky to work at the restaurant.

text_a: Wayne got cut from the basketball team his junior year. The coach told him he needs to become quicker and taller. Wayne spent the entire summer working on his speed. And he had a late growth spurt and grew three inches.
text_b_pos: He made the team next year.
text_b_neg: He decided he wanted to join the chess team.

text_a: Ben liked to compete with his dog in Schutzhund tests. He had trained Nero, his Rottweiler, for over a year. Today was Nero's first test. Nero was startled at first but then enjoyed every minute of the test.
text_b_pos: Ben and Nero performed really well and got a good result.
text_b_neg: Nero likes running in the forrest.

text_a: Tom always wanted to be an actor. He moved out to California to pursue his dreams. Once there he was able to land some small roles. Mostly commercials and sitcoms.
text_b_pos: He was totally happy about his actor career.
text_b_neg: He was constantly looking to land a bigger role.

text_a: Zelda was making brownies for a party and ran out of cocoa powder. She saw an unlabeled package of powder that looked like cocoa. She added it to the brownies and baked them. The house began to smell like cinnamon bread.
text_b_pos: The authentic chocolate brownies were a success.
text_b_neg: Zelda couldn't get the smell out for days.

text_a: I  thought the Oogum Boogum song contained bad words. I bought the cd to find out if my suspicions were true. I played the Oogum Boogum song over and over. I repeatedly listened to each and every word.
text_b_pos: I had indeed bad words.
text_b_neg: My mom took the cd.

text_a: Mary came by and told me she was having problems with her computer. She and I then went over to her apartment. I fooled around with her computer for about an hour. I finally found that her wall plug was bad.
text_b_pos: So we used another wall plug that worked.
text_b_neg: So we installed Firefox to try and make it work.

text_a: My cat had been suffering from cancer for awhile. She couldn't retain any nutrients either. She weighed five pounds yesterday. So we had to put her down.
text_b_pos: My family and I had a barbecue to celebrate the event.
text_b_neg: I consider this day one of the saddest of my entire life.

text_a: Janet loved taking pictures of herself. She would do it every chance she got. Her friend bought her a selfie stick. Janet used it all the time.
text_b_pos: Janet loved using the selfie stick to take pictures.
text_b_neg: Janet threw out the selfie stick.

text_a: Sara wanted to have a baby. She was already 35 years old and worried she waited too late. Sara prayed and kept trying to get pregnant. She went to a routine women's health check up.
text_b_pos: She found herself was single.
text_b_neg: She had a baby successfully after one year.

text_a: Hannah lived in a poor section of town. Her dog got out one morning. She went out on the porch and yelled for Snickers. The neighbor heard her and got angry.
text_b_pos: He gave Hannah some money.
text_b_neg: He yelled at Hannah.

text_a: Avery had a new engagement ring. Avery was in her pottery class. She took of her ring to work and lost it. She went back to look, but couldn't find it.
text_b_pos: She was really sad about it.
text_b_neg: It was not a special ring anyway.

text_a: Tara had a very itchy mosquito bite on her leg. It was so itchy, she scratched it until it bled. She then put some cream on it to relieve the itch, but it burned. Because she had scratched it so badly, the cream did nothing to help.
text_b_pos: Tara needed to go to the hospital.
text_b_neg: Tara wished she had not itched the mosquito bite so badly.

text_a: Jimbo loved the new show on Fox. He found himself binge watching the entire first season. He stayed up so late that he was half awake for the last few episodes. He eventually fell asleep.
text_b_pos: Jimbo dreamed about the show.
text_b_neg: Jimbo went outside and drove his car to the next city.

text_a: Sam was at the store looking to buy a television. He found one he liked and then looked it up online. He decided to buy it for a cheaper price online. Before he did a store employee told him they price matched.
text_b_pos: Sam decided to buy it at the store right on the spot.
text_b_neg: Sam went home to reconsider his options.

text_a: I want to learn how to play guitar. I bought my own guitar to learn how to play. I spent weeks and weeks practicing. I'm still not very good at playing.
text_b_pos: If I keep practicing, I know I will get better.
text_b_neg: I got frustrated and smashed my guitar.

text_a: Steven loves the ocean. He goes boating every weekend. Unfortunately he got caught in a storm while on the water. Steven's boat sank.
text_b_pos: Steven navigated the boat out of the storm.
text_b_neg: Steven had to swim all the way back to shore.

text_a: Dan woke up early to cook breakfast for his mom. He was frying up some eggs and wanted to be fancy. He tried to make the eggs do a flip in the pan. He flung the eggs in the air, but he missed the catch.
text_b_pos: Dan cleaned the pan.
text_b_neg: Dan's mom found it funny.

text_a: I was raking up the leaves in my yard into a pile for disposal. I saw what I thought was a large stick of wood in the pile. I bent down to pull the stick out, but suddenly it moved! The stick was really a garter snake resting in the warm leaves.
text_b_pos: I jumped back and ran home.
text_b_neg: I did not like the cold weather.

text_a: Heather wanted to watch her reality TV show. Her brother Bennett wanted to watch wrestling. The two argued over who gets control of the TV. While they were arguing their dad turned on the news.
text_b_pos: They were happy to watch the news with dad.
text_b_neg: They both went to their friends to watch what they wanted.

text_a: Willow fell to the ground. The pavement was covered in her blood. Pedestrians stopped to help. Picked her fragile body from the ground.
text_b_pos: She could feel that her arm was broken.
text_b_neg: She started whistling her favorite song.

text_a: Sam and matt wanted to play basketball. They woke up to rain. The boys decided to stay inside. They tried out a new video game.
text_b_pos: The weather was beautiful.
text_b_neg: It was great fun!

text_a: Christine went to the beach in the morning. She wanted to swim. She saw a kid playing too far from the beach in the sea. The big wave came.
text_b_pos: Christine hurried into the water to save the kid.
text_b_neg: Christine built a sandcastle.

text_a: Jane was turning thirty. She was depressed about her milestone birthday. None of her friends had mentioned any plans. Jane had decided she was just going to stay in and order food.
text_b_pos: Her friends had organized a surprise party and the had a great evening.
text_b_neg: She enjoyed the delicious food.

text_a: Rene was bored one day. All she had was a pen. She started drawing on her hand. She made a tattoo.
text_b_pos: She regretted it afterwards.
text_b_neg: The tatto was on her foot.

text_a: Jennifer was walking down her driveway to go to her car. As she opened her door, a large dog began to run at her. The dog was barking and foaming out the mouth. Jennifer hopped into her car, closed her door and began to drive away.
text_b_pos: The dog bit the tires and she couldn't get away.
text_b_neg: The dog was chasing the car for a while.

text_a: Carolann called her friend for a favor. Her friend said yes to the favor. She would provide the activity for Carolann's daughter's birthday. The kids made bracelets at the party.
text_b_pos: Her daughter didn't like the cake.
text_b_neg: Carolann was really grateful for the help.

text_a: Mark went to the shopping mall to look for some shoes. He ran into Jane while walking to the store. Mark likes Jane a lot. They ended up having lunch together in the food court.
text_b_pos: Mark forget about his groceries.
text_b_neg: Three years later they married.

text_a: Kate's mom wanted her to help paint the living room. Kate tried to make excuses. Her mom countered each one. There was no way out of the chore.
text_b_pos: Kate loved to paint the wall.
text_b_neg: So Kate had to paint the wall with her mom.

text_a: Sandy had never been to a horse race before. She was excited. All the jockeys and horses were going on to the track. They lined up in the gate and were off with a bang.
text_b_pos: Sandy was amazed by the event.
text_b_neg: Sandy completed her homework.

text_a: Laura was lacking confidence in her looks lately. She was using more makeup every day and it made me worried. She told me she thought other people didn't find her attractive. Laura decided to get a haircut to see if that helped her.
text_b_pos: After the haircut, Laura was more confident in her appearance.
text_b_neg: Laura blamed me for getting a bad haircut.

text_a: Randy hated being late. He would get really angry at slow drivers. Last week he snapped at a big guy in a truck. The guy got out with a baseball bat and smashed Randy's car.
text_b_pos: That's what we call road rage!
text_b_neg: Randy loved it.

text_a: The Smith family had a fire in their home one day. Everyone made it out of the house with no injuries. Their home needed a lot of work afterwards so they stayed at a hotel. For four weeks, they got to use a private pool and hot tub every day.
text_b_pos: They did not want to move back.
text_b_neg: The hotel rooms were too small.

text_a: Frank is a teacher who is ready for it to be summer. He has two more weeks until school is over and he's struggling. He thinks of creative ways to make time go by faster. He gives his students a daily project to work on.

text_a: My first step to solving my problems was admitting I have one. In the second step I changed what I had control over. I prayed for help in my third step. I made healthy choices for my life in the fourth step.

text_a: Edward wanted to make a lasagna. He made a list of the ingredients he would need. Edward bought the ingredients at the grocery store. At home, Edward followed the recipe to make lasagna.
text_b_pos: The lasagna he made was delicious.
text_b_neg: The cookie he made was delicious.

text_a: The weatherman said it would be dry today. I went to work without an umbrella. It rained anyway. I got soaking wet.

text_b_pos: Delaney hated her mom.
text_b_neg: Delaney was very sad.

text_a: John was driving to work while listening to the radio. But he couldn't find a song he liked. He kept switching stations. He finally found a song he liked.
text_b_pos: He kept on listening to this station for the rest of the drive.
text_b_neg: He turned off the radio.

text_a: Susie went on a date with Fred. She was excited to go out with him. But the food was terrible. Susie was not impressed.

text_a: Tonight I ate too much dinner. Everything on my plate was so good that I couldn't stop eating. I even went back for seconds. When my husband brought out dessert, I couldn't hold back.
text_b_pos: It looked so delicious.
text_b_neg: It looked so bad.

text_a: Lisa made chili for her boyfriend. She had a salad first, so he started eating the chili before her. He jumped up after the first bite for a glass of water. Lisa tasted the chili.

text_b_neg: It was very spicy.

text_a: The man sat down on the ground. He was tired of walking. He took out his water bottle. It was empty.
text_b_pos: He then walked to the bar to buy a bottle of water.
text_b_neg: He was feeling better after drinking from the bottle.

text_a: Shelby was looking forward to her school's winter break. First, though, she had to complete all of her final tests. Break would start as soon as every test was completed. Shelby worked hard and took all of her exams early.

text_a: Mary had a very solid idea what French food consisted of. She thought French food was just frog legs and snails. Her parents decided to take her to a French restaurant. Mary protested and though she would hate it.
text_b_pos: But Mary discovered French food was much more than that and she liked it.

text_a: Blake lost his job. He began looking for a new job. Blake found a new job in another city. He had to move to take the job.
text_b_pos: Blake started to sing.
text_b_neg: Blake moved to the other city to take the job.

text_a: Marvin had a girlfriend named Joan who he loved very much. He decided to dedicate a song to her. He wrote a song and named it "Love of My Life". Marvin sung the song to Joan one evening and proposed to her.

text_b_neg: She said yes.

text_b_pos: She was happy with the new attention she got.

text_a: Caroline stole the keycard. She snuck into the facility. She took a bottle of medicine off the conveyor. She then ran outside.
text_b_pos: Excited it had worked, she went right back in.

text_a: Ed wanted to go for a boat ride. He went down to the marina. There, he asked a captain to give him a ride. The captain agreed.
text_b_pos: Ed liked the ride on the boat.
text_b_neg: Ed could not go on a boat ride on this day.

text_a: Samantha was having her birthday party in a few days. She wanted to pick out a really nice looking dress. She shopped with her mother at the mall. She found a red dress that was perfect.
text_b_pos: However it was too expensive.
text_b_neg: But she was not looking for a dress.

text_a: Margaret made a costume for a Halloween party. She worked very hard on it. When she got to the party, she saw someone had made a similar costume. The two started to talk.
text_b_pos: The other one had no costume.

text_a: Miley's parents thought she was spending too much time on video games. So they made a rule: they measured how long she spent on studying. Then they allowed her to spend just as much time playing games. Miley began to spend much more time on her studying and homework!
text_b_pos: She didn't like video games anymore.
text_b_neg: As a result her grades improved too.

text_a: George and Sally got in a huge fight. George was so angry he left the house and started walking. He walked for miles and when he calmed down and realized he was wrong. He purchased some flowers and walked home.
text_b_pos: He married with Sally.

text_b_pos: The Johnson's were compensated.
text_b_neg: The Johnson's spoke highly of the hotel.

text_a: Pauline invited Josephine to her house for tea. Josephine went to Pauline's house and brought some cookies. Pauline tasted one and said that it was disgusting. Josephine told Pauline that her tea was disgusting.
text_b_pos: Pauline left Josephines house in anger.
text_b_neg: Pauline had to agree with her on that.

text_b_pos: I was very sad at this time.
text_b_neg: I was very happy at this time.

text_a: Sarah is really trying to get into shape for her wedding. She hasn't had much luck yet and she feels lost. She is just running but she doesn't seem to loose any weight. She read a book that told her to mix cardio and weightlifting.
text_b_pos: She decided to lift twice a week and run twice a week.
text_b_neg: She continued only running until her wedding.

text_a: Ed wanted to play baseball with his son Matt. He bought a ball and bat. Then he taught Matt the rules. He and matt began practicing.
text_b_pos: Matt played well after a few days.
text_b_neg: They were practicing badminton all the time.

text_a: Chelsea purchased a printer online from a large retailer. She had it shipped via their Site-To-Store feature. When the printer arrived at the store, it was broken. She tried to return it to another branch of the same store.
text_b_pos: They wouldn't take it back.
text_b_neg: She was happy about the printer.

text_a: After a few weeks of sickness, Shelly discovered she was pregnant. She was thrilled, and told her husband, mother and sister immediately. She told them to tell no one, as she wanted to tell people slowly. Later that day she saw her mother had told everyone on Facebook.
text_b_pos: Shelly was very angry with her mother.
text_b_neg: Shelly liked it.

text_a: Quentin had always wanted to meet people nearby his apartment. He decided to talk with his neighbors one day. Quentin and his neighbors became friends. Over time he got to know more and more people there.
text_b_pos: Quentin feels at home in his neighborhood.
text_b_neg: Quentin hates to talk to people.

text_a: The family always take a vacation. They usually go during spring break. Their spot is Denver. This year they decided to go to the beach.
text_b_pos: They celebrated Christmas as never before.
text_b_neg: They had a great time together.

text_a: Dan was very sad in his little apartment. He stood alone gazing out the open window. The city seemed like ants from where he stood. This however was a great analogy for how he felt in life.
text_b_pos: Dan liked ants.
text_b_neg: Dan wanted to move closer to the city.

text_a: Summer was trying to figure out how to file taxes. It was her first year of having a job and it was confusing! Her dad showed her the way to do it and from there she was fine. She quickly learned it was a pain in the butt.
text_b_pos: She moved to Australia to becoome a farmer.

text_a: The weather outside was very nice and warm. Sam decided to open a window to let in some fresh air. A fly came in through the open window. The insect filled Sam with great terror.
text_b_pos: Sam hated insects.

text_a: My husband's hair was getting really long. I suggested to him that he cut it. However, he was uninterested, as he wanted to grow his hair out. One day at work, his boss suggested that he cut his hair.
text_b_pos: He refused to do so and quarrelled with his boss.
text_b_neg: He had no choice but to cut his hair.

text_a: Magick is a black cat. Magick likes catnip. Magick's owner bought him a bag of catnip. Magick rolled in the catnip.
text_b_pos: And ate it all.
text_b_neg: It rolled and died.

text_a: I wanted to save some money, but times were hard. I decided to collect cans and recycle them. Altogether, I managed to get over $100 for one month's collection. I was pleased and decided to start collecting bottles, too.
text_b_pos: I reached my saving goal within 3 weeks.
text_b_neg: I fell down from the ladder.

text_a: I joked with my friend that I was a princess. She called me the wicked witch of the west. A few weeks later I got a package. Inside was a jewelry container.
text_b_pos: It contained the crown of a real princess.
text_b_neg: It contained a bracelet with a small crown on it.

text_a: Today I have been working on the alphabet with my son. He has learned the first three letters. Today we are working on the fourth and fifth letters. He has been a little frustrated, but he keep on trying.
text_b_pos: He is having a hard time learning the alphabet.
text_b_neg: He mastered the alphabet by the end of the day.

text_a: It was Emma's first day of kindergarten. She was excited to start school. Emma was also nervous that she would not know what to do. Emma's teacher was very nice and helped her feel more comfortable.
text_b_pos: Emma did not go to Kindergarten after all.
text_b_neg: Emma really liked the first day.

text_a: Mike feels anxious in social settings, especially meeting new people. He knows that his anxiety is holding him back in life. Mike decides to attend more parties to force himself to be social. Gradually Mike becomes less anxious around new people.
text_b_pos: Mike is very proud of his achievement.

text_a: Robert was just coming off an injury to his leg. He was recovering nicely but he had a basketball game on Friday. The coach let him skip gym class to go work on his footwork. Robert got a couple extra hours of practice in and felt a lot better.
text_b_pos: He now was well prepared for the game later that week.
text_b_neg: Robert decided to resign from the team.

text_a: Brandon was only nine years old and a straight-A student. His family was going on a vacation to a famous site. He asked his principal for permission to go with his family. The principal said he would not be permitted if he was older.
text_b_pos: Brandon couldn't go on the vacation.

text_a: Jan went to the mind reader at the county fair. She asked him if he knew what she was thinking. The mind reader nodded. Jan asked how could it be that he knew this?
text_b_pos: The mind reader said that it was a secret.

text_a: Gordon was in 3rd grade. 3rd grade classes are required to clean the cafeteria after lunch. Gordon really didn't want to clean the cafeteria. He ate at the 4th grade lunch table to appear as a 4th grader.
text_b_pos: Gordon liked playing at the playground.
