text_a: Robert started his very first job today! He is a cashier at a local bakery. He meets a lot of people through work. It makes him happy to meet more people around his town.
text_b_pos: Robert got the job right after he finished college.
text_b_neg: He feels like he has fitted into this town pretty well.

text_a: Dan went to Las Vegas for a business trip. Dan missed his wife and kids. Dan called them every night after the meetings. Finally the day came for Dan to return home.
text_b_pos: Dan bought some presents for his kids.
text_b_neg: Dan is single and wants to find a girlfriend.

text_a: Jill had been very depressed. One day, she decided she had to get help. She made an appointment with a therapist. The woman gave Jill a prescription for antidepressants.
text_b_pos: Jill didn't take the medicine.
text_b_neg: Jill took the antidepressants to get better.

text_a: Tom joined the army after 9/11. He was sent to Iraq soon after. There he ran into a lot of trouble. His convoy was hit by a bomb and Tom was severely injured.
text_b_pos: Tom used to be in the basketball team in high school.
text_b_neg: Luckily he survived it.

text_a: When Eric received a call from the hospital, he was very worried. He rushed to his car and drove to the hospital in a hurry. In the hospital, he was lost. He asked the front desk for the right room.
text_b_pos: Eric left the hospital because he couldn't find the room.
text_b_neg: Eric reached his wife in time.

text_a: The boat was at sea. The seas got really rough and the crew was nervous. The captain kept them calm. The storm passed after five hours.
text_b_pos: The captain was crying.
text_b_neg: They felt relieved that it was over.

text_a: Tabitha was rushing to get ready for school. She was trying to apply eye makeup but it looked wrong. For some reason she just couldn't get her makeup right. Running out of time she reluctantly skipped the makeup.
text_b_pos: The teacher reprimanded her for not having a makeup.
text_b_neg: At school no one noticed she did not have makeup.

text_a: Allison was entered to be in a competitive eating contest. On the day of the contest her mom came to visit her. She went out to breakfast with her mom and ate a lot of food. She got too full and it was going to affect her later.
text_b_pos: She felt great.
text_b_neg: She lost the competition.

text_a: Jim decided to get a credit card. Jim went shopping and used the credit card frequently. Jim spent thousands of dollars with his credit card. Jim realized he was in debt from his credit card spending.
text_b_pos: He began to realize why many people had spending issues with credit cards.
text_b_neg: As the holidays were coming up, he bought some gifts with his credit card.

text_a: Ann went to her Friday night bowling league at the bowling alley. She put on her shoes and lucky bowling glove. Ann grabbed her pink bowling ball and walked up to the pins. She threw her bowling ball and got a strike.
text_b_pos: She left early because she was upset.
text_b_neg: She bowled well the whole evening.

text_a: Dominick got out of bed after a long night sleep. He thought he wasn't tired anymore. He curled up on the couch after getting his tummy full. His dog jumped up on the couch with him.
text_b_pos: He started to pet the dog.
text_b_neg: He was starving.

text_a: Anna's dad left a sandwich in the fridge. At night she ate it because it looked delicious. In the morning he blamed her brother for eating it. Anna felt so guilty!
text_b_pos: Anna apologised to her brother later
text_b_neg: Annas brother had, in fact, eaten the sandwich.

text_a: John was visiting a farm where they had baby chicks. He cried until his mother agreed to get him one. He and his chick became fast friends. Even when she grew up and wasn't cute and fluffy anymore.
text_b_pos: John ate his chicken.
text_b_neg: John spend most of his time with his chick.

text_a: Maxwell took the bus home from school every day. He was tired of waiting for the bus to arrive. Maxwell decided to try walking one day. He discovered that it was faster to walk home.
text_b_pos: The bus was very fast.
text_b_neg: He never took the bus again.

text_a: Michael wanted to go to the county fair this weekend. But his boss wanted him to work a Saturday. Michael decided to work overtime over the week. He managed to make a lot of progress by Friday.
text_b_pos: Michael was able to go to the county fair.
text_b_neg: Michael is working on the project for more than two years.

text_a: In 1973 I worked in a table tennis factory. It was a summer job. I packed paddles into a box. I also glued handles.
text_b_pos: I can't remember why I did this summer job.
text_b_neg: From the wage I bought my first bicycle.

text_a: Ella wanted a kitten, and she had finally convinced her parents. They went to all the pet stores in town, cat shopping. But none of those cats were quite right for her! Finally Ella visited the local animal shelter.
text_b_pos: She found the perfect cat.
text_b_neg: Ella hates cats.

text_a: Luis had a present from a year earlier. It was from his mom. He refused to open it because he wanted her to see him open it. A few days later she stopped by.
text_b_pos: Luis opened the present with his mom.
text_b_neg: Luis and his mom went to get ice cream.

text_a: Dan heard a tune that he really enjoyed while driving. The announcer never stated what it was or who the tune was by. Dan asked several friends if they knew the tune. Dan felt frustrated by not knowing who did the tune.
text_b_pos: As soon as he was home he googled the song.
text_b_neg: Dan liked the name of the artist.

text_a: Uma had ordered a TV stand online. She was excited, imagining it would look really nice. When it arrived, it was much smaller and uglier than pictured. Uma tried it out but hated how it made her home feel.
text_b_pos: Uma sent it back.
text_b_neg: Uma kept it and proubly showed it to all her friends

text_a: I ate a big muffin. But it wouldn't go away! There always seemed to be more! So I ate more!
text_b_pos: I was all sweaty when I finally woke up from my nightmare.
text_b_neg: I went out to buy some more muffins.

text_a: Jimmy enjoyed running after school. He wanted to join the track team this year. He ran all summer long to practice and increase his stamina. It was time for tryouts, Jimmy ran as hard and as fast as he could.
text_b_pos: He was not fast enough for the team.
text_b_neg: He ran away and was never seen again.

text_a: I like to dress up for school each morning. I like to wear a suit and tie to look very professional. At first the other kids were making fun of me. Now the other kids are starting to dress up too.
text_b_pos: I don't wear the suits anymore.
text_b_neg: I give fashion tips.

text_a: Cameron was hosting the talk show. He was nervous but excited. He introduced the guests and talked to them about their projects. He was only scheduled to host for a week.
text_b_pos: Cameron really enjoyed hosting the talk show.
text_b_neg: Cameron found all of the projects very boring.

text_a: Today was my first day volunteering in my son's classroom. It was exciting to see what he and his classmates did during the day. I helped and listened to a few kids read books. It was a wonderful experience.
text_b_pos: I felt like me and son connected on this day.
text_b_neg: I started crying when I came home.

text_a: Jenny needed to light a candle. Her lighter wasn't working. She decided to try something else. She lit a dry spaghetti noodle on the stove.
text_b_pos: She used the lighter to light the candle.
text_b_neg: She was proud of her creative thinking.

text_a: Kathy was running a marathon. She was toward the middle of the group. She had never finished a marathon before. She was within a mile of the finish line.
text_b_pos: She was certain that she will finish the race.
text_b_neg: Kathy hated running long distances.

text_a: For years, Martin has been trying to think of the next big invention. Finally, he had a breakthrough. Martin built a prototype of a bowl that separates the cereal and milk. He pitched his idea to several flatware companies.
text_b_pos: Martin normally has cereal with milk for breakfast.
text_b_neg: They didn't like Martin's idea at all.

text_a: The black dog did not appear to have a home. Jimmy saw the dog and felt sorry for it. He walked over to it slowly. The dog came over to Jimmy and wagged his tail.
text_b_pos: He killed the dog.
text_b_neg: He petted the dog affectionately.

text_a: Tom was at a friend's house. They were all smoking together. Tom lost his lighter. A friend noticed he had it in his pocket.
text_b_pos: Tom set the house on fire.
text_b_neg: Tom was happy to have his lighter back.

text_a: My sister-in-law has a lot of aches and pains. She has bursitis and arthritis. She is constantly taking tylenol. One day we were in her apartment and found her son's Naproxen.
text_b_pos: We called the police.
text_b_neg: We told her to go to the doctor and get a prescription.

text_a: John didn't really care for school. John did not study at all for the test he was about to take. He looked over at his friends paper and copied all the answers. The teacher caught John cheating on the test.
text_b_pos: John was congratulated by both his parents and teacher for his achievement.
text_b_neg: John received a severe punishment after his parents found what had happened.

text_a: Ted liked fish. He bought a big aquarium for his house. He stocked it with exotic fish. He watched them for a long time every night.
text_b_pos: Ted was happy he could observe his fish.
text_b_neg: Ted realized he liked birds more.

text_a: Shaun and Kelsey were getting married. They started to plan their wedding. Kelsey did not know who to pick for her maid of honor. Shaun helped Kelsey choose.
text_b_pos: Together they decided quickly.
text_b_neg: They had an argument and broke up.

text_a: Tom drove a manual car. He wasn't very good at it. He would constantly grind his gears. It eventually messed up his transmission.
text_b_pos: Tom was such a good driver.
text_b_neg: He had to bring his car to a garage.

text_a: As Ella laid on the floor whining one morning, she spied a box. Mommy always told her not to climb on the box. Ella thought the light switch needed to be flipped, though. Ella climbed up onto the box.
text_b_pos: Her mommy saw that and praised her for doing that.
text_b_neg: Her mommy saw that and told her to come day.

text_a: Jake had a twin named William. Jake was lazy, while William was hardworking. Jake went to Will's work one day disguised as Will. He worked hard, and then took home Will's paycheck.
text_b_pos: Will invited him to lunch.
text_b_neg: When Will noticed he got very mad.

text_a: Kay was new to using coupons when shopping. At the store she purchased 3 things which she had store coupons for. At checkout she was tired so she went quickly. When she got to her car she realized she forgot to use her coupons.
text_b_pos: She was happy she had saved so much on her shoppings.
text_b_neg: She got upset and told herself to remember next time.

text_a: Olive was reading a thriller book when she heard a noise outside. She jumped out of her couch and went to the door. She looked through the peephole but saw no one. She called out but no one answered.
text_b_pos: She was eager her brother came back home.
text_b_neg: She started worrying something bad was about to happen.

text_a: I decided to watch a movie at the cinema. I went to the cinema but the movie was sold out. So, I decided to go to a cinema in a nearby city. Alas, the cinema there was also sold out.
text_b_pos: I decided to sneak in and sit on the stairs.
text_b_neg: I had so much fun.

text_a: I went outside to enjoy a cigarette one morning. I walked to my driveway to check the mail. All of a sudden, I noticed a deer running straight at me. I began to run away as the deer chased me into my house.
text_b_pos: I pet the deer.
text_b_neg: I got back into the house before the deer catched up to me.

text_a: The baby had a basket full of toys. Her favorite was a puppet. She would laugh every time her mom put the puppet on. One day, her mom scared her with the puppet.
text_b_pos: The baby started crying.
text_b_neg: The baby was very happy.

text_a: Mike had an upcoming assignment for his newspaper. He had delayed the assignment until today. He was desperate and sought help. One of his friends thankfully covered for him.
text_b_pos: Mike managed to fulfill the assignment.
text_b_neg: Mike postponed the assignment for another week.

text_a: I decided to have a dinner party for all of my friends. I went to the grocery store to purchase all of the groceries. Suzie came over to help me cook. We made lasagna and french bread.
text_b_pos: Suzie ate everything by herself.
text_b_neg: My friends loved the meal.

text_a: Janet was serving an old couple on a Sunday. She did her best to give them good service. The couple seemed pleased with her. At the end of the meal they left a terrible tip.
text_b_pos: She was very happy with the tip.
text_b_neg: She was very upset.

text_a: My girlfriend and I were hungry one day, so I used Chipotle's app. Not thinking anything of it, I used the saved credit card on file. When I went to pick up the food, the employees stared at me weirdly. One asked me to wait while she called the police.
text_b_pos: Although I hadn't done anything wrong, I got scared and ran away.
text_b_neg: I used a stolen credit card.

text_a: Kelsi opened up a bottle of grape juice. She poured herself a glass. Accidentally she spilled some. The carpet was now covered in juice.
text_b_pos: Kelsi did not care as she wanted to throw the carpet away anyway.
text_b_neg: Kelsi admired her beautiful, clean carpet.

text_a: Joel was walking home from school when he ran into a group of boys. The boys were all smoking cigarettes. One of them offered Joel a cigarette. He declined and continued walking.
text_b_pos: The boys laughed at him.
text_b_neg: The boys thanked him.

text_a: Brooke needed a ride to the airport. All of her friends were too busy to take her. Brooke decided to call a taxi cab. When the taxi cab never showed, Brooke called a neighbor.
text_b_pos: Luckily the neighbor drove her to the airport and she made the flight.
text_b_neg: She paid the taxi driver a tip.

text_a: A former coworker had an affair. It ended when the man's wife found out. The man broke off all talk with the coworker. She was insulted, and posted details of the affair on FB.
text_b_pos: He has extremely happy for that.
text_b_neg: He sued her under the new GDPR.

text_a: Max realizes that he has been wearing the same shirt to work for days. He decides he might need to buy another shirt. Max goes to the store and finds a nice blue shirt on sale. He buys it.
text_b_pos: Max threw the new shirt in the garbage.
text_b_neg: Max wore the shirt to work the next day.

text_a: Tina went swimming in her backyard pool only to find something out. She lost her favorite necklace. Tina looked all around the pool and couldn't find it. She searched her deck but it wasn't there either.
text_b_pos: Tina had lost her necklace.
text_b_neg: Tina didn't like wearing a necklace.

text_a: Sally made her list last summer. A list of all the things she wanted. But she was not a good girl this year. And she knew this deep down.
text_b_pos: Sally got everything she wanted for her birthday.
text_b_neg: It made Sally sad that she would not receive many of the things she wanted.

text_a: Lance is a lifeguard on a beach. He notices a kid drowning. He runs into the ocean. He saves the kid from drowning.
text_b_pos: People applaud him for what he did.
text_b_neg: People despise him for what he did.

text_a: Edna was hired as secretary at a local business. She found it hard to locate files in the office. Edna reorganized all the files. She was able to find the files easier.
text_b_pos: Her boss commended her for her efficiency
text_b_neg: Edna quit her job.

text_a: Bert felt very agitated. He needed time for himself to recuperate. When he cleared his whole weekend for two day of rest, the phone rang. His mom was coming to town and wanted to see him.
text_b_pos: The town was empty.
text_b_neg: He was really pissed.

text_a: The model rocket flew well. The parachute cord had to be replaced. The one I made out of tape my dad did not like. I decorated it.
text_b_pos: Now that it looked pretty, my father liked it.
text_b_neg: My father said it was still unacceptable.

text_a: Amy always thought suede looked luxurious. When she had a job of her own she decided to buy one. She had never owned real suede before. She wore the coat everyday, even in the snow.
text_b_pos: Amy was glad that she had bought the coat.
text_b_neg: Amy did not like the coat anymore and gave it to a friend.

text_a: The king became tired of wearing his crown around all the time. He hired a servant to carry it behind him. The servant tried to wear it himself but the king stopped him. As a punishment the servant had to wear a dunce cap.
text_b_pos: The servant never tried to wear the crown again.
text_b_neg: The servant continued to wear the crown.

text_a: Manuel had just made a ham and cheese torta for lunch. He packed it with ingredients to the brink and toasted it as well. He set it to the side and went to get a soda to complete his meal. When he got back the torta was gone and crumbs were left instead.
text_b_pos: He felt happy that the torta was gone.
text_b_neg: He got mad because he was so hungry.

text_a: Barry's sister asked him to babysit his niece for the night. Barry never babysat a toddler before, so he was scared. However, Barry's sister gave him a detailed schedule to follow. Barry followed the schedule, and he had fun with his niece.
text_b_pos: He thought it was a great experience.
text_b_neg: He was angry at his sister.

text_a: Mildred took over the farm when her husband died. She was very old and inexperienced. She hired a farmhand named Mark. He turned the farm around and saved her business.
text_b_pos: Mildred rewarded Mark handsomely with a bonus.
text_b_neg: Mildred reprimanded Mark.

text_a: Tom had just started working at the morgue the week before. He had seen a few bodies, and it still was scary to him. Arriving at work one morning, there were three new body bags. Opening them up, he pushed the tables in for examination.
text_b_pos: He couldn't stop vomiting once he looked at the bodies.
text_b_neg: He performed the examination without any emotional disturbance.

text_a: Lucy wanted a new tv. The problem was that she could not afford it. Luckily her brother bought her a new one. She was very pleased.
text_b_pos: She loved going over to his place and watching TV together.
text_b_neg: Soon she'd be able to afford a new TV herself.

text_a: Sam couldn't afford to fly home for Christmas. He decided to spend the holiday volunteering at a soup kitchen. Sam considered canceling when a snowstorm closed the subway. Finding snow shoes, Sam trudged through the storm to the soup kitchen.
text_b_pos: Sam didn't want to cook the whole time.
text_b_neg: Sam could finally cook delicious meals.

text_a: Jasper was the hardest worker at the mill. While other workers would take Sunday off, Jasper always worked. One Sunday, Jasper decided he needed a day off too. He had a great day fishing and eating fried cheese curds.
text_b_pos: He felt bad for not being at work that day.
text_b_neg: Now he understood why the others were enjoying their days off.

text_a: Joe was driving his old car when it broke down on him. Joe had enough and decided to buy a new car. He went down to the dealership looking for a new car. He went back and forth but finally decided on a Mustang.
text_b_pos: His old car was a good as new.
text_b_neg: He loved his Mustang.

text_a: The county fair was having a pie eating contest. June felt her pies were superior to everyone else's. She tried to bribe the judges to win the contest. They refused the bribe as they wanted to play fair.
text_b_pos: Jun made the best cookies.
text_b_neg: June won the contest.

text_a: Tina saw that Beth had new shoes. She liked them so much she wanted the same ones. Tina asked her mom to get them for her. Her mom said maybe for her birthday.
text_b_pos: Tina was thankful to her mom.
text_b_neg: Tina threw her shoes away.

text_a: Tom bought a new coat. It wasn't that big or warm but it looked good. He wore it out on a very cold night. Tom was not able to stay warm.
text_b_pos: So he went into a coffee shop to warm up.
text_b_neg: So he threw the coat away and walked home in a shirt.

text_a: Bob and Marla have been having marriage troubles for a while. He planned a surprise weekend getaway with her. They went to dinner and talked about old times when they had fun. They enjoyed the weekend together talking about the future.
text_b_pos: Bob's idea has been a great failure.
text_b_neg: Bob's idea has been a great success.

text_a: Susie picked up some coffee on the way to work. She took a long sip and started driving. All the sudden her car went to a halt. She spilled hot coffee on her.
text_b_pos: Susie knew she would be late for work.
text_b_neg: Susie decided to buy a new car.

text_a: Karen had two cats. Her roommates always told her to change their litter. Karen rarely did so. It made the house smell bad.
text_b_pos: Karen and her roommates were in bad relationship.
text_b_neg: Her roommates were proud of her.

text_a: Our 2-year-old granddaughter loves Winnie the Pooh. She watches only one movie. She watched the movie every day of her visit to us. We watched it with her.
text_b_pos: We got tired of the movie.
text_b_neg: We love the movie.

text_a: Paul renovated his bathroom. He found a big, beautiful vanity mirror. He hung it carefully over the sink. As soon as he stepped away, it crashed to the floor.
text_b_pos: Paul was happy with his new mirror.
text_b_neg: Paul was very sad.

text_a: Lenny was desperately looking for work. He finally got a job interview lined up. He arrived at the place early. Finally, he went in for an interview.
text_b_pos: He performed well and got the job.
text_b_neg: He did not want to pay attention to the interviewer.

text_a: Jane was upset a co-worker had let her down. He agreed to help with a project and flaked out. She found him in the break room watching TV. Jane launched a rant of fury on the co-worker.
text_b_pos: The co-worker felt embarrassed.
text_b_neg: The co-worker thanked Jane.

text_a: Jimmy was entering names into a database. He then spilt some water on his computer. His computer sparked and then turned off. Jimmy panicked.
text_b_pos: He had destroyed both his work and the computer.
text_b_neg: Rebooting the computer solved the problem.

text_a: My mom bought a porcelain dog for the porch. He's very realistic looking, so he tricked everyone. People walked up to the door, looked down and jumped. They thought there was adorable puppy staring up at them.
text_b_pos: We went to buy a live dog instead.
text_b_neg: We had many good laughs.

text_a: Our daughter is coming home to Boston to visit. She loves sourdough bread from a local bakery. My wife ordered the bread this morning. They had only 2 loaves left.
text_b_pos: She was happy she was able to get the bread.
text_b_neg: She told told them she did not want the bread.

text_a: Kelly just moved to a new town. She was quite nervous to move there. She was worried she would not make any friends. However to her dismay as she walked in the school she made some.
text_b_pos: She did not want to make new friends.
text_b_neg: She was very relieved.

text_a: I was at Taco Bell one evening. Nobody came to the counter to serve me. They even walked past, ignoring me. I shouted at the workers and stomped out of the restaurant.
text_b_pos: They had earned my loyalty.
text_b_neg: The waiter followed me out of the restaurant and apologized.

text_a: The boy ran into the kitchen. His hand hit the cup on the table. It hit the ground with a bounce. The cup did not break.
text_b_pos: He drove his wheelchair into the garden.
text_b_neg: His mother came in and scolded him.

text_a: Annie never knew his father. He lived alone with his mother and worked for an old man. The man was strict but fair and treated Annie well. One day, he offered Annie an extra job to make more money.
text_b_pos: Annie really needed those money.
text_b_neg: Annie was rich.

text_a: Rory has a test today. He was not prepared for this test at all. Desperate, Rory wrote the answers on the sole of his shoe in pencil. The teacher noticed the answers shining from the ceiling lights.
text_b_pos: The shine hurt the teachers eyes.
text_b_neg: Rory failed the test and got suspended.

text_a: I was feeling very sleepy. Alas, I had a project to finish. I decided to drink some coffee. However, I fell asleep.
text_b_pos: I started doing drugs.
text_b_neg: I dropped out and married a Christian.

text_a: Joe's dad cautioned him to stay off of thin ice. One day, Joe and his pal saw a sign by a pond that said Thin Ice. Joe's pal dared him to go out to the middle of the pond. Joe refused, but his pal headed out on the ice.
text_b_pos: Joe thought it was a good idea.
text_b_neg: His pal sank in and needed to go to the hospital.

text_a: Frank entered his apartment after finishing work. He was greeted by a blast of heat to his face. It wasn't long before the air conditioning was on full blast. Frank decided he needed to keep the air conditioning on all night.
text_b_pos: It got very hot inside the room.
text_b_neg: Frank got a cold.

text_a: One day Sally went on a picnic. She opened her basket and found a spider. Sally dropped her basket on the ground. The spider ran away.
text_b_pos: Sally wanted to eat the spider.
text_b_neg: The spider was more scared than Sally.

text_a: Jenna spilled soda on her sister's new dress. Her sister was furious and told her she would never forgive her. Jenna worked hard to clean the stain out of the dress. She even took it to the dry cleaners but the stain wouldn't come out.
text_b_pos: Jenna decided to never talk to her sister again.
text_b_neg: Jenna bought her sister a new dress.

text_a: Kay was a popular girl. She was out at the mall with her currently boyfriend of the week. At the mall, she passed by a group of boys. Kay realized she had dated half of the boys in the group.
text_b_pos: She hided behind her current boyfriend.
text_b_neg: Kay went shopping with her boyfriend.

text_a: Gus is a good dog except on rainy days. When it rains, Gus barks and runs around. If he hears the rainy falling he paws at the glass door. Gus's owners bought a thundershirt to make Gus calmer on rainy days.
text_b_pos: Gus now really loves running around in the rain.
text_b_neg: Now Gus is a much nicer dog to have around.

text_a: I had a big play to do. I practiced all my lines. I got up on the stage. I was still very nervous.
text_b_pos: I forgot to eat breakfast.
text_b_neg: My legs were trembling.

text_a: The casino player challenged me to a game. He quickly shuffled a ball between three cups. He told me that I will get $100 if I guess which cup had the ball. I picked one cup and I found out that no ball was in there.
text_b_pos: I got a $100.
text_b_neg: I didn't get any money.

text_a: Harry was taking a walk. He saw a squirrel. Then he realized it wasn't a squirrel. It was a chipmunk.
text_b_pos: He noticed it because of the green colour.
text_b_neg: Harry took a cute picture of it and posted it on Instagram.

text_a: Claire liked being a good hostess. She would serve fancy things to her guests. She bought a new cheese board to serve some great cheeses. The next time she had guests, she set the board out.
text_b_pos: The board was stacked with vegetables.
text_b_neg: The guests were amazed by how good of a host she was.

text_a: When I was younger my family and I would go on summer vacations. We would always go the Branson, MO. During one summer we stopped going because of money. It has been 4 years now and we have not gone back to Branson.
text_b_pos: I miss those holidays.
text_b_neg: Last year we went to Branson for holidays.

text_a: Who doesn't love pizza? Sam sure did so he ordered 3 larges. He saw a hungry kitten and felt bad. Sam decided to go outside and give the kitten some pizza.
text_b_pos: The kitten sniffed the pizza, but refused to eat it.
text_b_neg: The kitten ate it all.

text_a: Tom was prepping for a party. He was helping friends inflate balloons. Right when he had one full a friend snuck up from behind. They popped a balloon right by Tom's ear.
text_b_pos: Tom let go of his balloon and he had to fill it again.
text_b_neg: Tom read a book.

text_a: I gave a ride to my friend. When he got in the car, he noticed it was a mess. There were soda cans and burger wrappers everywhere. I felt embarrassed because of the junk.
text_b_pos: My friend refused to get into the car.
text_b_neg: My friend told me not to worry about it.

text_a: Larry loved to go hiking. He looks for pretty birds. Today he saw a coyote on the trail. He was very still as the coyote passed.
text_b_pos: He made some noises to chase the coyote away.
text_b_neg: The coyote didn't notice that Larry was there.

text_a: Larry wanted to get a new baseball cap. He didn't have enough money though. He started asking friends if they had any extra hats. His friend Bill had one.
text_b_pos: Bill asked Larry twice the price of the hat.
text_b_neg: Bill gave Larry the hat as a present.

text_a: Jona and Taylor wanted to pull a cool stunt. They decided they wanted to jump of the roof onto something. Jona suggested his trampoline. Right before they could jump, Jonah's dad came home.
text_b_pos: Jonah went to bed.
text_b_neg: His dad did not like the idea.

text_a: My ex-boyfriend and I were not getting along. He was purposefully doing things to anger me. We started fist-fighting hard. He overpowered me, so I called the police.
text_b_pos: The police were very funny.
text_b_neg: The police shot him.

text_a: John was shooting in target practice. He aimed steadily, but his arrows always missed. His instructor told him to practice more. John complied, practicing often.
text_b_pos: After some years of practice John became one of the best at it.
text_b_neg: His instructor stopped helping John since he wasn't trying to improve.

text_a: Three friends lived together. Every night they met in the kitchen. They sat at the table and discussed their problems. Cheesecake was the fortitude of these conversations.
text_b_pos: Nobody liked cheesecake.
text_b_neg: They had decided to bake cheesecake once a week.

text_a: My wife and I went out to dinner on Valentine's Day. We went to a restaurant near our home. The bread and drinks were delivered late. The entrees arrived only minutes after the appetizers.
text_b_pos: It was the greatest date we ever had.
text_b_neg: We asked to talk to the manager.

text_a: I was painting my garage and was almost finished. My phone rang and when I reached to get it I knocked over the paint. Red paint spread all across my white carpet. I tried to get up the paint before it set but it was too late.
text_b_pos: Now there is a huge stain on the carpet.
text_b_neg: I am proud of the work I did on the carpet.

text_a: Tom had a new job. He wanted to make a good impression. He would show up early to work his first week. After a while his boss got used to it.
text_b_pos: Tom is unemplyed and still looking for a job.
text_b_neg: He wants him to come that early every time.

text_a: Meg was invited to a fancy dinner party. But she could not afford any fancy clothing to wear. Her mom encouraged her to go anyways. Meg decided to take her mom's advice.
text_b_pos: She got thrown out of the party and was told to never come back.
text_b_neg: It turned out that most people didn't care anyway.

text_a: The Smith family was a family of political independents. They all had varying views of how the country should be run. Because of the election coming up soon, they got into arguments. The arguments led to the family agreeing to not talk about politics.
text_b_pos: Family dinners became much more pleasant from then on.
text_b_neg: Mr. Smith openly voiced his disdain for the current president.

text_a: Fred had a stomach ache at school. But he didn't want to miss out on anything important. But as the day went on, his stomach ache got worse. In Fred's last class, he threw up.
text_b_pos: The teacher then also threw up.
text_b_neg: He was sent to the doctor immediately.

text_a: Kim was a vegetarian for 10 years. She had been considering returning to meat. One day when she was at a restaurant she ordered salmon. Her husband was in the restroom.
text_b_pos: She still felt bad to eat the fish.
text_b_neg: She suddenly ran outside.

text_a: Today, I got to spend some time with my granddaughter. She loves to swim. So, we went to a gym with an indoor pool. We had a lot of fun.
text_b_pos: She then wanted to play a game of chess.
text_b_neg: We spent the whole day together at the pool.

text_a: The creative industry of the United States was in big trouble. They didn't have the courage to foster new ideas or finance projects. And endless dirge of Comic Book stories and vampire movies resulted. The industry attempted to recruit creative talent, but didn't invest.
text_b_pos: This was the sunset of the American creativity.
text_b_neg: This caused a new civil war in the United States,

text_a: A man celebrated his 50th birthday. He felt a little bit old. His kids called him old. It actually kind of hurt him.
text_b_pos: He did not like aging.
text_b_neg: He had never been so alive.

text_a: Ken got a call from work one day. He was supposed to be there. Ken told them that wasn't his schedule. He was informed that the schedule was changed last minute.
text_b_pos: Ken was promoted.
text_b_neg: Ken lost his job.

text_a: Ian loved playing sports. But he hated letting down others. After he joined his school's soccer team, he was afraid of messing up. During an important game, he failed to block the goal.
text_b_pos: Ian was made captain of the soccer team.
text_b_neg: He decided to drop out of the his school's soccer team

text_a: Oliver was in an arcade for his birthday. He was mastering so many of the games and winning tickets. At the end of the day he had more tickets than he had ever seen. He went to redeem his prize.
text_b_pos: He felt upset that day.
text_b_neg: He felt very happy and went back home.

text_a: He picked up the pencil, haltingly at first. Feeling the thin wood object in his hand, he closed his eyes. Pencils always made him feel good and he began to imagine. The first thing that popped into his mind was a baby girl.
text_b_pos: He decided to get another pen.
text_b_neg: He started to sketch a portrait.

text_a: Kim had a drinking problem. Her friends and family got together to help. They all talked to Kim and tried to be comforting. Kim understood they were right.
text_b_pos: Kim decided to stop drinking.
text_b_neg: Kim decided to be alcoholic.

text_a: Brenda was on her way home from work one day. She decided to stop by the grocery store. She picked up a few items to make for dinner. She decided to buy a lottery ticket.
text_b_pos: Brenda threw the lottery ticket into the garbage bin.
text_b_neg: A few days later Brenda realized she had won the lottery.

text_a: Andy wanted some candy. His wallet is empty. Andy has to steal a candy bar from the gas station. The attendant saw him do it.
text_b_pos: But he did not say anything.
text_b_neg: The addendant stole more.

text_a: Amy made a friendship bracelet for her best friend. She used colored embroidery thread. After knotting it together, she added some beads. Then she put a shiny red clasp on the bracelet.
text_b_pos: Amy was bad at doing handcrafts.
text_b_neg: She believed that her friend would like it.

text_a: Mrs Jones told her class she would buy them pizza. The one condition was that they did well on the exam. They studied for many days. When it was time for the test, they all aced it.
text_b_pos: So they all had a really nice pizza.
text_b_neg: They went to eat spaghetti.

text_a: Daniel had a very sick friend named Seth. Seth had cancer and wasn't expected to survive much longer. Daniel asked his church to pray for his friends health. To everyone's surprise Seth made a full recovery.
text_b_pos: Seth believed that God saved him.
text_b_neg: Danial was sad about Seth's recovery.

text_a: Steve usually likes to light candles around the house. He usually remembers to blow them all out when leaving. One day, he forgot to blow out the candles. The candle fell off the counter.
text_b_pos: Steve's house was flooded.
text_b_neg: Steve's house went on fire.

text_a: Brenda had lots of important papers. She got a safety deposit box at the bank. She stored them all there. After a few years, she went to retrieve them.
text_b_pos: But she had lost the key.
text_b_neg: The documents were green.

text_a: Sara was learning how to drive with her dad. Sara was excited, yet anxious about learning to drive. Today's lesson was about Speed limits, and Sara knew she failed. Sara sped through several crosswalks, and failed to follow the signs.
text_b_pos: She promised her dad to do better next lesson.
text_b_neg: They went to have ice cream together after the lesson.

text_a: Tom had several messy roommates. He kept trying to get them to wash their dishes. They always had excuses not to. One day Tom decided to move out.
text_b_pos: He liked the clean dishes but missed the colleagues.
text_b_neg: Tom went shopping every day.

text_a: My grandpa bought me a bike with training wheels. I rode it for a while and asked grandpa to take them off. I pleaded and he finally agreed but didn't think I could ride it. He took off the training wheels.
text_b_pos: The bike had four wheels.
text_b_neg: I fell off the bike.

text_a: Barry ended up failing the final exam. His class grade jumped from a 91 to 79. A few days later, he decided to go to the teachers office. He begged the teacher for a grade curve.
text_b_pos: But the teacher told him that it does not work like this.
text_b_neg: Barry became the new teacher of the class.

text_a: Ferny always wanted to travel to an isolated island somewhere. He had planned an extensive trip for him and his wife. They rented a boat and sailed off in the sunset hoping for adventure. They got much more when they got caught in a storm and had to abort.
text_b_pos: They had an awesome trip.
text_b_neg: He never realized his dream.

text_a: I was hiking through the desert. I was on my way to get to a large canyon. I walked through a large open dry area. I finally made it to the canyon and went swimming.
text_b_pos: The water was cold and clear.
text_b_neg: I lost my keys in the water.

text_a: Sara was shopping for a dress. And she picked several to try out. But after an hour, she could not find anything that fit properly. Sara began to cry in the dressing room.
text_b_pos: She went home without a new dress.
text_b_neg: She loved her new dress.

text_a: Every year my in-laws take my family to Disney World. We stay at one of the resorts right on the grounds. We visit the parks and stay late every night. By the end of the week we are all exhausted and ready to go home.
text_b_pos: However we look forward to going back the following year.
text_b_neg: We just don't like to spend time with my in-laws.

text_a: Dan was getting ready to start his work day from home. As Dan sat down, he realized his computer would not turn on. Dan realized he would have to get his computer repaired. Dan called a local computer repairman, but he couldn't come until 5pm.
text_b_pos: The repairman got lost on the way home.
text_b_neg: When the repairman came, the computer was fixed within 5 minutes.

text_a: I was at the movie theater the other day. At the theater they had a claw machine. I tried to play the claw machine to win a stuffed bear. I tried so many times to win that bear, but I never did.
text_b_pos: Luckily that day there was an old man who told me a trick to win it.
text_b_neg: Unfortunately I didn't have time to try since the game was about to start.

text_a: Louisa wanted to go on a scavenger hunt. She went on one with her friends. The girls started finding many objects. After an hour, they were done.
text_b_pos: Lousia was dissapointed.
text_b_neg: Lousia found a nice mug she decided to keep.

text_a: Kim had fancy a tennis court installed in her backyard. And right away, she practiced using her ball machine. But after she finished, she noticed black skid marks on the new court. She realized she was wearing black shoes.
text_b_pos: Kim had to clean the marks on the court because they were ugly.
text_b_neg: Kim sold the ball machine.

text_a: Heidi cannot see well. She needs to get glasses. Heidi is worried how she will look. Heidi gets to pick out her pink glasses.
text_b_pos: She threw her new glasses away.
text_b_neg: She loved her new glasses.

text_a: Kelly sat down to take her math test. She had her blue pen. In the middle of the test however, her pen ran out of ink. Kelly didn't know what to do.
text_b_pos: Her friend gave Kelly a pen.
text_b_neg: Suddenly a pen fell from the ceiling.

text_a: Michael had never been a drinker. He had a date with a young woman. She began to drink a few beers. She encouraged him to drink one or two.
text_b_pos: He drunk a couple of beers.
text_b_neg: He ate a couple of chips.

text_a: Karla liked colorful pens. She bought a huge pack of them. She wrote things in her planner in different colors. She felt more organized when her calendar looked pretty!
text_b_pos: She was happy about how organized she was.
text_b_neg: She regretted having filled in the calendar.

text_a: I wanted to check my latest work schedule. They post them on the company's website. I went online to look. They scheduled me to work on my unavailable days.
text_b_pos: I did not mind at all.
text_b_neg: I called the office immediately.

text_a: I cleaned out my garage today. I was surprised to find boxes of old albums. They were from my teenage years. Going through them brought back so many memories.
text_b_pos: I scanned them so that I could have digital copies
text_b_neg: I burned them in the garden.

text_a: Tom loved nature and the outdoors. He decided to buy plants for his home. He browsed many plants at the nursery. He found a plant with very soft leaves.
text_b_pos: Tom bought the same one in the supermarket.
text_b_neg: Tom likes playing video games.

text_a: Michael liked to paint figures on little blocks of wood. He sold them at crafts fairs and other local events. He got the materials for less than ten dollars. He sold the blocks for twenty five dollars each.
text_b_pos: With the earnings Michael could afford to buy a new bike.
text_b_neg: Michael was sad he was not making money through this business.

text_a: Bill wanted to run for class president. His competitor was very popular. Bill spent a lot of time meeting students. He asked them for their vote.
text_b_pos: He never actually wanted to be class president.
text_b_neg: In the end he lost in the election by a close margin.

text_a: When I was little, I asked Santa for a bicycle. When I woke up on Christmas morning, it was there! I was sure Santa had come and left it. Now that I'm older, I know it was my mother.
text_b_pos: My mother never told me about Santa.
text_b_neg: I was sad when I figured out that Santa doesn't exist.

text_a: I wanted to watch shrek the third. I had it saved in my playlist. But then all the sudden it was gone. I was annoyed.
text_b_pos: Shrek the third was a wondeful movie.
text_b_neg: I had to search on Internet one more time.

text_a: Jake will be seeing a scary movie tonight. He is frightened very easily. He wouldn't have agreed to go but his crush will be at the theater. He is afraid of screaming in front of her.
text_b_pos: He decides not to go because he does not want to see her anyway.
text_b_neg: To calm himself before the movie, he drinks a little liquor.

text_a: Ed broke his phone one day. He was walking down the street and dropped it on the concrete. The screen was smashed badly. He realized he couldn't fix it.
text_b_pos: He was happy it was broken.
text_b_neg: He was sad

text_a: Sally fell in love with a pair of shoes. She knew they were out of her budget. She decided to save up for them. She finally had saved up enough.
text_b_pos: She bought the shoes and never regretted the decision.

text_a: Our son sprained an ankle in 2013. He went to the hospital emergency room. He got good treatment. The bill was $100.
text_b_pos: Our son's ankle is now much better.
text_b_neg: Our son still has trouble walking.

text_a: Sidney was a great cook. Cajun food was her favorite thing to cook. She made a big pot of gumbo. She fed it to her kids and husband and they all loved it.
text_b_pos: She developed skills in cooking Italian food.
text_b_neg: She made it for her friends when they came over to visit.

text_a: John got a new puppy and wanted to train him. He signed him and his dog up for obedience classes. The first day of class was very hard for John and his dog. However, they kept going to class and working hard.
text_b_pos: His dog improved a lot and could follow every command.
text_b_neg: A thing he didn't notice however is that his dog started being intelligent and outsmarted him.

text_a: Sam was looking for his glasses. He couldn't see well without them. After a while he took a break and sat down. Same heard a crunching sound and felt something on his butt.

text_a: Arnold was scared of the color yellow. Many believe it was because of his childhood experiences. One day arnold decided to draw with a yellow marker. As he was drawing he felt very wobbly.
text_b_pos: But in the end he got used to it.
text_b_neg: Arnold bought a yellow car.

text_a: A street mugger leaned against a wall in a dark alley at night. He looked for potential targets as they walked by. Everyone looked either too poor or stronger than him. He had to compromise on a guy who seemed poor but not strong.
text_b_pos: The street mugger stole $100 from the man.
text_b_neg: The street mugger gave the man $100.

text_a: I have a lot of work to do and am stressed out. I decided to organize my work desk. Ever since I organized it, my life feels better. But one day, I come into work and my desk is a mess again.

text_b_neg: I decided to get rid of my desk.

text_a: On the way home we stopped at a small animal rescue. We looked at several bears and tigers in captivity. Their spaces were very small and cramped. I felt sad for the animals.

text_a: My friend and I decided to go to school to review for a test. Before we started, she wanted to get a drink from the vending machine. When she put her dollar in, she entered a number in. A Coca-Cola bottle came out.

text_b_neg: My friend and I went to a party afterwards.

text_a: Sally was happy when her widowed mom found a new man. She discovered her siblings didn't feel the same. Sally flew to visit her mom and her mom's new husband. Although her mom was obviously in love, he was nothing like her dad.
text_b_pos: She felt uncomfortable around him.
text_b_neg: Her mom decided to leave him.

text_a: Sam was not very good at swimming. When he was young, he almost drowned. Sam practiced long hours every week. Sam got really good at swimming.
text_b_pos: Next, he learned horse riding.
text_b_neg: He even went on to train as a lifeguard.

text_a: Aveline wanted attention. She told everyone she had health problems. The whole community reached out with support and empathy. Aveline basked in the glow of their compassion.

text_a: Jonas was born was a very high IQ. He excelled in school with ease. As a result, Jonah became bored in class. Jonah would sleep through most of his lectures.

text_a: The high school hired a new football coach. After doing so their football team lost several games. The coach was given another chance. The team lost even more games.
text_b_pos: The coach was then promoted.
text_b_neg: The coach was then fired.

text_a: Annie's daughter was starting school. Annie helped her daughter get ready for school. She brought her daughter to school in the morning. Annie returned to pick up her daughter.
text_b_pos: Annie did not have a daughter.

text_a: Alicia found out she was getting a new babysitter. Alicia was not happy. This was her tenth sitter. So Alicia decided she would pull pranks on her to get her to leave.

text_a: My uncle showed up ringin my doorbell. I opened the door groggily. He handed me a large bag. It was filled with fresh ground deer meat.
text_b_pos: I was surprised, but accepted the meat.

text_a: Callie was a singer. She loved to sing every single day. One day, she saw a flyer for a singing competition. She decided to enter.
text_b_pos: The jury was impressed by her voice and she joined the competition.
text_b_neg: She was not very good at singing and she was discarded.

text_a: Mindy was late to work, but she couldn't find her umbrella. The weather was awful, and she couldn't leave the house without it. Suddenly, she remembered - she'd left it on the train yesterday. Making do with a piece of newspaper, she hurried out to catch the train.
text_b_pos: She stayed in her house and started watching TV.
text_b_neg: Nevertheless, she got wet before she could reach the car.

text_a: I am a violinist and have taken many orchestra auditions. Three years ago I auditioned for the Kansas City Symphony. I prepared for months and was very confident in my preparation. The day of the audition I played well and made it to the finals!
text_b_pos: I decided to become a manager instead.
text_b_neg: I didn't get the job.

text_a: Robert loved baby animals. One day he went to the local farm. He saw a lot of animals. Once he saw the chicks though, he fell in love.
text_b_pos: He nevery really liked baby animals.
text_b_neg: He went to the chicks and petted them.

text_a: I was doing my math homework during the afternoon. The delivery man knocked on my door. He gave me a huge package. When I opened it up, it was a Korean Drama Comic Book.

text_b_pos: She decided not to go to the school dance.
text_b_neg: She decided to go bare foot.

text_a: Paul was working for an advertising agency. Paul's company lost a major client. Paul's company had to fire a lot of the staff. Paul was fired.
text_b_pos: Paul was rehired.
text_b_neg: Paul was very sad and decided to call his wife.

text_b_pos: He told us that we did the right thing.

text_a: Will was driving his truck. While driving he hits a rock. His stops his truck and gets outside to look. He has a flat tire.

text_b_neg: He calls AAA to get roadside assistance.

text_a: John was playing frisbee with his friend at the beach. John hits someone with the frisbee. The man who got hit was angered and looked who hit him. John was afraid he would get beat up and so he did admit it.

text_b_neg: The man beat him up.

text_a: Samantha read online that mayonnaise makes a fantastic suntan lotion. She bought a jar from the store to take to the beach with her friend. They didn't think about how bad the mayo would spoil in the sun. The girls left the beach early when the smell became overwhelming.
text_b_pos: Next time they used a sun lotion.
text_b_neg: They decided to try using mayonnaise again.

text_a: Gina didn't want to go to school. She didn't want to sit at her desk near her old friends. She wanted to stay at home and mope. But her mother wouldn't allow her.
text_b_pos: She enjoyed her time at school.
text_b_neg: She was angry at her mother.

text_a: We all have confessions, some big and some small. Some are dark secrets, others are lies and untold truths. Everyone feels their presence and its weight, they think they're alone. The truth is we are not alone, we choose to feel these burdens alone.

text_a: Gabriel was preparing for a big concert. He was so nervous, his hands were shaking. He took his violin out and dropped it on the floor. The wood splintered and the violin was unusable anymore.
text_b_pos: Gabriel aced the concert with his beloved violin.

text_a: Andrew heard about a "hands on the hard body" car contest. He decided to try it out. He really needed the car. For a while he did really well.
text_b_pos: Andrew decided to quit his job and not get a car.

text_a: I was walking down the street. I saw a young girl crying all alone. She said that her best friend was leaving for camp this summer. She was here all alone.
text_b_pos: I was trying to cheer her up.
text_b_neg: She felt very happy in that moment.

text_a: I needed to simulate a data set. I decided to use a Monte Carlo simulation algorithm. Alas, the data set was not normalized so my algorithm failed. I decided to try a bootstrap simulation instead.
text_b_pos: It failed again, due to a bug in my code.
text_b_neg: I like visiting new cities.

text_a: Tom used his phone's alarm to wake up. One morning he realized the alarm never went off. Tom's phone had died even though he had it plugged in. Tom realized the charger was broken.

text_a: I was playing baseball at school. I touched first base. I went right past second base. They said I was out.

text_b_neg: I had my very first home run.

text_b_neg: Gary was angry at the dog.

text_a: Kelly was late to school too many times. As a result her teacher gave her detention. Kelly was nervous about that. She walked into the classroom.

text_b_neg: Her teacher punished her and she decided to be on time in the future.

text_a: Jim was exhausted from the night before. He had been out partying rather than studying for his exam. On the day of his exam, he decided to guess on every question. He thought he had failed the exam.
text_b_pos: But he received a passing grade.
text_b_neg: But then he failed the exam.

text_a: Anita was a chef in a kitchen. She made a delicious dish for a customer. The server mistakenly brought the dish to another diner. Anita realized what the server did.
