text_b_neg: She made him correct his mistake and apologize to the customer.

text_a: Tom was going to sing karaoke. He picked a song he knew by heart. The dj played another song by mistake. Tom didn't know it as well but went along with it.
text_b_pos: He asked the dj to play the same song again.
text_b_neg: He did very poorly and got booed of the stage.

text_a: Donna was short on money but needed groceries. She went to a dollar store to find some inexpensive food. She found many canned goods to buy. Donna checked out and was happy with the food she purchased.
text_b_pos: Disgusted, she spit out her dinner.
text_b_neg: She made dinner, and realized that canned food was just as good.

text_a: Lucy was lost in a neighborhood she didn't know. She had been walking for hours trying to get back there. It was dark now and she was crying and afraid. She had no idea how she was going to find her way back.
text_b_pos: She unlocked the door and got into her home.
text_b_neg: Police found her after some hours.

text_a: Molly is out swimming. Molly swims deep into the ocean. Molly feels something swim near her. A shark begins to attack molly.
text_b_pos: Molly starts screaming for help.
text_b_neg: Molly loves wildlife encounters.

text_a: Tom put a portable fan too close to the window curtain. The blades pulled the curtains into the fan. The fan quickly seized and overheated, starting the curtains on fire. Tom was too mesmerized to consider he was in danger.
text_b_pos: The fan started smoking and stopped spinning.
text_b_neg: Tom started singing to the rhythm of the fan.

text_a: Joe ripped his backpack. He needed a new one. He went to Office Depot. They had only one in stock.
text_b_pos: Joe bought the backpack although he did not like the colour very much.
text_b_neg: Joe did not buy the backpack because he did not really need a new one.

text_a: The neighbor's dog was loud and annoying. It would bark at all times. Enough people complained about it. The neighbors got a shock collar for the dog.
text_b_pos: People were still complaining about the barking.
text_b_neg: The dog never barked anymore.

text_a: I went for a fun drive on Sunday. I knew the market square was always crowded, then. I floored my car through the pedestrians, knocking them all down. My car stalled out from all the blood and brain matter in the engine.
text_b_pos: The police could catch me and I got jailed.
text_b_neg: My friend who is mentally ill likes to write sad stories.

text_a: The nurse took Jared's vital signs first. Then, she asked him to sit on the exam table. She listened to his heart and lungs. She told him the doctor would be in shortly.
text_b_pos: The doctor gave Jared a lollypop and sent him home.
text_b_neg: Jared diagnosed the doctor.

text_a: I went to a Detroit Lions game for my birthday. I had a large Birthday card to try to get autographs. After warm ups I was getting a few autographs. A player gave me his gloves which were signed.
text_b_pos: They're very precious to me.
text_b_neg: I threw the signed shoes away.

text_a: Tom was strolling home from work one day in New York. He noticed people gathered in the park. He noticed two people playing chess. Tom loves chess.
text_b_pos: He ate a sandwich.
text_b_neg: He asked to join for another game.

text_a: Brent had to take a statistics course as a requirement for his major. It had never been his favorite branch of mathematics. Brent found himself worrying a lot about the course. On his first day in class a very pretty young woman sat beside him.
text_b_pos: Ten years later he married that woman and was happy he took the course.
text_b_neg: He told her about his passion for statistics.

text_a: Bill loved home renovation projects. He rented a drum sander from a home improvement store. Bill sanded down his hardwood floors carefully. The sander's dust bag slipped off the discharge.
text_b_pos: It then took a long time to clean.
text_b_neg: Bill started to distribute the dust over the whole floor.

text_a: Tom had a big date. He was extra nervous about it. Tom got a cold sore because of it. He tried to fix it but it wouldn't go down.
text_b_pos: He eventually cancelled the date.
text_b_neg: Tom's date wanted to get herpes from him.

text_a: Tom was walking home from work. There was a protest going on at the same time. They were marching in the same direction. Tom was swept up as part of it.
text_b_pos: He panicked and ran away.
text_b_neg: He was glad that he did not get into the demonstration.

text_a: I loved swimming at the beach. One day I saw a big shark. The shark suddenly attacked me. I lost my left hand.
text_b_pos: I have never been to the hospital.
text_b_neg: Doctors could stitch it back to my arm.

text_a: Our water service at home suddenly became weak and cloudy. I looked out front and saw the water main had broken. I called the city to send a repair crew to fix it. The repair crew arrived after a short while and mended the water main.
text_b_pos: The water supply was back to normal for my evening shower.
text_b_neg: I brought them some food as they looked hungry.

text_a: In 1975, one of my coworkers was an attractive young woman. We talked on occasion during lunch. She was dating a man who worked in the warehouse. One day she confessed all her teeth were false.
text_b_pos: I was surprised she never went to a dentist.
text_b_neg: I was shocked, her teeth looked so real.

text_a: Kevin was driving to work. He saw a woman stranded on the side of the road. Kevin stopped to help. He remained with the woman until a tow truck arrived.
text_b_pos: The woman was very grateful to Kevin for helping.
text_b_neg: The woman was very upset with Kevin.

text_a: I tried my first sip of beer in sixth grade. I tried it at my friend's birthday party sleepover. My friend snuck a beer from her dad. We all sat in a circle and took a sip of the beer.
text_b_pos: After that I was drinking beer every day.
text_b_neg: At the time I did not find it tasty.

text_a: Zach bought his friend a gift. We wrapped the gift in Christmas paper. He gave his friend the present on his birthday. His friend complained that it wasn't Christmas.
text_b_pos: Zach thought it was Christmas.
text_b_neg: Zach felt ashamed that he used the wrong paper.

text_a: My cat had multiple seizures the other day. The seizures caused her pain. She also lost her sight. I took her to the vet to be put down.
text_b_pos: She died right away.
text_b_neg: The vet complimented her beautiful fur.

text_a: Jeffrey loved oranges more than any fruit. Unfortunately, his family also loved oranges. They would always eat all of the oranges before he could have any. So, Jeffrey hid the oranges in a box that said it was celery.
text_b_pos: Jeffrey had an orange every evening from then on.
text_b_neg: Jeffrey ate celery for dinner.

text_a: I just want today to be a restful day. I go visit my friend at her house. We go for a walk. We talk about life.
text_b_pos: I have a lot to do in my job today.
text_b_neg: She told me she is pregnant.

text_a: Bill was looking for a new job. Bill got two new job offers on the same day. One job would make Bill happy. The other job would pay Bill more money.
text_b_pos: Bill chose neither of the two offered jobs.
text_b_neg: Bill chose the job that made him happy.

text_a: Sally loves to dance. Her first dance class was today. The teacher was very nice. She learned how to twirl with a ribbon.
text_b_pos: Sally hated her dance teacher.
text_b_neg: Sally had a happy day.

text_a: I was picking up my crush from a mutual friend's house with my mom. When he got in, she said I could do much better in French. Of all the things we've talked about, she forgets he speaks French. The ride home was the most awkward thing I've ever done.
text_b_pos: I hate my Mom.
text_b_neg: My mom loves riding her bike.

text_a: Sue liked sandals. She had several pairs in green and pink. One day she went to the new sandal shop in town. She saw the prettiest pair of orange and blue sandals.
text_b_pos: Sue went home to take some money and bought them right away.
text_b_neg: In the end Sue didn't bought them since she wasn't very keen on that type of shoes.

text_a: I used to make necklaces in my spare time. I primarily tried to sell them in an online store. I also sold them at different conventions. I made an amount of money that rounded to zero dollars.
text_b_pos: I stopped making necklaces.
text_b_neg: I became rich.

text_a: Keisha used to be a vegetarian, but she strayed from the lifestyle. She succumbed to cravings for turkey and hamburgers. Keisha was disappointed about this and wanted to renew her commitment. She signed up for a vegetarian cooking class at a restaurant.
text_b_pos: She enjoyed the class.
text_b_neg: She asked for a vegetarian option.

text_a: Lulu was finishing up the last of her new book. She was excited because this was her first book launch. She gathered her friends together for a large party. She was sure it would be a hit.
text_b_pos: Nobody came.
text_b_neg: It was indeed a hit.

text_a: My senior year of high school I was in the Miss Indiana pageant. I prepared for a whole year. All the other girls were more experienced than me. I felt silly at the competition, especially during on stage question.
text_b_pos: I was so prepared and confident, I answered all the questions.
text_b_neg: All the other participants answered more question than I did.

text_a: Kelly was nervous to try a new hairstyle. She decided to dye her hair purple yesterday. It was a curious decision. As she went to school the next day she actually got compliments.
text_b_pos: So she felt happy about it.
text_b_neg: She hated compliments.

text_a: Ben was on a hike one day. Suddenly, he realized he was lost! He tried to stay calm and remember what to do. He stayed put so rescuers could find him.
text_b_pos: They never came.
text_b_neg: Finally he found the parking lot.

text_a: Mom had a fancy pearl necklace that she treasured. One day she lent it to Jo, who broke the clasp! She took it to Mom, but Mom just laughed. Jo was confused, but then Mom pulled out her necklace.
text_b_pos: Mom had not given the real necklace to Jo.
text_b_neg: Mom never gave Jo the necklace again.

text_a: One of my retired coworkers is a bus consultant. She is on a project to rebuild transit buses. She drove up to the rebuild site last week. She took a photo of a rebuilt bus headed back.
text_b_pos: Now she is rebuilding her own bus.
text_b_neg: She took the bus to come back.

text_a: Amy liked to bake. She made a huge batch of cornbread. She slathered it with butter. She packed it in her lunch.
text_b_pos: Amy bought a huge lunch at the cafeteria.
text_b_neg: She was very popular at school that day.

text_a: Jordan was watching TV on her couch. It was raining outside and she noticed her cat scurrying inside. The cat ran over to Jordan and hopped onto her lap. Jordan realized that the cat's paws were wet, but it was too late.
text_b_pos: The cat had already left wet marks on the floor.
text_b_neg: It should have been wet sooner.

text_a: I needed some new headphones. I saw them at the store for nine dollars. The cashier insisted that they were fifteen dollars. I got the manager.
text_b_pos: I had to pay hundred dollars.
text_b_neg: He told me that the sign was wrong.

text_a: My roommate wanted to make some extra money. She decided to do so by making sandwiches. With all of her work and school though, she'd have no time to sell. Turns out, at her work, her boss wanted to put sandwiches on the menu.
text_b_pos: They made a deal where she would sell sandwiches to her work.
text_b_neg: She really didn't like eating sandwiches.

text_a: Allie loved her phone. It was a great phone. But the only downside was the screen protector. The protector was not good.
text_b_pos: She decided to buy a new screen protector.
text_b_neg: She gave the phone to her best friend.

text_a: The magician pulled out a top hat. He pulled some fabric out of the hat. The fabric seemed to be very long. The audience clapped for the trick.
text_b_pos: The magician gave the hat to someone in the audience.
text_b_neg: The magician bowed.

text_a: Tanner loved playing baseball. He worked hard on his hitting abilities. Tanner wondered if he was good enough to make the highschool team. He attended tryouts.
text_b_pos: He hated playing baseball afterwards.
text_b_neg: He got a good score.

text_a: When I was at cub scout camp we all ate in the same huge tent. One day I saw a group of other cub scouts that my group did not like. I picked up a handful of corn and threw it at them. Soon there was food flying everywhere in that tent.
text_b_pos: We became great friends with the other group.
text_b_neg: I was completely covered in food.

text_a: Jennifer was at the fair. She had bought a cute pink balloon. Suddenly, the wind blew it out of her hand. She tried her hardest to catch it.
text_b_pos: Jennifer like the balloon so much.
text_b_neg: She failed and the balloon flew away.

text_a: Lance was having a hard time finding a date. He was a gay guy and it was frowned upon by man in his community. Lance decided to browse online for a cute guy to date. Lance meets a handsome young man not far from him.
text_b_pos: They went on to become a couple.
text_b_neg: Lance decided to stay celibate.

text_a: The man grunted at the woman. The woman ran from the man. The man shrugged his shoulders. Another man noticed that.
text_b_pos: He told the man that it was inappropriate.
text_b_neg: They both laughed.

text_a: A man rolled his car to the gas pump with no gas in his tank. He asked the gas attendant to fill up his tank. After it was filled, the man owed $40 for all the gas. The man did not have any money to pay.
text_b_pos: The man did not have to pay.
text_b_neg: The gas attendant called the police.

text_a: Tom was cooking dinner. He was trying a meal he found online. He had all the ingredients except for one. Tom decided to substitute it for something similar.
text_b_pos: Nobody noticed the missing ingredient.
text_b_neg: He jumped in his car and went to the grocery store.

text_a: Paul had to take out the garbage to the curb. He emptied all his small garbage cans into a large garbage can. He then took the large can out to the curb. Once the garbage man came, he brought his empty can back inside.
text_b_pos: Paul had to repeat this every week.
text_b_neg: Paul rented a car for his next vacation.

text_a: Jason never had a picket fence dream. But when he met Alissa, she only dreamed of the perfect house. To please her, he perused the market to find a great house. He found one, but Alissa didn't like it.
text_b_pos: He asked Alissa to look for one herself.
text_b_neg: Alissa bought the house.

text_a: Rebecca went out of town for the weekend. She forgot to pay her rent before she left town. Rebecca called her landlord to explain the situation. He told her that there would be a late fee if her rent was late.
text_b_pos: Rebecca said she would pay the late fee and rent as soon as she got back.
text_b_neg: Rebecca said she was never coming back.

text_a: Tim's dad had been stressed from work. Tim wanted to do something special for his father. He bought his dad a brand new radio. His father listened to the news every morning.
text_b_pos: Tim was happy that his father liked his present.
text_b_neg: Tim did not see his father much anymore.

text_a: Last night I kept getting facetime calls from my sister. The phone would ring and they suddenly stop. When I called back it went directly to voicemail. I was beginning to worry.
text_b_pos: Her sister was playing a game.
text_b_neg: Her phone was broken.

text_a: Christopher's apartment complex was redoing their parking lot. Christopher panicked because his car had a flat tire. As he didn't want to be towed, he went to the garage. He bought a new tire.
text_b_pos: He decided to sell his car.
text_b_neg: He changed the flat tire with the new one.

text_a: Chelsea was invited to a dinner party. Each guest was bringing a dish. Chelsea didn't know how to cook. She volunteered to bring dessert.
text_b_pos: Chelsea decided not to go to the party.
text_b_neg: Chelsea bought ice cream to bring to the dinner party.

text_a: Randy was lactose intolerant. At his friend's birthday party, all of the treats had milk in them. He decided to eat a bunch of cake anyways. The following day he felt extremely sick.
text_b_pos: Randy regretted eating the cake.
text_b_neg: To feel better, Randy ate some more cake.

text_a: In the summer Jerry was incredibly bored. It was far too hot to go outside. And Jerry only enjoyed outdoor activities. Jerry moved to Canada where it was not so hot in the summer.
text_b_pos: Jerry was living in an igloo now.
text_b_neg: But you could still go to the beach so Jerry was happy.

text_a: Eliza was sending her daughter Avery to college. It was a tough moment for Eliza. She couldn't believe how the years flew by. Eliza started shedding tears.
text_b_pos: Eliza couldn't wait for Avery to leave.
text_b_neg: Avery was sad about leaving her family and shed tears too.

text_a: Tom had his cat for several years. It got really sick. There wasn't anything the vet could do to help. Tom decided to put it down.
text_b_pos: Tom decided to put it down.
text_b_neg: He was very sad.,He was very happy.

text_a: I just turned 21 years old. My dad took me to a bar to have a drink. We ordered whiskey. It was disgusting!
text_b_pos: We ended up emptying the bottle.
text_b_neg: I don't know what should be great about drinking alcohol.

text_a: Jordan was having breakfast. She was drinking a glass of orange juice with her food. Suddenly, she bumped the cup and it spilled. The juice went all over her mom's antique table cloth.
text_b_pos: Jordan threw the table cloth out.
text_b_neg: Jordan was worried her mother would be angry.

text_a: I went to the store to pick up some food. On my walk there I noticed an attractive girl. As I passed by, I asked her what she's doing. As time went on, I asked if I could have her phone number.
text_b_pos: She walked right past me.
text_b_neg: We dated for two months before breaking up.

text_a: Carlton liked to play with all children. One child was sick however. His mother told him not to play with him. And so Carlton listened.
text_b_pos: Carlton was eating a huge plate of pasta for dinner.
text_b_neg: When Carlton saw the child alone he played with it despite his mothers order.

text_a: My son came home from school wanting to play a new game on his Ipod. He turned it on and waited to play. He waited and waited and waited some more. There was a major update being installed.
text_b_pos: He lost the iPod in the Forest.
text_b_neg: After 30 minutes the iPod was finally ready.

text_a: Summer had just ended. The leaves were changing colors. Some fell onto the ground. I raked them into a pile.
text_b_pos: I then put the leaves back on the tree.
text_b_neg: The next day, the neighbour's dog destroyed the pile.

text_a: Kate and her friends were going on a road trip. But they hadn't timed the trip well. They left at 8 AM. And were stopped dead by rush hour traffic.
text_b_pos: They arrived very late and were unhappy.
text_b_neg: Kate and her friends arrived on time.

text_a: Mary and Evan were engaged to get married. Mary wanted to get married on a beach in Hawaii. They told their friends about their plans. Most of their friends said that they couldn't make the trip to Hawaii.
text_b_pos: Heavy-hearted, they started to look at other venues.
text_b_neg: They were looking forward to having a special day.

text_a: Jason invited his best friend over for dinner. When his friend James arrived, the two ate and played video games. Jason's friend then got sick and vomited all over the couch. Jason's mom came and picked him up.
text_b_pos: Jason enjoyed the evening.
text_b_neg: Jason felt better the next day.

text_a: Two troupes of bagpipers decided to re-enact West Side Story. But with bagpipes. They got as far as, When You're a Jet, You're a Jet. That's when the townspeople came for them.
text_b_pos: They were very successful.
text_b_neg: Both of them hated theatre.

text_a: John had a strong fear of the devil. His mother warned him not to ever sin. John attended church every week. John's priest suggested that he have an exorcism.
text_b_pos: John bought popcorn.
text_b_neg: John didn't know what to do.

text_a: Karen was going to first grade. She was nervous about meeting a new teacher. When she went to school, she was very scared. Karen's teacher turned out to be very nice.
text_b_pos: She thought she was very lucky.
text_b_neg: She was disappointed.

text_a: Becky was in Girl Scouts. She had to do a lot of volunteering. She had a lot of good experiences doing it. It really helped her in life.
text_b_pos: She found many friends in the Girls Scouts.
text_b_neg: She never liked the Girl Scouts.

text_a: Malory was out paying bills when she decided to go to the casino. She had a dollar to spare and thought why not. Mallory played the first machine she saw. She thought she was rich when the machine said jackpot for 8 million.
text_b_pos: Malory paid another bill she had forgotten about.
text_b_neg: Malory kept on gambling but lost all the money again.

text_a: When I was a boy, I found a stray cat on the street. I brought it home and my parents got mad at me. They told me I could not have a cat in the house. I did not want to let it go, but I placed it outside.
text_b_pos: I saw my new cat every day on my way to school.
text_b_neg: I saw my new dog every day on my way to school.

text_a: I embarked on a new diet. This time I started restricting more than ever. I limited myself to no more than 800 calories per day. I lost a lot of weight at first.
text_b_pos: But after a while, I could not lose any more weight.
text_b_neg: I started to gain weight again.

text_a: I had never gone skiing before. My friend invited me on his family's ski trip. I was nervous and inexperienced. I took a ski class the first day.
text_b_pos: The second day I went on the slopes.
text_b_neg: The next day I was skiing with ease.

text_a: Bob and Judy were bored. They decided to cure their boredom by going out for ice cream. So they jumped into their car and took off for downtown. They got to the ice cream shop and parked the car.
text_b_pos: Bob and Judy hate ice cream.
text_b_neg: Bob takes a vanilla ice cream.

text_a: Ken hated cleaning. He decided to hire a maid. She came over once a week and did all the cleaning. Ken was thrilled with her work!
text_b_pos: He made plans to do it himself again in the near future.
text_b_neg: He decided it had been worth paying her.

text_a: Joanne bought a new pan at the store. When she got home she cleaned it. She cooked veggies in it but a strange smell emanated from the pan. She removed the veggies but the smell was still there.
text_b_pos: She kept using the pan.
text_b_neg: She returned the pan.

text_a: Kim wanted to go shopping. But all of her friends were busy that day! Then Kim decided to ask her mom and sister. The three women went to the mall together.
text_b_pos: Kim quickly got bored and wanted to go home.
text_b_neg: Kim shopped for three hours.

text_a: Bree had woken up late. She rushed to school as quickly as possible. When she got there the parking lot was empty. Bree was confused and called her friend.
text_b_pos: Her friend told it was Saturday.
text_b_neg: Her friend asked her why she wasn't at school.

text_a: The row team had trained for several months. Today was race day and they lined up at the start. Midway through the race, the row team was in second place. With only one minute left, the row team surged ahead as practiced.
text_b_pos: The race took place on top of the mountain.
text_b_neg: The row team won.

text_a: Gina's grandma saved her breakfast as she slept in. She was upset when there was no food on the table. She didn't want to have to cook her own breakfast. She wanted to eat her grandma's cooking.
text_b_pos: Her grandma knew that so she saved the breakfast.
text_b_neg: She did not care when there was no food on the table.

text_a: Making crafts for Christmas gifts was a mistake, Jane decided. She tried not to panic when her hand became stuck to the table. Then the doorbell rang. Jane had forgotten all about her date.
text_b_pos: Her date entered and unglued her hand.
text_b_neg: Her date broke up with her.

text_a: Jeff loved ice cream. He ate it every night. He got really fat. Jeff couldn't get a girlfriend.
text_b_pos: He decided to get back in shape.
text_b_neg: His girlfriend also liked ice cream.

text_a: Susan got a jigsaw puzzle for Christmas from her father. It was a homemade puzzle he cut himself. The picture was of a tropical island. When she turned it over, the back was a ticket to see Taylor Swift.
text_b_pos: She went to the concert.
text_b_neg: She was upset at the gift.

text_a: Lindsay was getting ready for her friend's wedding. She changed into her outfit. She realized there was a stain on the front of her dress. Lindsay's mother had stain remover.
text_b_pos: The stain turned bright red.
text_b_neg: Unfortunately, the stain could not be removed.

text_a: Miley had wanted to sing in the church choir. She was told there was no room for any new singers. Last Sunday she was asked to fill in for a week. Miley gladly accepted the invite.
text_b_pos: She wanted to impress the audiences so that she would have a chance to stay at the choir.
text_b_neg: Miley barely knew how to sing.

text_a: Tom wanted to eat something delicious. He also wanted to be a healthy person. He saw oatmeal raisin cookies at the store. He thought that oatmeal and raisins were both healthy.
text_b_pos: Therefore, he decided to buy ten cookies.
text_b_neg: He did not care that the cookies contained a lot of sugar.

text_a: Stacy was a little girl. She watched a lot of cartoons. She asked her parents to do her room in a cartoon theme. They had to think about it for awhile.
text_b_pos: Eventually Stacy's parents agreed and painted her room the way she wanted.
text_b_neg: Stacy's parents painted her room black.

text_a: The teacher announced that there would be a vocabulary quiz in a week. The students decided not to define their terms. When it was time for the test, the students were not ready. The teacher gave out the quizzes and there were many complaints.
text_b_pos: Everyone passed easily.
text_b_neg: Almost everyone failed the quizzes.

text_a: Evan liked to help his Mother make dinner. One evening Mother was boiling water to make Macaroni and Cheese. Evan came to the kitchen to help as usual. He tried to look into the pot, but knocked the pot off the stove!
text_b_pos: His mother thanked him for his great help.
text_b_neg: His mother was very angry.

text_a: Amy's mom was taking her to have her hair braided. Amy sat in a chair while a woman braided her hair. The braids were tight, and they hurt. When finished Amy liked her hair very much.
text_b_pos: Amy didn't enjoy her new appearance.
text_b_neg: Amy was very happy.

text_a: Andy and his wife had been trying to conceive a child for three years. However, after three years, their attempts to conceive did not work. Andy and his wife decided they would try to adopt a baby instead. After meeting with an adoption agency, they now had to wait.
text_b_pos: They decided they didn't want a child.
text_b_neg: They decided to wait until they could adopt.

text_a: Linette was at the shopping mall. She was absolutely parched but couldn't find a working fountain. She complained to a manager about the out of service fountains. He apologized and promised to handle it.
text_b_pos: Linette ate a pizza.
text_b_neg: The next week the fountains were working.

text_a: Eva signed up for a spinning class. She wanted to get in shape. At first she was nervous about spinning. But when she arrived, she sat that it looked quite fun.
text_b_pos: She decided to go back home.
text_b_neg: She wasn't so nervous afterwards.

text_a: Ken was going on a flight to his parents home. He had to pass through airport security. Ken had forgotten that he had his pocket knife on him. Ken's pocket knife was confiscated.
text_b_pos: Ken never saw that knife again.
text_b_neg: He was very happy.

text_a: I went to the theme park for the rides. I went to the most popular ride in the entire park. The line was very long. I stood at the end and waited for my turn.
text_b_pos: I don't like rides in a theme park.
text_b_neg: After the wait I could finally enjoy the ride.

text_a: Kia started hanging with a bad crowd in high school. For a few weeks, they were fun and seemed exciting to her. But then one of the group's antics landed Kia in detention! Kia spent a long week thinking things through.
text_b_pos: She left that crowd and told them she had changed.
text_b_neg: Kia praised the group for their great idea.

text_a: Adam loves spaceships. He was on his way to Port Canaveral to see a live spaceship launch. Upon arrival, he found a space where he could see clearly. As the countdown began Adam got extremely excited.
text_b_pos: Because his dream to see a spaceship will finally come true in seconds.
text_b_neg: He will burn the spaceship down.

text_a: She started to dance, but there was work to do and so she stopped. She picked up the pen and paper instead. Since her body couldn't dance, she made the pen dance on the paper. Her body, refusing to hold still, started to sway in time with the pen.
text_b_pos: The pen was empty.
text_b_neg: She gave up working and started dancing with her whole body,

text_a: Ana didn't need to read about the heatwave in the paper. All she needed to do was open her door to feel it. Ana decided she was going to do something about it. She grabbed her bikini and went right down to the local pool.
text_b_pos: She felt cool at the local pool.
text_b_neg: She enjoyed the sunshine in the afternoon.

text_a: One night my friends and I learned that our favorite band was playing. The location was about 2 hours away but we didn't have tickets. As it turned out, a friend in a group chat was giving away free ones. We quickly snagged them up and headed to the concert.
text_b_pos: We gave the tickets away in a group chat.
text_b_neg: We had a great night at the concert.

text_a: After taking a bath, I went to the living room. I took out several books and began studying. When I read a passage, my eyes started to close. An hour later, my sister woke me up.
text_b_pos: I had read the entire book in the meantime.
text_b_neg: I felt very relaxed.

text_a: One day Desi's husband was a few minutes late coming home. She hoped he was okay and hadn't gotten stuck at work! Then he came through the door with his hands full. He held out a big bouquet of roses to Desi!
text_b_pos: Desi did not like that he was late.
text_b_neg: Desi gave him a passionate kiss.

text_a: We found a car wash that was automatic. We had to stop and remove the antennae. As we drove into the wash, the water came down. The car was covered in soap.
text_b_pos: The antenna broke.
text_b_neg: We got a clean car afterwards.

text_a: My friend asked me for help when he was writing his book. I was supposed to act out a character he wrote then ad lib. I really got into character and he was really impressed with me. I went on for a long time and made the story my own.
text_b_pos: My friend also liked my story.
text_b_neg: I am a better writer than my friend.

text_a: The kid had a new watch. It was set to go off every night at nine pm. His dad would get so annoyed when he would hear it. Finally, the dad took the batteries out.
text_b_pos: The kid thanked dad.
text_b_neg: The kid was very disappointed.

text_a: Senator Johnson was elected into office. He promised his constituents he would vote for higher pay. When the time came to vote, Senator Johnson wasn't in session. His constituents felt let down by his absence.
text_b_pos: He had delivered on his promises.
text_b_neg: He didn't get reelected.

text_a: Our 2 year old granddaughter finally got to Boston. It was a five hour drive from New Jersey. There was a lot of traffic in CT. We waited outside for them to come.
text_b_pos: It took another hour and then they finally arrived.
text_b_neg: They took too long so we decided not to wait anymore.

text_a: My fingers were swelling from arthritis. I didn't know how I would work. I tried putting ice on them. I also took some aleve.
text_b_pos: I like my job.
text_b_neg: The pain would not disappear.

text_a: Marcus tapped his fingers on his lemonade stand. Business was slow. Every car seemed to be passing by. Finally, a bicyclist pulled up.
text_b_pos: Marcus thought the bicyclist was crazy and would not serve him any lemonade.
text_b_neg: The bicyclist bought two cups of lemonade.

text_a: Jenna was sick. Her doctor told her to take medicine three times a day. She forgot half the time. She got even sicker and had to go back.
text_b_pos: She was cured.
text_b_neg: The doctors now only gave her three months to life.

text_a: Alan went to his family's party. Although it was boring, he enjoyed eating the food. After he was full, he decided to leave without telling anyone. The family was trying to look for Alan when they noticed.
text_b_pos: Alan called his mother and said the food was bad.
text_b_neg: He later regretted his decision and wrote an apology by email.

text_a: Rudy worked on the local news station as a weatherman. His predictions were not always accurate, but he was very funny. During a bad hurricane, Rudy was sent out to report on the weather. He unfortunately got hurt by a flying piece of wood while filming.
text_b_pos: I really miss Rudy's funny weather reports.
text_b_neg: Rudy was a bad and unfunny reporter so it was ok.

text_a: Rita and Katie were looking for the moon. They both wanted to see the moon first. Katie ran around looking at the sky. She fell down from running too fast.
text_b_pos: She couldn't see the sky.
text_b_neg: She broke her leg.

text_a: Steve took his Texan wife to a soccer game. The fans shouted loudly and Steve forget she was there with him. When he eventually remembered her, he saw her nose was bleeding! One of the fans had elbowed Steve's wife in the face!
text_b_pos: Steve congratulated him.
text_b_neg: Steve punched him in the face!

text_a: The heater at Bobby's house didn't work. It was very cold. Bobby spent a few nights at his friend's house. He saved up money to fix the heater.
text_b_pos: Bobby stayed in his house while it was cold.
text_b_neg: Now Bobby's house is warm again.

text_a: Colin broke up with his girlfriend when he moved to Minnesota. He didn't want to have a long-distance relationship. He also felt that it was time for them to date other people. However, Colin soon realized that he missed Barb terribly.
text_b_pos: Colin did not want to talk to Barb again.
text_b_neg: Colin was sad and realized his error.

text_a: Tom loved a song that came on the radio. He tried to find it everywhere. Finally a friend told him he found the song. Tom was excited to hear it again.
text_b_pos: He listened to it all day long.
text_b_neg: He hated his friend.

text_a: Alfred knew something was different about today when he awoke. He opened his curtains and saw snow everywhere! He turned on the radio and listened intently. The radio announced that school was cancelled!
text_b_pos: Alfred was happy that he could go back to bed.
text_b_neg: Alfred went to school.

text_a: I decided to make burgers. I made the patties and put them on a plate. I left the plate on the picnic table. Next thing I knew, the dog had stolen the plate.
text_b_pos: The dog ate everything.
text_b_neg: The dog took his fair share and left the rest to me.

text_a: Joe had a huge headache. He tried to sleep it off. He woke up with a bigger headache. He then took some medicine.
text_b_pos: He got a even worse headache.
text_b_neg: He felt better after taking the medicine.

text_a: Yannick was happy to visit New York city. He sent daily emails to his friends in France to update them. They asked him if he dared going up the Empire State building. Yannick didn't like heights but he accepted the challenge.
text_b_pos: Yannick likes climbing high buildings.
text_b_neg: When he was at the top he got a heart attack.

text_a: Darcy had been asked out on a date. She was supposed to meet him at the theater. She stood there for almost an hour. Soon, she realized that her date wasn't going to show up.
text_b_pos: Darcy loves going to the theater with her dates.
text_b_neg: Darcy was sad and went home alone.

text_a: Jackie was participating in an engineering program. Their class got to build a robot to compete in a race. The robot took a lot of time and effort. In the end, it pulled through.
text_b_pos: The robot was disassembled.
text_b_neg: It won the race and Jackie got a medal.

text_a: Miranda had fallen asleep with her laptop. She was rolling around in bed through the night. Suddenly she woke up to the sound of a crack. She had rolled onto her laptop.
text_b_pos: The laptop was broken.
text_b_neg: The laptop had not been hurt.

text_a: Tom was having a pizza party for his birthday. He had all his friends over. They played games and opened presents. The time for the pizza was near.
text_b_pos: Tom wanted to continue playing games.
text_b_neg: Tom hates Pizza.

text_a: Bill worked at a gas station. He did not like his job very much. One day Bill was an hour late for work. Bill's boss fired him for being late.
text_b_pos: Bill thought that it was time to look for another job anyway.
text_b_neg: Bill begged the boss not to fire him.

text_a: A photographer was in a dangerous situation. He took a photograph as the situation deteriorated. He was injured and this left him unable to explain what he had seen. The photograph was examined by the authorities.
text_b_pos: It was useless.
text_b_neg: The photographer really liked his camera.

text_a: Tim was with his family on a trip. They went to a gemstone mine. After learning about the place they were allowed to mine. Tim found several nice rocks.
text_b_pos: He took them home and still treasures the today.
text_b_neg: Tim had wanted ugly rocks.

text_a: I arrived at the festival. There were a group of band performers on stage. One of the speaker boxes exploded into flames. Everyone jumped out of the stage.
text_b_pos: Luckily nobody was harmed.
text_b_neg: It was an amazing concert.

text_a: Allen loved to cut hair. He was one test away from getting his barber license. During the final test he had to demonstrate some advanced hairstyles. On the very last hair cut his hand twitched and the scissors slipped.
text_b_pos: He never liked cutting hair at all.
text_b_neg: It fell on his foot and he started bleeding.

text_a: Serena was shopping at the mall all day. She was about to leave when she realized that her wallet was missing. She rushed inside and began searching everywhere for it. Soon the mall had closed before she could find it.
text_b_pos: Serena returned in the morning to search again.
text_b_neg: She went happily home.

text_a: Henry was playing baseball with Jeff. Henry challenged Jeff to a throwing contest. However, he broke a classroom's window when he threw the ball. The teacher got out of the classroom and scolded the two.
text_b_pos: The teacher gave them a new ball.
text_b_neg: They apologised and helped repairing the window.

text_a: I decided to make fried chicken again for dinner. I got the chicken out of the freezer and let it thaw. Then I put it in my frying pan with just a little oil. The first side got browned so I turned it over to cook the other side.
text_b_pos: The other side was already brown.
text_b_neg: I cooked the other side as well.

text_a: A new grocery store was opening in town. First hundred customers got a hundred dollar gift certificate. I got there at six in the morning to wait in the already long line. Finally, near opening time, workers started passing out the goodies.
text_b_pos: Workers were hard working.
text_b_neg: I was the 101th person waiting in that line.

text_a: She was excited when she found the coupon. It was for $50 at her favorite makeup store. She browsed the site for hours. She chose her purchase carefully.
text_b_pos: She checked out the goods using the coupon.
text_b_neg: She gave the coupon to her friend.

text_a: My aunt was against using vaccines. She thinks they might not be safe. Whenever we talk we discuss the issue. She says she will look into it further.
text_b_pos: I do not think vaccines work.
text_b_neg: I do not think my aunt understands how vaccines work.

text_a: Harry needed to save his friend. He was told where the friend would be. Luckily Harry had the skills to defeat his friend's captors. His friend was happy to be saved.
text_b_pos: His friend pushed him away in anger.
text_b_neg: His friend was deeply thankful.

text_a: Bill was throwing rocks at school. It was recess time. But the recess teacher on duty caught what he was doing. And he was sent to the principal's office.
text_b_pos: The principle scolded Bill for throwing rocks.
text_b_neg: Bill decided to smell the flowers instead.

text_a: Tom enjoys cooking. He wants to make a delicious meal for the family event. He plans to spend all day cooking tomorrow. The stove wouldn't turn on in the morning.
text_b_pos: He forgot to pay the bill from the gas company.
text_b_neg: Tom wanted to order pizza anyways.

text_a: Henry is trying to launch a startup. He wants to start an independent videogame developer. However, he has no programming experience. Henry recruited some of his friends in computer science to help.
text_b_pos: They were all given shares in the company.
text_b_neg: The computer stopped working.

text_a: The local high school was having a fashion show. Jim went as a reporter for the school paper. He interviewed the designers, and photographed the event. Jim wrote a glowing review of the event.
text_b_pos: Nobody read Jim's report.
text_b_neg: Jim was praised by the editor.

text_a: Laura worked at a convenience store. One evening, a man walked in and drew a gun. He demanded all the money that Laura had in the register. Laura reached behind the counter and drew pepper spray.
text_b_pos: She wished she had a weapon to defend herself.
text_b_neg: She sprayed it into the mans face and ran away.

text_a: Phil was in the middle of a conversation. All of a sudden his phone died. The battery was depleted. Phil got angry and threw the phone.
text_b_pos: The phone started working again.
text_b_neg: The phone landed on the ground and broke.

text_a: The girl was starting dance class. She bought a new leotard for the occasion. It was pink and purple spotted. She put on the leotard and was so excited to start dancing.
text_b_pos: She stopped going to her dancing class.
text_b_neg: She ripped her leotard on the way to the class and was very sad.

text_a: Alyssa had to be awake by 7 am in order to be on time. The electricity went off, the alarm clock did not. It was after 9 am when she woke up. She frantically rushed to get dressed, hitting her ankle on furniture.
text_b_pos: She came late.
text_b_neg: She went to the doctor.

text_a: Tom was a fitness enthusiast. He would frequent the local gym. He saw a new piece of equipment. He tried the new equipment.
text_b_pos: He had sore muscles the rest of the week.
text_b_neg: He was too weak for it.

text_a: Pat was at a race. He wanted to win badly. He ran until he fell and hurt his knee. Pat decided to hop on one leg to finish.
text_b_pos: She had a wonderful time.
text_b_neg: She did not make it to the finish line.

text_a: Tina was having a party. It was celebrating the new year. Everyone was invited. Except for Suzy.
text_b_pos: Suzy was very angry about this.
text_b_neg: Suzy enjoyed the party very much.

text_a: Justin was driving his black car down the road. He was speeding but he didn't realize it. The next thing you know he was pulled over by a cop. The cop told him he was going too fast.
text_b_pos: He got a fine.
text_b_neg: He married the police officer.

text_a: Nick found out he had throat cancer. It was a total shock. It was stage III, so he was very worried. But luckily, his surgery went well.
text_b_pos: Nick regretted every single day having had that surgery.
text_b_neg: Nick kept living a normal life without further consequences.

text_a: Tim called his friend Paula on the phone. They had a nice conversation for several minutes. Paula was busy so she told Tim she would call him back. Tim watched television while waiting for Paula to call.
text_b_pos: Tim was happy when Paula called him back.
text_b_neg: Tim didn't want to speak to Paula again.

text_a: Andrew made a plate of chicken for himself. He heard the phone ring. He went to answer it. He came back and the chicken was gone.
text_b_pos: Andrew was very confused about where the chicken went.
text_b_neg: Andrew was delighted.

text_a: Ben was riding a bike fast one day. Down the sidewalk he went as fast as he could. Ben didn't see the large branch in the way. His front tire hit the branch and the bike and ben went flying.
text_b_pos: Ben was lucky to wear his helmet.
text_b_neg: Ben was more attractive without his helmet.

text_a: Holly was feeling very sick. Her mother checked her temperature. They found out she had a fever. She was allowed to stay home instead of go to school.
text_b_pos: Holly decided to go swimming with her free time.
text_b_neg: Holly went to the hospital.

text_a: Lindsey was very excited to try her new recipe. She carefully coated chicken in cheese and bread crumbs. She then placed the chicken breasts in a pan to put in the oven. As her guests arrived later, she saw she had never turned the oven on.
text_b_pos: She did not like to be around people.
text_b_neg: Lindsey turned the oven on.

text_a: Ky took a summer job dogsitting. It sounded like easy money-just let the dog out twice a day. She also had to walk it once every evening. But she hadn't counted on the dog being so mean-and strong!
text_b_pos: Once when she let the dog out, the dog got away from her.
text_b_neg: Ky wanted to get a dog.

text_a: Alice was a teacher at an elementary school. Alice stepped out into the hall to talk to another teacher. Her class became extremely loud. Alice stepped back into the room.
text_b_pos: Things calmed down again quickly.
text_b_neg: They started singing a song together.

text_a: Ben dropped some sugar in his kitchen. He forgot to clean it up right away. The next day, he saw a nasty shock. The kitchen floor was swarming with black ants!
text_b_pos: He immediatly went out to buy poison.
text_b_neg: He decided to throw an ant party.

text_a: Neil was doing a story on the country of Burma. He took a plane into Burma, or Myanmar. There, he interviewed members of the press. He got a great story to take to his editors.
text_b_pos: Neil was fired for his laziness.
text_b_neg: He won a Pulitzer prize for his work.

text_a: I started using the monkey emoji with one of my best friends. One day she said something that was embarrassing, and sent the emoji. I thought it was cute, so it became a habit between us. Now, whenever someone says something scary or shameful, we use it.
text_b_pos: I went to a fancy restaurant with my best friend last night.
text_b_neg: Other people saw it and started using the money emoji too.

text_a: Corey gave a lot of thought to doing some volunteer work. Corey wanted to give back to his community in a meaningful way. At a school presentation, Corey learned about Habitat For Humanity. Corey signed up for a Habitat for Humanity project in his town.
text_b_pos: He then moved away from his town.
text_b_neg: It was a lot of work but he felt good doing it.

text_a: Rob had always wanted to join the Marines. He knew it would be quite difficult, but believed in his dream. He spent all his free time preparing and joined ROTC. When he turned 18, Rob immediately started the process of joining.
text_b_pos: Rob was a pacifist.
text_b_neg: He got accepted on first try.

text_a: Jake was having a great time at dinner. He was out with his girlfriend. They finished up at the steakhouse. Jake walked out to his parking spot.
text_b_pos: But his car was gone!
text_b_neg: He then walked back into the steakhouse.

text_a: John hated the neighbors two doors down. Every year, they put up tasteless and gory Halloween decorations. But this year, they really topped anything from prior years. They had a very realistic stuffed man hanging from a noose in a tree.
text_b_pos: John wrote a complaint letter to the housing association.
text_b_neg: John congratulated the neighbours for their achievement.

text_a: Jackie believed she was the best at yodeling. She challenged her father to a yodeling contest. Her father agreed to the challenge. Jackie practiced really hard on her yodeling skills.
text_b_pos: She beat her father in the contest.
text_b_neg: Jackie did not like yodeling.

text_a: David bought a nice-looking painting at a garage sale. David's friend said he thought it looked like a Picasso. David became convinced he had found a treasure. He took it to an appraiser, and was told it was not priceless.
text_b_pos: David went on to celebrate his discovery.
text_b_neg: It turned out he'd just bought a cheap copy after all.

text_a: Loni was very worried about her cat. It kept coughing and making strange noises. She was going to take it to the vet. However, the source of the cough was quickly found.
text_b_pos: Her cat quickly got healthy.
text_b_neg: She took her cat to the vet.

text_a: Neil flew into Chiang Mai, Thailand. He booked a jungle tour. They took him to ride elephants and see jungle tribes! Then he shopped for jungle souvenirs.
text_b_pos: The elephants were enemies of the jungle tribes.
text_b_neg: They expectedly were overpriced.

text_a: Lola was writing her first novel. Her computer crashed and she lost all of her data. Lola was worried she would have to start over. She remembered she made a backup last week.
text_b_pos: She was relieved that the bulk of the story was backed up.
text_b_neg: She did not bother to check whether the story was backed up.

text_a: Travis was supposed to go cycling, but it just started raining. Dejected, he sat down on the couch. Then he spotted a book he read a decade ago. He dove into the book and read 300 pages during the day.
text_b_pos: He did not like the book at all.
text_b_neg: He lost complete track of time.

text_a: I began the new year by starting Middlemarch. It was George Eliot's masterpiece. The book was 830 pages long. I read a 100 pages a day.
text_b_pos: I could finish the book after just a week.
text_b_neg: It took me until December to finish the book.

text_a: Josh heard the news about the Rams trading Smith, their quarterback. That was Josh's favorite player. He even had Smith's football jersey. Josh felt so betrayed.
text_b_pos: Josh became a fan of the Rams.
text_b_neg: Josh was really upset.

text_a: Tom had a blind date. He was nervous about it. He got to the restaurant early and started drinking. After a while he had too many glasses of wine.
text_b_pos: He did not make a good first impression.
text_b_neg: He did not like wine.

text_a: Tom was taking a road trip. He saw some beautiful nature. He pulled the car over to view it. He got out of his car.
text_b_pos: He emptied his trash on the side of the road.
text_b_neg: He took a picture and shared it with his wife.

text_a: Marion and Louise had a pet parrot named Preacher. When I walked in, Preacher said hello. He started learning my name when he saw me. I walked in one day and he said hello with my name.
text_b_pos: I was deeply impressed by his abilities.
text_b_neg: Preacher is a nice boy.

text_a: I sent flowers and a big cookie to my wife for V Day. I sent cookies to my daughter. I sent these items to work. Their colleagues were impressed.
text_b_pos: So they wanted to get to know me.
text_b_neg: They did not like flowers.

text_a: My school practices what they call alternate seating. We're allowed to do our work while laying on the floor or on beanbags. For tests and written work, we use our desks still. It's really nice to be able to relax while I read or study.
text_b_pos: I find it hard to focus on work while lying on the floor.
text_b_neg: My friends from other schools are all very jealous of our special seating agreement.

text_a: Jay grew up obsessed with hip hop. He dreamed he could one day be a rapper. So for Christmas his mom bought him a mic and a boombox. Jay is now a thirty year old accountant with a new wish.
text_b_pos: He wished he had not dropped out of school for his rapping career.
text_b_neg: He wishes he had never been born.

text_a: One night the Schnauzer family had a board game night. They played Pictionary. Mrs Scherzer's drawings were horrible. Everyone made fun of her.
text_b_pos: She started being angry, and left the room.
text_b_neg: Mrs Schwerzer started using the black pen instead.

text_a: Patty had a husband. One day she walked to the store and met a guy. He flirted with her. Patty went with him to his house.
text_b_pos: Patty had a husband and a new dog.
text_b_neg: Patty had a husband and a new lover.

text_a: Today was the big day for Tony. He was graduating college. All of Tony's family was in the audience. When Tony walked across the stage his family cheered.
text_b_pos: He would remember this moment forever.
text_b_neg: He was sad.

text_a: Bob was a traffic cop. He has a quota requirement every month. He was behind on his totals for November. Because he was behind on his totals, he made a plan.
text_b_pos: He decides to resign his job.
text_b_neg: He will work harder this month.

text_a: Julian was at the grocery store when his grandma called. It was his birthday and she immediately began singing him a song. Somehow his phone went on speaker and everyone could hear her sing. Julian cringed as people began staring at him.
text_b_pos: Julian turned off the phone immediately.
text_b_neg: Julian felt happy with that song.

text_a: Willard seeks health through foods. He knows they're good for him if they have the right label. He religiously buys organic, and nothing else. Willard is baffled, though.
text_b_pos: Healthy food did not heal his cancer.
text_b_neg: Willard found a living animal among organic potatoes.

text_a: The school was buzzing with excitement. They were having a college football team come speak to them! They shook hands with the players and got autographs. The kids were so happy to meet these amazing athletes.
text_b_pos: The kids didn't like football.
text_b_neg: The athletes inspired the kids to play football.

text_a: Everyone said that Cecil was a good cook. He decided to use that talent to make money. Cecil got a business loan to open his own restaurant. The place was packed for the grand opening!
text_b_pos: He could not repay loans.
text_b_neg: He achieved his dream.

text_a: Christina is unhappy at work. The people she works with are discriminating against her. Christina is Filipino, and cherishes her traditions and lifestyle. Her boss had a team meeting and requested that the action stop.
text_b_pos: Her boss liked Filipino food.
text_b_neg: However, that didn't really end the discrimination against Christina.

text_a: Lacey just bought new nail polish. She was painting her nails when her dog came running. Her dog knocked over the bottle and it shattered on the floor. Lacey was not able to get the stain out.
text_b_pos: She gave the dog a treat.
text_b_neg: She was mad and screamed at the dog.

text_a: The tiny green alien was made of plastic. The girl giggled as it popped open against the fridge. She touched the magnet gently against the metal. The eyes popped open and its ears shot up.
text_b_pos: She got some milk from the fridge.
text_b_neg: It made her laugh even more.

text_a: Derek loved math in school. He went to college for math. Derek is now a math teacher. He gets to be around math every day.
text_b_pos: He thinks Math is important.
text_b_neg: Derek is not a teacher.

text_a: Lonny wanted to travel to India. He knew he would have to learn Tamil. Tamil was a very important dialect in India. He studied the language for a year.
text_b_pos: Lonny has never taken any language classes.
text_b_neg: But he still couldn't manage it.

text_a: Jody was a waitress. She worked hard at her job. She made sure her customers were taken care of. Today she received a table of mean teenagers.
text_b_pos: The teenagers went to school together.
text_b_neg: But she treated them respectfully anyway.

text_a: Fred had a bad habit of interrupting his friends. He did it more when drinking. One night he annoyed everyone too much. They all told him to stop.
text_b_pos: He got upset and left.
text_b_neg: He tried to change his interrupting.

text_a: Bidd Badd sat his sister down. He looked her right in the eyes. Then he gave her the terrible news. She started crying.
text_b_pos: The news was nothing serious.
text_b_neg: A good friend of hers got into serious trouble.

text_a: I grilled some steaks for my friends the other day. I bought some real nice cuts from the store. I spent all day grilling them. I forgot to take them off the grill.
text_b_pos: They were completely burnt.
text_b_neg: A dog jumped and ate them.

text_a: June was an excellent worker. He got the most sales. So he expected to get the promotion. However, her boss gave it to another co worker.
text_b_pos: June was happy for his coworker.
text_b_neg: June was really disappointed and started to look for another employer.

text_a: A family was going grocery shopping. Their grocery list was longer than usual. The family got to the store late and wanted to have dinner earlier. The family divided into teams with separate parts of the list.
text_b_pos: The family managed to do the shopping on time for the dinner.
text_b_neg: Afterwards the family went for dinner late, as they had hoped for

text_a: Karen had been suffering from nightmares for several weeks. She was having more and more trouble sleeping every night. A friend recommended Karen try hypnotherapy. Karen has several appointments with the hypnotherapist.
text_b_pos: The hypnotherapist does not help at all and she continues to have horrible nightmares.
text_b_neg: Karen decides to quit the therapy because she does not have any problems.

text_a: Katie and Erin were best friends. They played together every day. One day Erin got sick. Erin played with Katie anyway.
text_b_pos: Katie killed Erin with a knife.
text_b_neg: Katie got sick.

text_a: Tim was in a new movie. It became more popular than expected. They had a premier for it. Tim was excited and invited may friends.
text_b_pos: All the friends congratulated him.
text_b_neg: Tim wanted to become a bus driver.

text_a: I was taking my dog for a walk. Suddenly the latch on the collar broke. My dog took off down the street. Fortunately a passerby got his attention.
text_b_pos: The passerby run away with the dog.
text_b_neg: The passerby brought the dog back to me.
