text_b_pos: The doctors told Tray not to worry about it and sent him home.
text_b_neg: Luckily the doctors were able to treat him immediately.

text_a: Trey was on the battlefield for the first time. He hid and ran a lot, not confident that he could fight well. Time seemed to go by so slowly. He noticed some of his friends were all running in one direction.
text_b_pos: Trey is a pacifist.
text_b_neg: He joined them running.

text_a: Sam took out his camera to film a movie with his friends. He pointed the camera at Jim and told him to act. Jim made up lines on the spot about being a scientist. He pretended to mix chemicals to make a strong poison.
text_b_pos: Sam left without talking to Jim again.
text_b_neg: Sam was happy with Jim's performance.

text_a: Jackson had always wanted to go on a boat. His parents arranged to a day on the water. He was very excited as he boarded the boat. Soon, he became very sick and did not stop vomiting.
text_b_pos: He didn't want to go on a boat anymore.
text_b_neg: He enjoyed the day.

text_a: Jack needed a new phone. He finally found the one he wanted. He ordered it online. When the phone came in, it was broken.
text_b_pos: He had to send it back and wait for another week.
text_b_neg: He was very happy with his new phone.

text_a: Joe is an avid book collector. There is one book he can never find. He has tried ordering it online with no luck. Joe finally gave up trying to find this book.
text_b_pos: Joe was disappointed.
text_b_neg: Joe was glad.

text_a: It was a very windy day. The weather was perfect for kite flying. Cal loosed his kite into the air and watched it soar. He ran across the field but soon felt a jolt in his string.
text_b_pos: Cal lay down for a nap.
text_b_neg: It was hurting a lot.

text_a: Chad sat down in the car. Joe, Mike and Larry joined him. Mike put on his seat belt. Chad hit a telephone pole.
text_b_pos: Mike was the only one who survived.
text_b_neg: Mike was the only one who dead.

text_a: Amy decided to try eyebrow waxing. She thought it would be less pain than plucking them. At the salon the woman waxed her first eyebrow. It was more pain than Amy expected.
text_b_pos: Her whole eyebrow is gone.
text_b_neg: She just goes for it.

text_a: Sam was always stressed at work. It would often bleed out into his personal life. He noticed it started straining his relationships. Sam decided to quit and get a different job.
text_b_pos: This decision ruined his relationships.
text_b_neg: This decision saved his relationships.

text_a: The man painted a mark on the fence. He shot his bow and arrow at the mark. The mark was hard to hit. He made the mark much bigger.
text_b_pos: He quit playing.
text_b_neg: Then he scored higher.

text_a: Silvia loved to sing. She would sing at the top of her lungs, in her apartment. One day, the police showed up at her door. They gave her a noise ordinance.
text_b_pos: Her neighbours loved to hear her voice.
text_b_neg: Her neighbours hated her singing.

text_a: Hank was driving down the road one day. Suddenly, he felt a big thump from a minor car accident. He looked over the window and saw that he hit a man's car. The man got out and he was very angry at Hank.
text_b_pos: Hank never drove again.
text_b_neg: They had to call the police to assess the damage.

text_a: Lisa was rushing to class, worried about being late. She wasn't paying much attention to where she was going. All of a sudden, she was wet and laying on the ground. She had fallen into a big puddle.
text_b_pos: She arrived to her class on time.
text_b_neg: She didn't make it to the class on time.

text_a: Suzy had a sick grandmother. She was dying of cancer. So she went and visited her in the hospital. It was her last moments.
text_b_pos: Suzy had been too late.
text_b_neg: Though sad her grandmother had gone, Suzy was glad she'd made it in time to say goodbye.

text_a: Clark was at the club. He wanted to hit on girls. He never got up the courage to do it. Eventually he got drunk with his friends instead.
text_b_pos: Because he never got a girl he tried out one of his friends.
text_b_neg: He decided to become a monk.

text_a: Bob went downtown to see the concert in his town. It was called Summerfest and plenty of new bands were playing. Bob loved all the great new music! He wrote down the names of the bands to remember them.
text_b_pos: A few weeks later he went to a concert of one of the bands.
text_b_neg: Bob did not like that kind of music.

text_a: Karl the supermarket bag boy was faced with a dilemma. To fit all the food in one bag or to waste a bag and use two? The stress of the situation piled on him greatly. At last he decided to use two bag just to be safe.
text_b_pos: He likes to use one bag.
text_b_neg: He was glad that he was able to make up his mind.

text_a: Matt was always a bit racist. He would say racial slurs jokingly. One of his friends confronted him about it. Matt got defensive and angry.
text_b_pos: Matt and his friend decided to go for asian food.
text_b_neg: Matt and his friend got into a fight.

text_a: Ken was at the bar. He was waiting to meet his friends. They called to cancel. Ken felt weird being there alone.
text_b_pos: He knew his friends never let him down.
text_b_neg: Ken did not like his friends cancelling on him.

text_a: The man retired. He had nothing to do. He watched too much television. His health became worse.
text_b_pos: He was told by his doctor that he had a good health.
text_b_neg: He finally had to go to the hospital for health check.

text_a: Rita genuinely believed that there were forty-nine states in the USA. Her friends tried their hardest to talk some sense into her. Rita kept denying that Hawaii was a state. She insisted that it was a city.
text_b_pos: But she was convinced eventually.
text_b_neg: She decided to visit Hawai.

text_a: Cindy and Josh had been dating for 3 years. Josh was ready to propose to her. He picked out a ring. One night he took her for a walk.
text_b_pos: The walk was boring and Josh decided to go home.
text_b_neg: He proposed and they were married a few months later.

text_a: My mom wanted to go on vacation this fall. She wasn't sure where she wanted to go but I recommended Korea. She was thinking about it and started researching Korea. She finally agreed to go to Korea and was excited.
text_b_pos: Two months later my mother went to Korea.
text_b_neg: My mother stopped talking about vacation.

text_a: The Omaha zoo was getting new elephants in their zoo. The family drove one hour to go to see the elephants. Once they got their they had to walk to the back of the zoo. One of the elephants was hiding behind the feeding shed.
text_b_pos: They were happy the other elephants were out in plain sight.
text_b_neg: They decided the trip had been well worth it.

text_a: Jenny approached a stranger at the mall. She asked the stranger if she knows where to find the bathroom. Since Jenny is not a US native, her English is hard to comprehend. As a result, the stranger didn't understand what she's saying.
text_b_pos: She explained herself again and the stranger finally understood.
text_b_neg: The stranger told her the way to the bathroom directly.

text_a: Keri need to go pick up groceries for dinner. She wrote a list of things she would need. At the store she was able to find all the items she needed. The cashier assisted her with placing the groceries in the cart.
text_b_pos: Keri went home to prepare the meal.
text_b_neg: Kery realized she had forgotten her list at home.

text_a: The carpenter built a house but measured in both inches in meters. Many parts of the house did not line up properly due to many errors. He was not sure if he was off by inches or meters. He decided to make his own unit system and finish with that.
text_b_pos: With the new system he was able to build better houses.
text_b_neg: The carpenter booked a flight.

text_a: Tim always loved reading and writing. He decided to try and write a book. It took him a long time. Not many people read it.
text_b_pos: Tim was very discouraged because of that.
text_b_neg: Tim made a fortune from his new book.

text_a: Ben lives in Australia. His mother lives in the USA. The phone costs too much for them to talk much. So Ben got his mother a computer.
text_b_pos: Now they use video chat to talk every day.
text_b_neg: Now they never talk to each other.

text_a: My son's FB friend owns a house in Allston. She has been there for ten years. Yesterday she got a $100 parking ticket. Her car was too close to a fire hydrant.
text_b_pos: As she is an FBI agent she did not have to pay for it.
text_b_neg: She has to move out of the house now.

text_a: Henry was a hobby craftsman of small electronics. One day he decided to make a little helper robot. He designed it to carry small buckets and vacuum the floor. His design was bought by a large manufacturer one day.
text_b_pos: He invested the money into his next robot.
text_b_neg: He started cleaning the floor.

text_a: Dan's brother was getting a divorce. His brother couldn't keep the dog. Dan wasn't happy. Dan's parents decided to take the dog.
text_b_pos: Dan went to a Chinese restaurant to eat the dog.
text_b_neg: Dan was happy that the dog had a new home.

text_a: Tom was feeling a bit down during the day. He decided to have an energy drink. Tom drank it fast. It hit him really strongly.
text_b_pos: Tom fell asleep.
text_b_neg: He was wide awake and had to work out for an hour.

text_a: There were rumors about an alligator in the lake. The town made money off of promoting it. One day a tourist was chased by the alligator. The police got involved and caught it.
text_b_pos: The alligator roamed around the city.
text_b_neg: The police had to take the alligator away.

text_a: Bob was playing the new shooter game with his friends online. He was really into the game and played with passion. In an intense match he accidentally cursed out his opponent. His opponent reported him.
text_b_pos: He got banned out of the game.
text_b_neg: Bob cried after finding out.

text_a: Ruby was arranging her baby's first birthday. She wanted everything to be perfect. Unfortunately as a baby her child wasn't cooperating much. Ruby was trying to get her to blow out her candle but gave up.
text_b_pos: Her baby likes blowing out candles.
text_b_neg: Finally, she did it for her.

text_a: Everyone in the bank was in a panic. A robber had burst in and threatened them with a gun! He stole the money and ran away. The police showed up quickly.
text_b_pos: They all partied together.
text_b_neg: The robber started shooting and killed an officer.

text_a: Frank had been drinking beer. He got a call from his girlfriend, asking where he was. Frank suddenly realized he had a date that night. Since Frank was already a bit drunk, he could not drive.
text_b_pos: Frank drove to meet his girlfriend since he was perfectly capable.
text_b_neg: Frank explained the situation to his girlfriend and postponed their date to the following day.

text_a: I went to the small store yesterday. When I got there I wanted some starburst. I grabbed some and went to check out, The man said it was cash only.
text_b_pos: I had to leave it there since I had only my card.
text_b_neg: I paid with my card and left.

text_a: Marcy isn't doing very well in her biology class. She asked her teacher for an extra credit opportunity. He told her to write a song about the content of the class. Marcy loves music so she made sure to make the song great.
text_b_pos: Marcy got extra credit for her successful song.
text_b_neg: Marcy hates writing songs.

text_a: Andre paced nervously in the locker room before his tennis match. He was playing Boris, the highest ranking player, today. He saw Boris, down the hall, pacing just like he was. He felt reassured that everyone gets nervous at times.
text_b_pos: He played a great match.
text_b_neg: He surrendered because he did not see a chance to win.

text_a: Cay and her dad were fishing one afternoon. Cay caught a big sturgeon. Her dad helped her clean it. Then Cay's mom fried it up for dinner.
text_b_pos: The sturgeon enjoyed dinner with the family.
text_b_neg: It tasted wonderfully.

text_a: Charles didn't want to put his mother into a nursing home. But she was ninety years old. Charles went to visit her in the nursing home. She said they didn't take good care of her and that he hated her.
text_b_pos: Charles talked to his boss about his new project.
text_b_neg: Charles regret that he couldn't take care of her himself.

text_a: Phil was hired by Pat to install drapes in his house. The drapes that Phil brought were too long. Pat said that the drapes will not do and to take them back. Phil cut the drapes with a pair of scissors to fix them.
text_b_pos: And now the drapes were too short.
text_b_neg: Phil and Pat became friends.

text_a: Bob was driving his truck down the road when it suddenly broke down. Bob looked under the hood but couldn't figure out what was wrong. He used his smartphone to look up possible explanations. It turns out that sometimes a fuse needs to be replaced in the engine.
text_b_pos: Paul drove to the next service station.
text_b_neg: Paul called the breakdown service.

text_a: Jordan ran into his ex at a lounge. He hasn't seen her in four years. She looked more beautiful than ever. He remember how badly he hurt her.
text_b_pos: He missed his wife.
text_b_neg: He smiled to her but said nothing.

text_a: Mike asked his mom if he could eat frosting. She said no, that's not good for you. Mike cried and begged. His mom gave him an apple instead.
text_b_pos: She said this was much healthier and would help his skin.
text_b_neg: Mike thanked his mom for making healthier choices.

text_a: Maryann has been watching the Olympics all week. Watching has made her miss playing sports. She decided she wants to get back in athletic shape. Maryann begins to plan out her workouts.
text_b_pos: She started eating junk food.
text_b_neg: She started running weekly.

text_a: Billy, a high schooler, really wanted a new car. Billy asked his parents if he could get one for his senior year. His parents told Billy that they would consider it. Billy woke up early for his first day of senior year.
text_b_pos: Billy was happy to see his new car standing in front of the house.
text_b_neg: Billy was happy about his new bicycle.

text_a: Mindy was trying to raise money with a car wash. She wasn't getting any customers. She decided to offer a brownie incentive. Soon, she had more customers lining up like crazy.
text_b_pos: The brownies tasted burnt so nobody wanted to buy them.
text_b_neg: There were not enough brownies so not everyone was able to buy one.

text_a: One day Quinn went to the library. Quinn picked up five books. She also got some copies of Vogue magazine. Then she checked out.
text_b_pos: Quinn went home with new books.
text_b_neg: She left the library without any books.

text_a: Lauren needs to buy a new car. Her old was is constantly breaking down. Lauren decides she has saved up enough money. She has a friend who is selling their newer car.
text_b_pos: She decides to buy a second hand bike.
text_b_neg: She buys the car from her friend.

text_a: Tom's apartment building had an old elevator. It was very slow. Tom decided to take the stairs instead. Over time Tom noticed he was getting in better shape.
text_b_pos: Tom called building services to complain about the elevator.
text_b_neg: The old elevator had actually done him a favor.

text_a: Chris was anxious about starting a new school. He had been at the same school since kindergarten. He was now starting high school as the new kid. In first period, he made a new friend.
text_b_pos: He likes his new friend and new school.
text_b_neg: He quit the school.

text_a: Jason had been practicing his moves. Terry had also been practicing his moves. The crowd cleared and the two stood in front of each other. The music started and they began an epic dance battle.
text_b_pos: But none of them could dance.
text_b_neg: The crowd was impressed and cheered them on.

text_a: The choir wanted to raise money for their trip. They decided to have a dog wash. They scrubbed people's' dogs until they were sparkling clean. It was a fun but messy job.
text_b_pos: They were allergic to dogs.
text_b_neg: They enjoyed their time.

text_a: My work made a mistake with my paycheck. They shorted me by one day. It happened at a bad time. My rent is due.
text_b_pos: I will buy a house instead.
text_b_neg: Now I have to borrow money from a friend.

text_a: Jill had just recently gotten a parrot. It would not stop chirping at night. It kept Jill up all night long for weeks. Jill could not focus on her work due to the lack of sleep.
text_b_pos: Jill gave away her parrot.
text_b_neg: Jill kept the new pet anyway.

text_a: Pancho decided to open a music store. He asked all his friends to suggest names for the store. No one had any good ideas at all for a long time. Finally his brother came up with one funny name.
text_b_pos: Everyone hated the name.
text_b_neg: The name made the story very popular.

text_a: Kia's brother offered to shake her hand on Halloween. She thought it was weird, but she accepted. But as she shook, she got a literal shock! Her brother had put a buzzer in his palm to scare her.
text_b_pos: Kia's hair fell off.
text_b_neg: Kia screamed because the electro shocks were too intense.

text_a: Norman was too fat to be healthy. He felt so heavy, he could barely get out of bed to start his day. To help himself, he started eating healthy food and exercised a lot. After a whole month, he felt a good difference.
text_b_pos: Even though, a month is not enough to get thin.
text_b_neg: He lost 300 pounds.

text_a: Jill couldn't control her spending. She needed to save money. But she kept buying things that she didn't need. She asked her parents for money to pay the bills.
text_b_pos: They bought her a car.
text_b_neg: They refused.

text_a: Ollie would like the moon for his birthday. His mother explains that the moon isn't for sale. Ollie suggests she hasn't asked the right people. Instead he receives a book with facts about the moon.
text_b_pos: Ollie was happy to learn more about the moon.
text_b_neg: Ollie threw the book out because it was not what he wanted.

text_a: After the beating, I felt very sore. I had trouble moving around comfortably for days. He told me it was all my fault. I had driven him to do it, and someday I would marry a man who would.
text_b_pos: I decided to run away from home.
text_b_neg: I was very happy that week.

text_a: When I opened the door the kitten froze. She saw the dog and got scared. She arched her back in fear. She stood there for a minute.
text_b_pos: As soon as the dog left the room the kitten relaxed.
text_b_neg: The kitten loved the presence of dogs.

text_a: Ben went to the pet store to buy a parrot. He found one that he really liked. He bought the parrot and took it home. On the way home he talked to the bird.
text_b_pos: The bird flew away.
text_b_neg: The parrot repeated every word.

text_a: Shauna went to the state fair. She expected to go to the livestock show. When she got there it was nowhere in sight. She asked someone what had happen.
text_b_pos: Shauna learned that PETA activists had killed all the animals.
text_b_neg: Shauna must had turned blind.

text_a: While walking down the street, Ramona found a wallet in the grass. She opened it and found the ID of a man named Jack. She searched the internet and messaged him about what she found. They ended up emailing a lot in the days before they could meet.
text_b_pos: Jack decided he did not want to meet Ramona.
text_b_neg: Ramona became good friends with Jack.

text_a: Anna was addicted to heroin. She was caught stealing to fund her habit. The judge sent her to prison for four years. There, she finally got clean.
text_b_pos: She fell asleep.
text_b_neg: She started a new life.

text_a: John had a really bad headache that wouldn't go away! He took Advil daily with no change. Finally, me and all his friends, told me to go to a doctor. When he went to the doctor he was told he had a sinus infection!
text_b_pos: He now needed antibiotics to get rid off the infection.
text_b_neg: The doctor told him he'd soon recover by himself.

text_a: Mary decided to make tacos for dinner. She cooked the meat and shredded the cheese. Mary put the filling in tortillas. She served the tacos with a big salad.
text_b_pos: She didn't like to anything.
text_b_neg: It was very delicious.

text_a: Jack had just worked out. He was thirsty. He took a big sip of the milk in the fridge. The milk was sour.
text_b_pos: He threw the milk bottle away.
text_b_neg: He gave some milk to his best friend.

text_a: Lauren could not remember where she left her coat. Her mother had Lauren try to recall the last time she had her coat. Lauren remembered that she had taken it off at school. The next morning, Lauren went to the lost and found at school.
text_b_pos: She was happy when they told her they had found her coat.
text_b_neg: She found her  best friend's bag.

text_a: Ray takes a trip to paris. He has never been there before. He visits the Eiffel tower. He stays there for a week.
text_b_pos: He never wanted to visit Paris.
text_b_neg: He enjoyed his time in Paris.

text_a: Tim was waiting for benefits. When he never got them he called to inquire. After several conversations they uncovered a filing mistake. They were able to fix it for Tim.
text_b_pos: Tim never saw the benefits they promised.
text_b_neg: Tim got all the benefits and bought something for him.

text_a: A man worked in a convenience store late on a tuesday night. Suddenly a man rushed in with a gun and held up the store. The clerk gave the man all his money. A siren roared and the cops rushed in.
text_b_pos: They also stole some money.
text_b_neg: They captured the thief.

text_a: My cousin Joi had three kids. One day, a neighbor in the building asked her a question. She wanted to know if Joi would sell an egg to her for $40K. She was trying to conceive a child with her husband.
text_b_pos: Joi was considering it because she needs the money.
text_b_neg: Joi was considering it because it was not expensive.

text_a: The people were hungry for breakfast. They decided to scramble some eggs. They made two dozen eggs in one pan. They all scarfed them down.
text_b_pos: They regret this decision.
text_b_neg: They looked out the window.

text_a: Len was at the racetrack. His boss had told him that a certain horse would win the race. Len bet several thousand dollars on the horse. The horse was slow and ended up getting last place.
text_b_pos: Len thanked his boss for his great help.
text_b_neg: Len did not trust his boss anymore.

text_a: Erica went with her friends to a new restaurant. They ordered everything off the menu. Everything looked delicious. However unfortunately Erica got sick the next day.
text_b_pos: Erica went to the restaurant again.
text_b_neg: Erica decided not to go to that restaurant anymore.

text_a: Gina's friends all had new friendship bracelets. Everyone except Gina. The next day her friend May brought one for Gina. It was clearly made with the leftover threads.
text_b_pos: She took May's bracelet from her cold dead body.
text_b_neg: Gina felt as she was always left over.

text_a: Allie wanted to go on a camping trip. So she got her friends together to go. But when they got there she got scared. They saw a wolf.
text_b_pos: They called the police who came and took care of the wolf.
text_b_neg: They decided to take the wolf to the veterinarian.

text_a: Jim has science fair judging tomorrow. He is extremely nervous. He spent three months on his project. He is convinced he will place but is still nervous.
text_b_pos: He takes a walk to calm his nerves.
text_b_neg: He is calmly optimistic he'll get a commendation.

text_a: Jane was helping Tim out with his auto store's grand opening. She was in charge of cooking free hamburgers for new customers. Jane worried when she cooked meat that it wouldn't be well done. She didn't want customers to get sick and BBQ'd the meat extra.
text_b_pos: Jane did not know you can get sick because of raw meat.
text_b_neg: As a result, she ended up overcooking the meat.

text_a: Jane was playing basketball. It was against her brother. She had never beat him before. This time she got one lucky shot in.
text_b_pos: She was very happy she won against her brother.
text_b_neg: She lost the game aginst her brother very badly.

text_a: Jane always took notes with a pink highlighter. Other students found it quirky but unremarkable. They primarily took notes in pen or pencil. On the day of an open-note exam, the room was dark.
text_b_pos: They could see their notes very well.
text_b_neg: Her mark ended up being better than theirs.

text_a: Liz's parents got a divorce. She wanted to live with her mom. Her mom requested full custody. The judge granted the request.
text_b_pos: Her mother told Liz to go live with her dad.
text_b_neg: Liz and her mother were happy.

text_a: Queenie was getting married in a day. Before her wedding, she went to get a pedicure. They made her feet all pretty. Then, she chose a color for her nails.
text_b_pos: She looked pretty on the wedding day.
text_b_neg: She did not like her feet at all.

text_a: Lori wanted to play a sport and act in a play. Both activities took place at the same time. She was torn between which to choose. Eventually she decided to act in a play.
text_b_pos: Thanks to the sport, she got very fit.
text_b_neg: In the end, it was the right choice.

text_a: Connie used to be a good dart player. When she met Jeff he challenged her to a game. Connie won the first game but lost the next four games. She quickly learned that Jeff was a much better player.
text_b_pos: Connie then tought Jeff how to play.
text_b_neg: Jeff showed her how to increase her skills.

text_a: It was around Christmas time. Kelly was busy making dinner. She went to the living room and saw ornaments on the ground. Her toddler had taken them and was playing with them.
text_b_pos: Kelly took the ornaments away from her toddler.
text_b_neg: Kelly encouraged her toddler to throw an ornament away.

text_a: Alice decided to surprise her husband with a new car, a Dodge Dart. Alice decided she would park the car in her neighbor's yard. This way her husband would not suspect anything. As Dan got home, he saw the car and went by the neighbors to look.
text_b_pos: The neighbors really liked the gift.
text_b_neg: It was the exact model he was dreaming of for years.

text_a: Regina had a pretend boyfriend. Her friend found out that she had made up her boyfriend. Her friend helped her find a real boyfriend instead of making fun. Now Regina and her friend go on double dates together.
text_b_pos: Regina is happy with her real boyfriend
text_b_neg: Regina isn't in a relationship right now.

text_a: The committee wanted to raise $1000 for the new playground balls. They had a bake sale. At the end of the day, they counted all their money. They had reached their goal!
text_b_pos: Everybody was very happy.
text_b_neg: So they went out and used it all for partying.

text_a: George loved to read. He bought a new book to read at night. He got so into the book that he read for hours. When George finished the book, he looked for a sequel.
text_b_pos: George was never going to read another book series.
text_b_neg: The sequel still was not published.

text_a: Tommy has been unemployed for two Year's. He has been looking for work but hasn't yet found anything. One day Tommy sees a babysitter job advertised in the newspaper. He applies and is given the job.
text_b_pos: Being unemployed had made him hate babysitting.
text_b_neg: He liked it and soon aplied for more babysitting jobs.

text_a: Ken was drunk at a bar. There was a mechanical bull. He thought it would be fun to ride. He got on it and stayed longer than anyone expected.
text_b_pos: As soon as he went down he threw up.
text_b_neg: Everyone was really disappointed.

text_a: Tina had sampled her mom's wine last night. Her mom had caught her and grounded her. But the next morning, Tina woke with a terrible hangover. She thought that was a far worse punishment than the grounding.
text_b_pos: Tina decided to drink the rest of the wine on the next day.
text_b_neg: Tina decided to never drink as much wine again.

text_a: Lauren notices that her jeans have developed a small rip. She goes to the crafts store to get thread and a sewing needle. Lauren carefully sews shut the rip in her jeans. She doesn't mind that the thread in her jeans is visible.
text_b_pos: She throws her old jeans away.
text_b_neg: She is satisfied as long as she can wear it.

text_a: Stephanie wanted to go on a date with her husband. The only problem was that she had just had a baby. They had never left the baby with a sitter before and were nervous. Stephanie called someone up and hired them.
text_b_pos: Stephanie had a fight and got divorced.
text_b_neg: The sitter did a great job and Stephanie decided to hire her more often.

text_a: Kenny went to the bar with his friends. He had a little too much to drink. He acted like a fool. His friends had to take care of him.
text_b_pos: Kenny hated them for it.
text_b_neg: Kenny apologized to them the next day.

text_a: Today my wife had a hankering for steak and cheese subs. Our favorite sub shop is only 2 miles away. We called them for delivery. They said we had to buy $100 worth of food.
text_b_pos: My wife ordered some nice robes.
text_b_neg: My wife ordered a lot of steaks and cheese subs.

text_a: We went to the zoo in Naples. They had Giraffe you could feed there. We paid the three dollars and got pieces of lettuce. We stuck it out and the giraffes ate it.
text_b_pos: Then the giraffes wanted more.
text_b_neg: The giraffe started vomiting because of the humans it just ate.

text_a: Thomas bought a train set. His father helped him set it up in the garage. They ran the train around the track for a few minutes. Thomas thought that it was pretty boring.
text_b_pos: He got mad at his dad.
text_b_neg: He decided to give it to his younger brother.

text_a: Bob had a calculus exam and he was well prepared to take it. He walked into class feeling confident. When he sat down at his desk, he realized he forgot his calculator. He panicked and told his teacher.
text_b_pos: His teacher asked him to use the one he had brought.
text_b_neg: His teacher lent him a spare one for the exam.

text_a: My favorite cartoon was called Duck Man. I stayed up in the middle of the night to see it. I felt it was an oddity for its time. I knew I wasn't allowed to watch, so I did so quietly.
text_b_pos: Duck Man is a cartoon most of the people do not know.
text_b_neg: Nevertheless my mom woke up and was angry.

text_a: My son didn't sleep very well. He stayed up all night long. He fell asleep just before his appointment. I woke him up and took him anyway.
text_b_pos: He fell asleep in the car.
text_b_neg: He was very refreshed.

text_a: It was allie's wedding in a few days. She was so busy she had to pick up the cake. When she got the cake everything was good. Until she dropped it.
text_b_pos: The guests enjoyed the nice looking cake.
text_b_neg: She no longer had a cake and ordered a new one.

text_a: Jane's neighbor was playing his music loudly in his car. Jane waited and waited till she could take no more. Jane went to her neighbor's car and knocked on the window. She asked him politely to turn the music down.
text_b_pos: Her neighbor apologised and did as requested.
text_b_neg: Her neighbor apologised and stopped singing.

text_a: Sarah loved to drink coffee. She drank coffee everyday. Her teeth were yellow from the coffee. She stained her teeth with a product she bought.
text_b_pos: Maisie went to the dentist.
text_b_neg: The product worked and Maisie's teeth turned back white.

text_a: Kate's friends were getting married. She couldn't afford anything on their gift registry. She decided to buy a knock off online. She bought the real one from the registry store.
text_b_pos: She was glad to have a gift.
text_b_neg: She opened the safe.

text_a: The child had virtually no fat. He was always cold. The nurses wrapped him in numerous blankets. He continued to shake uncontrollably.
text_b_pos: The boy asked for some ice cream.
text_b_neg: After he drank some tea, the boy felt better.

text_a: Riley liked Japanese culture. He had a Zen garden in his office. It relaxed him to play around with it. His coworkers had lots of questions about it.
text_b_pos: He never gave them any answers.
text_b_neg: They were wrong.

text_a: Bob was playing darts with his friends. When it was his turn, he accidentally hit his friend with a dart. The dart landed directly into his friend's arm. Bob carefully pulled out the dart afterwards.
text_b_pos: Bob's friend wanted to keep playing darts.
text_b_neg: Bob's friend started bleeding from the wound.

text_a: Eric loved warm days. He loved to swim on warm days. He lived in an area that was usually warm. As a result he could swim a lot.
text_b_pos: This made him happy.
text_b_neg: He loved the snow.

text_a: It was a warm day and the gas was cheap. I decided to drive around with the top down. The sun's warmth caressed my face as wind swept over my head. It was pleasant and calming.
text_b_pos: I felt diappointed with the whether that day.
text_b_neg: I enjoyed the whether that day.

text_a: The cat walked into the living room. There was a ball on the floor. The cat swatted the ball around. The cat played with the ball.
text_b_pos: The ball flew into the vase behind the sofa and broke it.
text_b_neg: The ball landed in the goal.

text_a: A band was playing bluegrass music at brunch yesterday. The band was very good. I assumed the banjo player was an American. It turned out she was from New Zealand.
text_b_pos: What really stroke me was his New Zealander accent.
text_b_neg: It turns out he was married to one of my cousins and I had no idea.

text_a: The snow had begun falling. Winter had finally arrived in the sleepy town. A layer of fine snow covered the roads and sidewalks. It felt cozy and like home to everyone.
text_b_pos: Except for Benny, Benny hated snow.
text_b_neg: The summer was great.

text_a: Chad wanted to get a haircut. He went to the local barbershop. He wanted a specific hair style and he told it to the barber. The barber then cut all of his hair off.
text_b_pos: Chad thanked the barber for a job well done.
text_b_neg: Chad was furious and demanded compensation.

text_a: A single woman dreamed of one day having a husband. So the single woman put an ad on Craigslist seeking a relationship. The single woman got an email message from a young man. The young man sent a picture that she found attractive.
text_b_pos: The women was marrying her best friend from the neighbourhood.
text_b_neg: So the women decided to met the man in person and things worked out perfectly.

text_a: Jane had problems remembering things. One day, she was drifting off to sleep. Suddenly, a memory popped into her head. She remembered something important from her childhood!
text_b_pos: After that, she ate breakfast
text_b_neg: She immediately wrote it down.

text_a: The other day I went for a walk in the woods. I came across a bush full of berries. The berries looked tasty so I picked them. I took them back to my place to eat them.
text_b_pos: I should have checked whether they're poisonous before taking them.
text_b_neg: I decided I wasn't hungry for berries.

text_a: Tara's dog had fleas. She tried to give the dog a flea bath. The flea bath did not help Tara's dog. Tara took the dog to the vet for flea medicine.
text_b_pos: Tara's dog doesn't have fleas anymore.
text_b_neg: But the dog did not make it.

text_a: Diane's family didn't have a lot of money. When she was 10 Year's old, she was allowed to pick one dress. She went to the store and looked at everything they had. She fell in love with a bright red, polka dot dress.
text_b_pos: Her parents bought her the dress.
text_b_neg: She refused to spend so much money on the dress.

text_a: Robert walked outside. The sun was far too bright. He went back inside to get sunglasses. When he walked outside again, the sky was cloudy.
text_b_pos: Robert went back again, put his sunglasses down, and got his umbrella.
text_b_neg: Robert was planning on a hiking with his friends.

text_a: Mindy didn't like her work at all. She was grumpy when she woke up, at work and back home at night. She decided it was time to change her life. She decided to move to a new city.
text_b_pos: She did not want a new job..
text_b_neg: She applied for a new Job on the other side of the country.

text_a: A new movie theater was built in Waikiki. It was large and much nicer than the original theater. The seats were leather and they reclined. The popcorn butter was organic.
text_b_pos: People form all Honolulu went to the cinema.
text_b_neg: All Hawaiians hated the cinema.

text_a: Clyde is tired of his new neighbors. All they do is make a ton of noise. One night while trying to sleep he hears a noise. He hears the sound of loud music being played next door.
text_b_pos: He asked them to turn it down.
text_b_neg: He joined their party and stayed up all night.

text_a: Cindy wanted a new dress. She did not have enough money to buy one. She decided to get a job and save up. She worked a job after school and finally had enough.
text_b_pos: Cindy decided to spend the money on something else.
text_b_neg: Cindy was able to buy the new dress she wanted.

text_a: Dan was at a fast food joint. He ordered food for him and his date. Once he got it he noticed it wasn't what he wanted. He went back to complain.
text_b_pos: He was able to get a new bed.
text_b_neg: His date did not like that and they did not meet again.

text_a: One summer at our pool party, my mom was caught off guard. She had seen her oldest son go diving off the diving board. He was almost forty years old, and she forgot he could dive. Everyone in the family harassed him after that too.
text_b_pos: He promised to not go diving anymore.
text_b_neg: He became a life guard.

text_a: Arsenal was Greg's favorite football team. They were not playing very well in the season. Greg did not want to watch any more games. However he wanted to support his team.
text_b_pos: Greg bought tickets to Australia.
text_b_neg: Greg felt deeply disappointed.

text_a: Zoe learns that her favorite band will be playing in town next week. She decides to buy a ticket. Zoe takes the long subway ride to the concert stadium. The show is amazing!
text_b_pos: Zoe started studying.
text_b_neg: Zoe never forgot that day.

text_a: Will had a recurring dream about being trapped in a cellar. After several times of dreaming this, Will thought he needed help. Will talked with a psychologist, telling him about the dream. Will was relieved to hear the doctor's response.
text_b_pos: He said that Will would die.
text_b_neg: He said that nightmares are normal and there is nothing wrong.

text_a: The rain cause the boy to run inside from playing in the yard. He took with him his ball. The boy continued to play with the ball inside. He bounced it off a wall and tried to catch it.
text_b_pos: Unfortunately, the ball smashed a vase off the table.
text_b_neg: His mother was happy with his work.

text_a: Chad was responsible for organizing the school fete. Chad wanted the fete to have face painting and games. In addition, Chad wanted to sell various foods at the fete. Chad also wanted to have a live concert at the fete as well.
text_b_pos: Chad really wanted the fete to go well.
text_b_neg: Chad did not want it to rain.

text_a: When Emily's friend ask her to go biking she thought it would be fun. Little did she know that her friend biked all the time. Emily only rode her bike once every few weeks. She didn't realize her friend meant a ten mile ride.
text_b_pos: Emily never rides with them again.
text_b_neg: Emily is a bike mechanic.

text_a: Leroy had been a bartender at the bar for a while. He had been debating on leaving the job to find better pay. He went into work that week on his normal shift. Strangely, the manager was there waiting for him.
text_b_pos: The manager wanted to have a whisky with him.
text_b_neg: The manager wanted to talk to him about a pay rise.

text_a: Tina never wore high heels. She was going to a big dance. Tina decided to wear heels for the first time. Within the first hour her feet were killing her.
text_b_pos: Tina tried to ignore the pain but was not successful.
text_b_neg: Tina felt great in her beautiful shoes.

text_a: Julie decided to have some fun with her game show app. She opened it up and started playing. To her delight she was winning. By the end of the game she made ten thousand in coins.
text_b_pos: She decided to play a higher level.
text_b_neg: She went swimming.

text_a: Tom was sleeping in on a weekend. All of a sudden someone walked into his apartment. Tom freaked out a bit. The intruder told him he was there to change the air filter.
text_b_pos: Tom called the police and reported the man.
text_b_neg: He relaxed and made some coffee.

text_a: Sylvie had spent a lot of the summer at her grandpa's farm. She loved to play with the chickens. One day she got lice from them. Her parents could not get the lice out of her hair.
text_b_pos: They gave up to get the lice out of her hair.
text_b_neg: They took her to the hospital.

text_a: Ben went to the printing station today. He was using the computer without printing anything. The cashier told him to get out since he was idling. Ben told her to be quiet.
text_b_pos: They had a nice chat.
text_b_neg: The cashier called security.

text_a: Once a little girl planted a seed. She watered it every day. She often wondered when the seed would sprout. Every day, she would sit in the garden and watch the hours pass by.
text_b_pos: One day the seed became a beautiful flower.
text_b_neg: The little girl liked fantasy movies.

text_a: Michelle loved dressing up like a ballerina. But her dog loved playing with Michelle's tutus. So Michelle's mom bought a new tutu. Michelle gave her old tutu to the dog.
text_b_pos: Now Michelle and her dog are both happy.
text_b_neg: She hated dressing up like a ballerina.

text_a: Anna's friend made her a friendship bracelet. Anna tied it on her wrist happily. But a week later, she noticed it was missing! Anna told her friend what had happened.
text_b_pos: Her friend invited her for dinner and congratulated her.
text_b_neg: Her friend said it wasn't a big deal and made her a new one.

text_a: Terry was substitute teaching at school. The teacher had left him no instructions. He told the children to color in their coloring books. The children enjoyed having Terry as a sub.
text_b_pos: Terry never liked the school when he was young.
text_b_neg: Everything went fine in the end for Terry.

text_a: I went to the cell phone store where the line was outrageous. The greeter told me it'd be a 2 hour wait which was crazy! Eventually I waited 30 minutes before a manager came out. The manager said that he would be giving everyone a $100 credit.
text_b_pos: The manager's words soothed people's anger about waiting.
text_b_neg: The manager closed the store.

text_a: Jane had a science project due. But the thought of attempting it stressed her out. She tried to ignore the project. But as the due date approached, she felt more and more anxious.
text_b_pos: Jane decided to calm down and start it before it was too late.
text_b_neg: Jane never felt more calmed that during those days.

text_a: John went to the bookstore. He looked up and down the aisles for an interesting read. After an hour of browsing he stopped in the classics. He picked up a book of Edgar Allan Poe's work.
text_b_pos: He decided to steal it.
text_b_neg: He decided to buy it.

text_a: The clouds started to become dark outside. I thought of walking near to the bus stop, but I stayed in my class. An hour later, rain appeared. Since I didn't want to be late to my bus, I ran outside.
text_b_pos: When I ran outside the sun was shining.
text_b_neg: When I arrived home I was totally soacked.

text_a: I went to my mom's house for Christmas. The whole family was there. We decided we needed to get together more often. So, we made a date to meet up.
text_b_pos: I went to my mom's house for Thanksgiving.
text_b_neg: We had a nice dinner together and planned to meet up every other week.

text_a: Sam was attempting to study at his apartment. His roommate was being way too loud. Sam decided to move to a quieter environment. He drove a few minutes to the coffee shop.
text_b_pos: The coffee shop was closed so he ended up going to the library.
text_b_neg: Sam decided not to study.

text_a: I was playing music in my apartment. The neighbors came and said there was too much noise. Slighted, I turned the music up louder. They called the police.
text_b_pos: The police gave me a fine.
text_b_neg: The police arrested them.

text_a: It was Hank's day off. He took a relaxing stroll to the beach. While there, he took pictures of the waves on the shore. He even got a photo of a passing boat.
text_b_pos: He enjoyed his day at the beach.
text_b_neg: He was exhausted at the end of the day.

text_a: A man robbed Josh's house. Josh decided to put cameras in his house. Later, the man tried to rob Josh's house again. Josh caught the man on camera.
text_b_pos: We went to the police to get the man arrested.
text_b_neg: He decided to do nothing about it.

text_a: Mrs Allen is a new teacher. She was nervous about her first day. She came in the class and said hello to all of the students. Everything went smoothly.
text_b_pos: Mrs Allen was glad her first day went so well.
text_b_neg: When she got home, Mrs Allen started crying.

text_a: Johnson is feeling bored one day. He calls up some friends to play a game of poker. Johnson and his friends play all afternoon. They all have a great time.
text_b_pos: Until Johnson realized he had just lost his car in a bet.
text_b_neg: Everyone won.

text_a: Mike was interested in the stars and planets. His birthday was coming up. Mike's parents bought him a telescope. Mike was excited to see the gift.
text_b_pos: He never used the telescope.
text_b_neg: He could finally watch the stars.

text_a: Fred constantly worried that he had a disease. So he had various tests done on himself every week. One day, he tested positive for a certain disease. So he decided to have surgery.
text_b_pos: Fred became much more relaxed.
text_b_neg: Finally, it had been a false positive.

text_a: Elizabeth grew up on a Flower Farm along a remote area. She didn't have a whole lot of friends and was often lonely. One day she notice her grandmother chatting with the flowers. Her grandmother believed flowers can make very good friends.
text_b_pos: She started to talk to flowers as well.
text_b_neg: She found a lot of friends in the town.

text_a: Zoey was going to a party and wanted to dress nicely. She wore her nicest dress. It wasn't until later that her boyfriend mentioned how short it was. She thought about it and realized that it was.
text_b_pos: Zoey went naked to the party.
text_b_neg: So Zoey put on a longer dress.

text_a: Sam bought a used Ford for not a lot of money. He started having problems with his transmission almost immediately. Sam took the car back to the dealer to diagnose the problem. They said Ford was recalling the transmission on his model of car.
text_b_pos: Sam felt being cheated.
text_b_neg: Sam thought his car was excellent.

text_a: I was playing blackjack. I had a ten and an eight. The dealer asked me for my decision. I decided to get another card.
text_b_pos: I got an 9 and lost the game.
text_b_neg: I had a royal flush.

text_a: My new car is amazing. It has all the bells and whistles. Two days after buying someone scratched it. I was furious.
text_b_pos: I shrugged it off pretty soon after that.
text_b_neg: It cost me a small fortune to have it repainted.

text_a: Mira loved to try new foods. Mira wanted to eat a new restaurant near her. Unfortunately, she was very busy at work. On the weekend she was finally able to go to the restaurant.
text_b_pos: The new restaurant was fantastic.
text_b_neg: The restaurant was closed on the weekend.

text_a: Adam's mom and dad worked until 5 every afternoon. Adam had to come home from school and let himself in. But in two months he lost his key four times! Finally his parents grew fed up with Adam's carelessness.
text_b_pos: Adam never lost a key anyway.
text_b_neg: And they started hiding a key right next to the door.

text_a: Last weekend I grabbed my surfboard and went down to the beach. It was really cold out so I had to wear my wetsuit. When I got into the water I realized that it was warmer than the air. I waited a long time for the perfect wave.
text_b_pos: I decided to sit on the beach for the rest of the day.
text_b_neg: I spent the whole day surfing as I wasn't cold after all.

text_a: John was a deep sleeper. He sometimes had nightmares. He had one particularly bad one. It threw him off the bed.
text_b_pos: He woke up completely disoriented.
text_b_neg: He continued to sleep peacefully.

text_a: Kim was preparing to go to a gala that night. She had the choice of two dresses and couldn't choose. She picked one at random and put it on. When she arrived at the gala, the host was wearing the same dress.
text_b_pos: So Kim went home again.
text_b_neg: Kim doesn't enjoy parties any more.

text_a: Daniel sent me a lot of work. I woke up in the morning and found a new load. He said he needed it done asap. I told him I would start immediately.
text_b_pos: Daniel is my boss.
text_b_neg: I don't have any work.

text_a: Erik wanted a pet. His parents decided he could have a fish. He was so happy. He reached in the tank to pet his new friend.
text_b_pos: The fish was scared of him.
text_b_neg: Erik doesn't like fish.

text_a: I had been alone in South Africa for a while and was lonely. I was excited to learn that some friends were having a celebration. It was for New Year's and the party was full of young people. That night I met some friends that I really liked.
text_b_pos: One of them became my best friend.
text_b_neg: They were all stupid.

text_a: Eric was a scientist. He tried to find cures for diseases. He worked for hours and finally found something. Eric had found a cure for cancer!
text_b_pos: Eric decided to switch careers.
text_b_neg: All those hours invested had been worth it.

text_a: Matt hated wearing glasses. He decided to try laser vision surgery even though he was nervous. He made the appointment and followed through despite his fear. The surgeon assured him it wouldn't hurt.
text_b_pos: Matt enjoys wearing glasses now.
text_b_neg: He didn't feel a thing.

text_a: Doug entered the lunchroom and looked for his friends. He spotted them and walked to their table. Doug sat at the table, greeting his friends. Todd came to the table and tried to shove Doug from the table.
text_b_pos: Doug was very upset.
text_b_neg: Todd and Doug are best friends.

text_a: Lulu wanted to take her friends on vacation with her to Amsterdam. She wanted to show them where she grew up. As the girls arrived in the city they were in awe. They thought it was great where she grew up.
text_b_pos: They decided to buy a house there.
text_b_neg: Lulu showed them the house she was born in.

text_a: In the 5th grade I wanted to be in band. The instruments were too expensive for my family. The bells were provided by the school. I studied and practiced for hours preparing for the concert.
text_b_pos: I decided music wasn't for me after all.
text_b_neg: Being part of the band was a valuable experience.

text_a: Rudy was 11 and wanted an allowance, since all his friends got one. His parents suspiciously asked what these friends did for their money. Rudy admitted that they did chores, like trash emptying & lawn-mowing. His parents talked it over and agreed to give Rudy an allowance.
text_b_pos: Rudy was excited about her parents' decision.
text_b_neg: Rudy didn't want the allowance.

text_a: June and her toddler daughter were in the kitchen for breakfast. A large mouse strolled across the kitchen floor. June screamed and threw her spoon at the mouse. She took her daughter and ran from the house.
text_b_pos: She invited friends to her house to party.
text_b_neg: She called her husband to check whether the mouse was gone.

text_a: Tia planted flowers in her garden and tended them often. One hot day, she donned gloves and a sun hat before working. But when she got inside later, she was shocked. Her arms and neck were bright red with sunburn!
text_b_pos: She was pleased with her tan.
text_b_neg: She regretted not having applied sunscreen.

text_a: Lisa was passionate about politics. she was encouraged by a friend to run for local office. She worked hard on her campaign. Lisa was always honest with her voters.
text_b_pos: Nonetheless, she got a small percentage of votes.
text_b_neg: She did not put a lot of effort in the campaign preparation.

text_a: Corey feels very heartbroken today. In an effort to feel better, he built a blanket fort. He had to gather all of the blankets in his house. Corey does not regret his decision.
text_b_pos: He felt much better afterwards.
text_b_neg: He felt much worse afterwards.

text_a: Our family had a collection of Beanie Babies. A friend was supposed to sell a few of them at a yard sale. My brother in particular had several of them. One of his sold for twenty dollars!
text_b_pos: My brother was angry about that.
text_b_neg: My brother was pleased about that.

text_a: Jennifer wanted to get a good job. She applied to a well known college. She went to school for four years. When she graduated she applied for a job.
text_b_pos: And she got a offer.
text_b_neg: She wanted to be a student one more time.

text_a: Jennifer decided to grill some corn one day. She went outside and preheated her grill. She peeled back the corn husks and removed silk. She then wrapped each ear of corn in aluminum foil.
text_b_pos: She placed the wrapped corn on the grill and was soon enjoying grilled corn.
text_b_neg: She turned off the grill and threw the corn in the bin.

text_a: Angela dated a guy in high school that she loved. They broke up before college and didn't talk again. One day they ran into each other on the street. They talked and decided to have lunch.
text_b_pos: They got back together.
text_b_neg: Angela likes to sing.

text_a: Jo smelled something horrible in her house. She searched everywhere for the source. She couldn't figure out what it was. She finally checked her brother's gym bag.
text_b_pos: She found out it was his brother's unwashed socks.
text_b_neg: Her brother left his cell phone in the gym bag.

text_a: Claudia was a big fan of photography. She bought an old camera from a charity shop to add to her collection. The camera was old enough that she couldn't source the right film. It collected dust on her shelf for 7 years.
text_b_pos: Then she sold it to a charity shop.
text_b_neg: She took beautiful pictures with the camera.

text_a: Ben went swimming in the quarry. He had a great time, but when he got out, he spotted something. Attached to his leg was a huge leech! Ben shrieked and panicked.
text_b_pos: He was scared, but the took off the leek.
text_b_neg: He continued to walk as if nothing happened.

text_a: Paul woke up very late. And he realized his alarm clock wasn't working. There was no power in his house. And he was 3 hours late for work.
text_b_pos: His boss raised his salary for being late.
text_b_neg: His boss was very upset.

text_a: Since we travel on business, we stay in the same hotel for months. We had the sweetest housekeeper who did a great job for us. One day, my husband saw her and she looked sad. Three weeks before Christmas, she told me that she had been fired.
text_b_pos: We tried to talk to her employee to give the job back.
text_b_neg: We were happy that she got fired.

text_a: Sarah makes the best chicken and broccoli casserole. All her friends love it. This time she tried something different. When she took it for potluck, no one ate it.
text_b_pos: The next time she made chicken and broccoli casserole again.
text_b_neg: Her friends hate potluck.

text_a: My credit card kept getting declined. I had no idea what that was happening. So I called up the credit card company. I found out that the card had been hacked.
text_b_pos: The credit card company sent me a new credit card.
text_b_neg: I used my credit card to buy oranges.

text_a: Sara's favorite band was playing in town. She didn't plan on going but last minute she was invited. She asked her parents and they bought her a ticket. Once she was there, she stood alone and watched the show.
text_b_pos: She blamed her parents for the failures in her life.
text_b_neg: It stirred up memories from the past.

text_a: Larry was tired after a long week of work. On Saturday he was happy to stay home all day. He ordered in a pizza. Then he rented a movie through the television.
text_b_pos: He felt refreshed after the relaxing weekend.
text_b_neg: He went out to hike with some friends.

text_a: Lou owned a pawn shop. A gentleman came in with several electronic devices. Lou was suspicious about the amount of devices the man had. Lou stalled the man while he notified the police.
text_b_pos: The police arrested Lou.
text_b_neg: The police arrested the man for stealing the electronic devices.

text_a: Tom had the flu. He accidentally gave it to his brother. His brother gave it to his teacher. His teacher got sick and lost his voice.
text_b_pos: The teacher retired from his job.
text_b_neg: The teacher gave the flu to his family.

text_a: Rick didn't like wasting gas driving to nearby places. So he bought a bicycle. He used his city's bike path. And he enjoyed beating traffic.
text_b_pos: Rick decided cycling was better than driving.
text_b_neg: Rick decided never to cycle again.

text_a: The bus dropped several kids off of the bus stop. Jen got out and spent five minutes walking home. She became nervous since she couldn't find her house keys. Since none of her family were home, she sat down and waited for them.
text_b_pos: She was relieved when her brother came home from school early.
text_b_neg: Jen played a game of cards.

text_a: Jane was out dancing with friends. She really got into it. During one song she tried to drop it low. Jane wound up tearing her jeans.
text_b_pos: Jane had to buy a new shirt the next day.
text_b_neg: Jane only wore dresses to clubs from then on.

text_a: Bob invited his friends over to his house in the country. Together they combed the forest, gathering wood. Then they massed all their sticks into a big pile. Bob lit in on fire.
text_b_pos: Bob put out the fire immediately.

text_a: The mayor wanted the town to decide how to use the warehouse. One person suggested that it be used as a communal studio space. The mayor agreed. He used the building himself to practice singing.
text_b_pos: Because he was the front man of Metallica.
text_b_neg: Because he saw the chance to practice with his band there now.

text_a: Milton is getting so hungry. He has been working on power lines all day. He decides to head to Burger King. He orders 2 Whopper sandwiches.
text_b_pos: He wolfs down the sandwiches in three minutes.
text_b_neg: He throws the sandwiches in the bin.

text_a: Olivia really loved going to the movies. She tried to go at least once a week. This week nobody wanted to go with her. She decided to go alone.
text_b_pos: Olivia's husband told her this was a bad habit.
text_b_neg: At the movies she met a friend from work.

text_a: My house had a fruit fly problem that I didn't know how to so. No matter what steps I took to eliminate them, they always came back. I finally decided to clean the entire house, top to bottom. I finally found the source of the fruit flies deep in a cabinet.
text_b_pos: I missed flies.
text_b_neg: I sovled the fly problem after that.

text_a: Gina met her friend Pam at the park. They walked and talked about Pam's school friends. Gina knew she had to get back home to work on a report. But she was having a good time hanging out with Pam.
text_b_pos: She decided to do her work late at night.
text_b_neg: She decided she didn't need to work.

text_a: The grandma made a hot tea on the stove. She fixed the table She called her daughter down the stairs. They had tea.
text_b_pos: Her daughter thanked grandma for the tea.
text_b_neg: Her daughter cried because she did not want to drink it.

text_a: Martha had always wanted to make wine. Having retired from her day job, she planned to do so. Martha purchased a small plot of land to grow grapes. Soon, she had enough to begin experimenting.
text_b_pos: She bought the land from a friend's dad.
text_b_neg: The first bottle of wine she produced was not good.

text_a: Ripley loved dinosaurs. He constantly mentioned facts about them to everyone he encountered. We decided to surprise him with a trip to the science museum. They had a sand pit for children to pretend to be archeologists.
text_b_pos: Ripley pretended to find dinosaurs in the sand.
text_b_neg: Ripley wanted to see the space exhibit.

text_a: Jim really wanted to camp on the island. After pleading for weeks he finally convinced his mom. While on the island he heard a very strange noise. He got in his canoe and paddled to shore as fast as he could.
text_b_pos: Jim never went back to that island again.
text_b_neg: Jim was not scared at all.

text_a: I knew a man who was good at chess. He would play at the park every day. I watched him play another guy. They both looked very focus.
text_b_pos: After some minutes, they decided to cancel the game.
text_b_neg: The game took long but in the end, the other guy lost.

text_a: Dana had a book report due. She didn't like to read. She tried to watch a movie that was based on the book. The movie was only loosely based on the book.
text_b_pos: She got an F.
text_b_neg: She failed the subject.

text_a: David wanted to save money on food. So he decided to live off of oatmeal. One week, it was very hot however. But he was determined to save money.
text_b_pos: He bought the most expensive ice cream he could find.
text_b_neg: So he continued eating oatmeal.

text_a: Rita's husband Mike wanted to get a puppy for their son, Jim. Rita was hesitant. She didn't think Jim could take care of a puppy. Mike agreed to help take care of the puppy.
text_b_pos: Mike bought a cat.
text_b_neg: Jim was very excited for the puppy.

text_a: Sam wanted to go to a party. Her parents wouldn't let her. She decided to go anyways. She ended up getting caught.
text_b_pos: Her parents were very happy that she went.
text_b_neg: Her parents were not happy that she went.

text_a: Kariem loved chickens and wanted to raise his own for the eggs. He ordered him some hens and rooster to get started. When the chickens grew up, he saw he had more roosters than he needed. Later that spring, several hens began to set and hatch off chicks.
text_b_pos: Kariem realized he had too many chickens.
text_b_neg: Kariem loved eating chicken.

text_a: A door burst open in a crowded room. A man stood there looking panicked. He loudly asked if there was a doctor in the room. Bob raised his hand even though he was not a doctor.
text_b_pos: Bob wanted to order a beer.
text_b_neg: Bob took his phone and called a doctor.

text_a: Ida wanted to learn German. She signed up for a class. But it turned out to be very hard! She thought about quitting, but she decided to persist.
text_b_pos: In the end it was worth it.
text_b_neg: It was really easy for her.

text_a: Xavier always wanted a horse. He found out about a auction for horses. He saw a horse that he really liked. It had had a very unhappy life.
text_b_pos: The horse made Xavier sad.
text_b_neg: Xavier wanted to give the horse a good life.

text_a: Finn's skin looked a little dull. He felt sluggish too. He had not been drinking enough water lately. Finn grabbed a glass.
text_b_pos: Finn did not like drinking plain water.
text_b_neg: Finn drank water until his thirst was gone.

text_a: A man decided to order some soccer balls. He found some at a good price, so he decided to order a lot. He settled on a gross. He didn't realize exactly how many a gross actually was.
text_b_pos: He learned that a gross was equal to twelve dozen.
text_b_neg: He received one ball.

text_a: Jane hated eating fish on Sundays. It was a family tradition. She begged her parents to change it. They decided to improvise for her sake.
text_b_pos: Jane discovered she likes Sushi.
text_b_neg: Now there's only fish for dinner on every second Sunday.

text_a: Becca was an awesome singer. She practiced since she was 6 years old. Her mom's birthday was today. She started singing her mom's favorite song at the top of her lungs.
text_b_pos: Everyone covered their ears.
text_b_neg: Her mom was amazed at Becca's voice.

text_a: Amy worked at home as a customer service representative. There was a caller who wanted a discount on her purchase. Amy offered what she could but the lady wanted more. Amy asked in the chat room for a supervisor to give more discounts.
text_b_pos: They were not able to give more discount.
text_b_neg: The supervisor wanted to kill the customer.

text_a: John was retired. He was bored. He decided to work in order to not be bored. He took a low paying, but fun job.
text_b_pos: John was the oldest employee of the company.
text_b_neg: John walked along the beach.

text_a: Marvin was excited to go to camp. It was no ordinary camp though. He was going to basketball camp for a week. He could barely sleep he was so excited.
text_b_pos: He canceled the camp because he was not able to motivate himself.
text_b_neg: He was a bit tired the first day, but the camp was a phenomenal experience.

text_a: All of Lisa's friends were on the soccer team. Lisa wanted to play on the team too. She practiced all summer. She went to tryouts in the fall.
text_b_pos: She got on the soccer team.
text_b_neg: She joined the volleyball team.

text_a: When I was a kid, my cousins and I loved fireflies. We would chase them all around my aunt's house. My aunt gave us a mason jar to keep them in. We caught 25 fireflies and put them in the jar.
text_b_pos: My aunt scolded us for catching the fireflies.
text_b_neg: We watched the fireflies in the jar all night.

text_a: I was ready for my first date with someone. I had my truck cleaned out nicely. It looked better than it ever had. It was a week before we were supposed to go out.
text_b_pos: My truck was very dirty.
text_b_neg: I felt well prepared for the date.

text_a: The boys were pumped. They were finally going to go see the band in concert. It had been advertised for a while and the day was finally here. They loaded up in the car and took off to the venue.
text_b_pos: The boys didn't like the music the band was playing.
text_b_neg: The concert was a huge success and the boys were happy.

text_a: Ally was nervous about her first dance class. Would she make friends? Would she like her teacher? That night, Ally learned about Ballet and Tap.
text_b_pos: Ballet and tap became his best friends.
text_b_neg: Ballet and tap were drug dealers.

text_a: Katherine planned her outdoor wedding for July. On the day of the wedding there were dark clouds in the sky. Katherine decided not to make any changes to the wedding. During the ceremony it started to rain very hard.
text_b_pos: Katherina was devastated about it.
text_b_neg: Katherine was glad that it went as planned.

text_a: Jan was a young high school girl. She had just had sex for the first time with her boyfriend. They didn't use protection. Jan found out she was pregnant and thought her life was over.
text_b_pos: With the help of their parents they were able to raise the child regardless.
text_b_neg: She was looking forward to being a parent.

text_a: A boy really wanted to see a new movie. He asked his mom and she said she would take him. He happily waited to go to the theatre. His mom and him grabbed snacks while they waited in line.
text_b_pos: It was the happiest day in his life yet.
text_b_neg: He started crying tears.

text_a: Jill was exercising at gym. But she quickly became tired. She decided to take a break but never returned to exercising. She hardly spent any time exercising.
text_b_pos: Jill got fat.
text_b_neg: Jill became very athletic.

text_a: We live in a condo building by a pond. The dumpsters are outdoors. One day I saw several rats by the dumpster. The property manager said they could do nothing.
text_b_pos: They said the rats were their friends.
text_b_neg: They weren't responsible for the dumpsters.

text_a: Little Jimmy had waited enough. There were still miles of kids in front of him to meet Santa. Jimmy marched forward and walked straight up to Santa. He demanded that Santa make his brother walk again.
text_b_pos: Jimmy's brother got a wheelchair for christmas.
text_b_neg: Santa gave him a red car.

text_a: When I was young there was a stray cat that was sick. I tried to save it but it died under the house. My mom called my dad to come take it out, and put it in the trash. I started crying and threw a fit and dad went to talk to mother.
text_b_pos: In the end we buried it in the garden.
text_b_neg: I decided to report my dad to the police.

text_a: The young man sat at his desk. He was incredibly bored. His phone rang and caused him to reach into his pants. His friends told him they were throwing a party tonight.
text_b_pos: Suddenly they got his attention.
text_b_neg: He needed help with his homework.

text_a: Cleaning out a deceased relative's attic, Ana found an old gold watch. The relative was distant and Ana did not know her well. Therefore, she felt okay about selling the watch. She took it to a jeweler, who appraised it at $9000!
text_b_pos: Ana changed her mind and returned it back to its previous owner.
text_b_neg: Ana proceeded with the sale and paid some debts with that money.

text_a: John was looking forward to a new thriller. He didn't get the chance to watch it opening weekend. While browsing facebook someone talked about it. They spoiled the ending and gave the plot-twist away.
text_b_pos: Now the movie was ruined for John.
text_b_neg: John wanted to see the movie even more now!

text_a: Cris is assigned a project due in a month. He procrastinates until the last minute before starting his project. He calls a good friend over to help him finish his project. They stay up through the night and barely finish on time.
text_b_pos: Cris submitted his assignment on time.
text_b_neg: The friend killed Cris.

text_a: Several females were walking around campus. They handed free candy to everyone. Although it seemed suspicious, many people accepted the treats. However, there was a large outbreak of diseases during the next day.
text_b_pos: The females were sought by the police but not found.
text_b_neg: People were looking for more candy on the campus.

text_a: Monday was making fudge with her mom. It was the holidays, the perfect time for fudge. She was stirring and stirring the hot fudge. She then slipped and threw the pan of hot fudge into the air.
text_b_pos: Her mom liked the fudge.
text_b_neg: She made a mess all around the kitchen.

text_a: Nathan arrived with a cooler of drinks. He was walking towards the food. However, he tripped on all of the food. The potato salad and lasagna landed on the ground.
text_b_pos: Nathan began to clean up the mess.
text_b_neg: But he didn't care, because he was too tired.

text_a: Cindy wanted new shoes. Her mom had just bought her a pair. Cindy knew she did not need to ask for more money. She decided to get a job and save.
text_b_pos: Cindy saved enough money to buy the chose.
text_b_neg: Cindy's mum bought her clothes.

text_a: Ted was a young man who loved cartoons. He would watch them all day long. His parents wanted him to go outside to play and be active. Ted told them no because he was watching cartoons.
text_b_pos: The parents punished Ted.
text_b_neg: Ted's parents gave him sweets.

text_a: Tayler had been out at sea for two weeks now. He loved being a sailor but was still scared of the open sea. One night it was particularly windy. The ship took a beating but held up.
text_b_pos: He never returned.
text_b_neg: He arrived safely to the port.

text_a: Ken planned a picnic date. He got everything together and picked a perfect spot. Once there it started to rain immediately. Ken had to pack everything up and leave.
text_b_pos: They had an awesome day by the lake.
text_b_neg: The date never happened.

text_a: Sally was making biscuits early in the morning. She ending up making 3 dozen for a meal later in the day. She sat them down on the table to cool. She went away for a bit.
text_b_pos: Sally does not like sweets.
text_b_neg: All the biscuits were gone.

text_b_pos: Jeff had to pack enough food for two weeks.
text_b_neg: Jeff didn't want it to take too long because he did not like going outside.

text_b_pos: Mary only moved again when she could not see the mountain lion.
text_b_neg: Mary jumped at the mountain lion.

text_a: The man stored emergency supplies in his cellar. There was never an emergency. The supplies deteriorated. The next owner found them.
text_b_pos: He threw all supplies away.

text_a: Tim lost his lighter. He thought a friend took it. Tim confronted the friend about it. The friend found it in his pocket and apologized.
text_b_pos: Tim accepted the apology.

text_a: Corey wanted to learn to skate so his dad got him a skateboard. Corey put on his knee pads and practiced everyday. It wasn't long before people started to gather around to watch him. Soon a Corey got sponsored by the local skate shop.
text_b_pos: Corey realized he didn't like the skateboard.
text_b_neg: His dad was very proud on Corey.

text_a: Joe grew up on an animal farm. There was a particular chick to which Joe felt attached. Joe watched the chick hatch and held it as a newborn. One evening Joe had a wonderful chicken dinner made by his mom.
text_b_pos: He was afraid she had slaughtered his special chicken.
text_b_neg: Joe didn't like fries as a side dish.

text_b_pos: Ellis eventually still became fond of the dog.
text_b_neg: Ellis is afraid of dogs.

text_a: I got a letter in the mail. It was from the government. They said I had to go to jury duty. I decided to not go.
text_b_pos: So the police had to come and get me.
text_b_neg: This was totally legal to do.

text_a: Ryan hiked to school in the snow. It snowed so much recess was cancelled. The school closed early because there was too much snow. Ryan took the bus back home.
text_b_pos: Luckily it wasn't as hot in the bus as it was outside.

text_a: Jake and Cindy decided to break up. It was on okay terms but they still lived together. They decided to wait until the lease was over. Unfortunately it was too uncomfortable.
text_b_pos: Cindy moved out and got her own appartment
text_b_neg: Jake and Cindy met every night to play cards.

text_a: Robbie was initially thought to be an odd Boy Scout. On one camping trip, a steak went missing from the cooler. The steak was eventually found in Robbie's sleeping bag. Robbie explained that he was very hungry, having no food at home.

text_b_neg: Nobody was angry at Robbie as it was only one steak  but they told him to aks the next time.

text_b_pos: Ned is a chemist.

text_a: Jim was almost 1 year old, but he couldn't walk. His aunt Kay would practice with him everyday. One day Kay stood him up, let him go, and called to him. Jim nervously took three steps, then walked to her.

text_b_neg: She tore the pages apart.

text_a: My daughter wants to buy a big screen tv for her husband. Their tv has a dark stain on the screen. We offered to help with the purchase. She hesitated because the tv is $50 more than she wants to spend.

text_b_neg: We watched tv together.

text_b_pos: After a long flight he was finally home in China.
text_b_neg: Wang stayed and did not go back to China.

text_a: I was at the beach with friends. We were bored and didn't know what to do. We began collecting seashells. The seashells were really colorful and unique.
text_b_pos: I don't like unique seashells.

text_a: It was going to be one of those days. I could tell as soon as I woke up. I couldn't seem to catch anything. I sat in front of my computer feeling annoyed.

text_a: Brenda found a kitten outside of her house. So she decided to bring it inside. She couldn't find a collar or an owner. So she decided to keep it.
text_b_pos: She was unhappy that she found it.
text_b_neg: She called it Kitty.

text_a: Julie made cookies for her dad. It was a lot of work to make them from scratch. Her dad ate them all. Julie ate one and noticed something was missing.

text_b_pos: The notice was a love letter from the plumber.
text_b_neg: The plumber had been too early and had already left.
