text_b_pos: We had an amazing dive.
text_b_neg: We were quite disappointed.

text_a: Tom was trying to log onto his e-mail. He kept putting in the wrong password by accident. Eventually he was locked out. He decided to change the password but it needed his alternate e-mail.
text_b_pos: Tom had two email accounts.
text_b_neg: But he forgot about that password as well.

text_a: Tina's best friend had a massive dog. It would always jump up on people. When she walked in, the dog frightened her. All of the sudden she noticed blood.
text_b_pos: She enjoyed the sun.
text_b_neg: She left the home terrified.

text_a: John had a hard time at work. Everybody was always ahead of him. He brought some work at home to get ahead. But even then, it was not enough.
text_b_pos: John decided to quit his job.
text_b_neg: He became employee of the month.

text_a: Amy was in the dentist chair. He was preparing to do an emergency extraction. He walked towards her with a needle. She was afraid of needles, so she closed her eyes.
text_b_pos: The shot was just a little prick.
text_b_neg: Amy decided not to get the shot.

text_a: Tim wanted to go on an adventure. He went cave diving with friends. It was his first time. He wasn't prepared for how hard it would be.
text_b_pos: He enjoyed how easy it has been for him.
text_b_neg: He had sore muscles in the evening.

text_a: Jane couldn't afford new clothes. She started dating an older guy with money. Jane was offered all new wardrobe. Jane reluctantly agreed to the offer.
text_b_pos: She felt felt embarrassed afterwards.
text_b_neg: She felt happy she had new clothes.

text_a: I went on the splash mountain ride last week. At first it was a peaceful ride. We went into a calm tunnel. Then we dropped unexpectedly.
text_b_pos: It was a smooth ride.
text_b_neg: It gave us a proper scare.

text_a: Kate was at the museum alone. As a kid she always loved to see the fossils. It was her first stop today. There was none of the expected awe she had as a child.
text_b_pos: She hated being a child.
text_b_neg: She realized that she had changed.

text_a: I went to a movie about global warming last night. It made me think about a lot of things. I had a big discussion with my friends. We decided to do more to help.
text_b_pos: We started creating a flyer which we would distribute in the neighborhood.
text_b_neg: I quit my job to collect contributions for the issue.

text_a: When it snows, Fred goes to his shed to get a shovel. He first shovels his own driveway and then walks the neighborhood. He offers his help to anyone who wants it. Fred spends all day shoveling our driveways.
text_b_pos: He is the hero we need.
text_b_neg: He is the hero we deserve.

text_a: Bill was very interested in runes. He bought a book and studied very hard. Bill became an expert on runes with many years of practice. Now archaeologists pay him for his help with identifying symbols.
text_b_pos: Bill is happy.
text_b_neg: Bill quits his job to become a exotic dancer.

text_a: Jade was getting ready to go to work. She checked her purse one last time for everything. She had her phone, wallet and some snacks for work. Walking out of the door, she locked it and began walking away.
text_b_pos: Then she realized that she had forgotten her car keys.
text_b_neg: Then she realized that she had forgotten her phone.

text_a: Dustin bought some groceries. He brought them home and put them inside. First he put away all of the fridge items. Next, he put away the frozen food.
text_b_pos: He took food from the fridge and put it outside.
text_b_neg: He than started to cook dinner.

text_a: Kelsey was about to file her taxes. She was nervous because she was sure she owed a ton of money. She went through the tax process, waiting for the blow to hit. Suddenly, she realized that she didn't owe any money.
text_b_pos: Kelsey then went to the ATM to withdraw money to pay her taxes.
text_b_neg: Kelsey was relieved that she had no to pay taxes.

text_a: Bill was excited for Easter Sunday. He decided he wanted to bake a ham for his family. Bill headed off to the grocery store. He bought the biggest ham he could find.
text_b_pos: But the ham is too big to fit into the oven.
text_b_neg: Easter Sunday was Bill's favorite holiday.

text_a: John hates travelling for his job. He likes his job just not the travelling. His wife also hates the travelling. They have twins on the way so quitting is no option.
text_b_pos: John finally quit his job.
text_b_neg: John enjoyed travelling for his job.

text_a: Tom hadn't received any email from work. It had been a few days. He decided to check his spam folder. It was all in there.
text_b_pos: He changed his Spam filters.
text_b_neg: Tom is still looking for a job.

text_a: Adam angered a classmate one day. He accidentally pushed the classmate in the hall. The girl, angry, challenged him to a fight. Ben agreed to meet her in the yard after classes.
text_b_pos: Ben liked his new classmate.
text_b_neg: He was beaten up by the girl.

text_a: Kane bought his lottery ticket that week just like always. He always played the same numbers, his lucky numbers he called them. The week of the drawing came and he paid attention with half interest. He vaguely heard a few of his numbers being called.
text_b_pos: He hated the lottery.
text_b_neg: It turned out that he won.

text_a: Sue entered a nacho eating contest. Nachos are her favorite food so she thought she could do well. Sue started off slow to pace herself. She then upped the ante.
text_b_pos: She was still hungry after the contest.

text_a: Kerry had a party to attend. She was so worried about what she would wear. She went to her favorite boutique and looked around. After some time, she found a lovely dress.
text_b_pos: She didn't like the dress at all.
text_b_neg: Unfortunately, the dress was too expensive.

text_a: The Chinese observe Ching Ming every year. They visit the graves of family members and burn paper money. I found a red receptacle for the money in a Chinese supermarket. Normally one threw the receptacle away, for superstitious reasons.
text_b_pos: I decided to never visit china again.
text_b_neg: I decided to keep it as a jewellery box.

text_a: The friends gathered for a party to celebrate the New Year. One friend brought a very expensive bottle of champagne. He opened it exactly as the new year began. The cork from the bottle shot off and hit the host in her left breast.
text_b_pos: They quickly washed her clothes.
text_b_neg: The bottle broke.

text_a: Albert had watched karate related shows on tv for years. One day Albert decided to take karate classes. Albert took his courses and practiced every day. Albert started getting the hang of karate.
text_b_pos: After five years Albert achieved the black belt in karate.
text_b_neg: Albert hated karate.

text_a: Ang was looking for a wedding dress. But all the nice ones were so expensive! She really could not afford them. Then she tried on her mother's old wedding dress.
text_b_pos: She loved them.
text_b_neg: Ang couldn't afford this dress either.

text_a: Amanda liked watched nature shows with snakes on TV. She was excited, then, to one day find a snake in her own back yard! Unfortunately, when she tried to pick it up, it bit her. Her mother had to take her to the doctor to make sure she was okay.
text_b_pos: She became the Queen of Blades.
text_b_neg: She was admitted to a psychiatric institution and became a cat lady.

text_a: Diana needed a bus ticket to get home. But she had lost her wallet. She was worried because this was the last bus. But a nice stranger heard her plight.
text_b_pos: And laughed at Diana's disadventure.

text_a: Alice's electric nail file stopped working in the middle of a service. There was not a store where she lived to buy a new nail file. She drove 200 miles to the nearest store and bought a new one. When she got home the new file didn't work so she had to go back.
text_b_pos: She was very frustrated.
text_b_neg: Her problem was finally solved.

text_a: Tommy fell after Ren crossed him in basketball. Although he was embarrassed, he was also mad. When Ren had possession of the ball, he ran into her. She fell on her hip and injured it.

text_a: Today was Frank's day off. Rather than being excited, he felt quite bored. Rather than staying at home, he decided to take a walk. He walked down the sidewalk and saw a beautiful red bird fly overhead.
text_b_pos: Frank was disappointed and went home again.
text_b_neg: He was happy he had decided to go out after all.

text_a: Penny went fishing with her family. They drove to a creek that was up on a mountain. Penny got her fishing pole and some bait. She found a spot where she could see the fish in the water.
text_b_pos: She downed there.
text_b_neg: She fished for the whole family.

text_a: I was driving home when a big storm hit. The snow was intense and blinding. I had to pull over to the side of the road to be safe. It didn't stop for hours.
text_b_pos: If only there was a girl to comfort me.
text_b_neg: It felt like an eternity passed  and I was alone in my car.

text_a: I watched the olympics on television yesterday. There are some very talented people. I watched the men's gymnastics tournament. I could not believe how flexible they are.
text_b_pos: They were not impressive at all.
text_b_neg: They could also do some pretty impressive tricks.

text_a: Before Hank goes grocery shopping, he makes sure to write a list. One time Hank went grocery shopping without a list. He bought lots of groceries and extra food too! When he got home, he realized that he didn't buy everything he needed.
text_b_pos: He had to go back to school to pick up the rest.
text_b_neg: He had to go back to the grocery shop to pick up the rest.

text_a: My sister in law came by last Monday. I listed some items to sell for her on ebay. She said she also had hermits for me. When she came by, she said she forgot the hermits.
text_b_pos: She bought them on ebay.
text_b_neg: I was angry as I really wanted them.

text_a: Gina was on the playground by herself. She didn't want to seem like she cared that she was alone. She decided to walk around the perimeter of the playground. She hoped it would look like she was exercising.
text_b_pos: She liked to be alone.
text_b_neg: She felt lonely.

text_a: Mary is a writer. She self publishes her books on Amazon. She sells a lot of ebooks. She makes a lot of money.
text_b_pos: She became a garbage collector.
text_b_neg: She had her life solved.

text_a: Jane's mother gave her $20 to play at the carnival. First, Jane tried the merry-go-round, but it was too slow. Next, Jane tried the roller coaster, but it scared her too much. Jane was worried she wouldn't find anything fun to do.
text_b_pos: Her mother suggested one and she was very happy with that.
text_b_neg: She tried the merry-go-round and the roller coaster again.

text_a: Mabel was very proud of her cute lemonade stand in front of her house. She welcomed her neighbors with glee. She didn't understand why all of them only took one sip though. When she tried her lemonade, she spat it out.
text_b_pos: She realized that the lemonade was way to sour.
text_b_neg: She realized that she charged too much for her lemonade.

text_a: Kendra wanted to learn how to cook. She took a breakfast cooking class at a community college for fun. She learned how to make eggs benedict. Her hollandaise sauce was amazing!
text_b_pos: She never made breakfast again.
text_b_neg: Her husband was very happy to eat her food.

text_a: Brad approached Elena after class. He simply asked her if she's doing anything later. Her first response was that she has a boyfriend. He looked confused and just said that he wanted to study with her.
text_b_pos: She had misunderstood his intention.
text_b_neg: She decided to leave the boyfriend for him.

text_a: Sue's parrot would not stop making noise. Sue tried everything to get it to be quiet. Sue's parrot kept her up all night. Eventually it began to calm down.
text_b_pos: Sue was not able to sleep.
text_b_neg: Sue was able to sleep.

text_a: Deb loved to eat tuna salad. She bought all the ingredients so she could make it for lunch. Deb began to boil her eggs on high temperature. While they were boiling she went to shower.
text_b_pos: The water went out of the pan and all over the floor.
text_b_neg: Deb is Vegan.

text_a: Gina bought a slushie from the gas station. She stepped out of the store into the heat and took a sip. She felt the icy cold drink slide down her throat. It gave her a chill in spite of the heat.
text_b_pos: When she was done she got a second one.
text_b_neg: She never bought slushies again.

text_a: Cathy was trying to get back into exercise. Cathy saw a flyer at her gym for spin classes. Cathy decided she would try out one spin class. After trying the class, Cathy loved the excitement of the class.
text_b_pos: Cathy wanted to find an easier way to exercise.
text_b_neg: She decided to sign up for more classes.

text_a: Dan loved basketball but didn't make the team. Dan was upset but decided to try again next year. Over the next year Dan practiced and worked extra hard. Dan went and did the try outs the next year.
text_b_pos: Dan made the team and went on to become the best player.
text_b_neg: Dan decided basketball was not for him.

text_a: Jimmy was playing basketball with his friends. He felt a prick on his arm. A bee had stung him. His face started swelling up.
text_b_pos: Jimmy likes bees.
text_b_neg: Later he died.

text_a: I was travelling along the road one day alone. When it got dark I decided to make camp and rest. I rested well but was greeted by a grim sight upon waking. In the dark I had camped near a large rock which rolled onto my gear.
text_b_pos: I went to the forest and was attacked by a wolf.
text_b_neg: I had to buy new gear.

text_a: Joe had cancer. He wanted to spend some time with his son before he died. He planned a big fishing trip. Unfortunately he died before they could go.
text_b_pos: Joe likes fish for lunch.
text_b_neg: His son thinks about everytime he goes fishing.

text_a: George bought a new car. He read the owner's manual. He disagreed with the recommended tire pressure. He contacted the manufacturer.
text_b_pos: The manifuacturer was annoyed.
text_b_neg: The manifacturer gave him a new bike.

text_a: Jill had always wanted to get a tattoo. She just didn't know what she wanted. She would look books and magazines for hours and hours. One day she finally found the perfect design.
text_b_pos: She ate pizza that night.
text_b_neg: She deduced to make it.

text_a: Rory began feeling sluggish after his thirtieth birthday. It had been years since he'd played sports or worked out. He got a new job across town. To save money, he usually walked instead of taking the bus.
text_b_pos: He gained some weight.
text_b_neg: He lost some weight.

text_a: Victor went on vacation. He went on tours of old castles. He saw a large castle with an extendable drawbridge. The sight fascinated him to no end.
text_b_pos: He went back home sadly after the trip.
text_b_neg: He took a photo of the drawbridge.

text_a: Kelly wanted to go to college in another state. He parents did not think that she was mature enough to move away. They wanted Kelly to go to college at home. Kelly suggested a compromise.
text_b_pos: She suggested a college, which was  two hours away so that she could come back for weekends.
text_b_neg: She left home and never came back.

text_a: Gina was upset to see a moving truck parked at her house. She went inside, expecting to see her parents packing. She was surprised when they weren't. They weren't moving at all.
text_b_pos: She really was hoping they would finally go.
text_b_neg: Her parents were dead.

text_a: Melly was shopping for new kitchen curtains. She decided on a lace gingham pair, airy and pretty. She used them to replace her broken old blinds. Then she stepped back and smiled broadly.
text_b_pos: Melly was really upset about the final result.
text_b_neg: She couldn't be more proud of her choice.

text_a: Kate liked to draw. She would draw everyday after school. She was so good that her mother put her into an advanced art class. Kate was the best in the class.
text_b_pos: All complimented her on her writing.
text_b_neg: All complimented her on her drawings.

text_a: I just got my w2s in the mail. I'm about to start doing my taxes. I'm excited to get money back. It's frustrating and a bit annoying.
text_b_pos: So I decided to pay someone to do them for me.
text_b_neg: I cooked lamb that night.

text_a: The kids decided to have a sleepover. They played video games for six hours straight. Their eyes burned and their fingers ached. They tried to go to bed but they kept thinking about the video games.
text_b_pos: The kids were awake all night thinking about video games.
text_b_neg: The kids hated playing video games.

text_a: Bo went to his boss to ask for advice on a project. Bo's boss was too busy to help Bo at the moment. The boss suggested that he ask another supervisor. Bo said that he did not know the other supervisor.
text_b_pos: Bo's boss did the project for him.
text_b_neg: Bo's boss introduced him to another supervisor.

text_a: Our 2 year old granddaughter came from NYC last night. We live in Cambridge. We had a bed set up for her. She refused to sleep on the bed.
text_b_pos: She slept on the floor in the bathroom.
text_b_neg: She went to sleep at her friend's place.

text_a: Lisa was due to give birth at any moment. The anticipation was high. Lisa did not know the gender of her baby. She went into labor and had a baby girl.
text_b_pos: She did not give her a name.
text_b_neg: She called her Lucy.

text_a: Kailey was pregnant and expecting any day. One morning her stomach began hurting. She was hoping it was time but wasn't sure. Instead of going to the hospital she took a bath.
text_b_pos: But the cramps were getting worse.
text_b_neg: She was ready to give birth here.

text_a: Selena invited her group of friends one evening. They celebrated late into the night. Around 3 am, the police banged on her door. She opened and got scared.
text_b_pos: The policemen offered her a coat,
text_b_neg: The police was searching for someone.

text_a: She wanted something that would make her eyes pop. She looked at the brands of mascara available. She didn't know what to try first. Most of them didn't meet her needs.
text_b_pos: She found one very fast.
text_b_neg: But at the end, she found one that fit her needs.

text_a: We always played Super Bowl Bingo during the big game. Each of the kids gets a bingo square. They pick out what commercial they believe they will see. Then whoever gets bingo first wins.
text_b_pos: The kids cried out for help.
text_b_neg: The kids had a lot of fun.

text_a: I was having problems sleeping and I had an Idea. I was going to start a boring hobby to help me fall asleep. I decided to crochet blankets as my new hobby. I loved this hobby and it helped me sleep in a way I did not expect.
text_b_pos: I don't have sleeping problems anymore.
text_b_neg: I don't enjoy crocheting.

text_a: Ed was flying to the Cook Islands. His small plane went down in the Pacific. Ed was presumed dead, but he managed to cling to a life raft. He floated to shore and sought help.
text_b_pos: He joined a party.
text_b_neg: A woman came to the rescue.

text_a: Tracy acquired a necklace from her mother. She had accidentally dropped the necklace down the kitchen sink drain. To solve her problem she had decided to call the plumber. The plumber retrieved the necklace.
text_b_pos: Tracy was very happy.
text_b_neg: Tracy wanted to get rid of the necklace.

text_a: Danny was thrilled when he got a bike for Christmas. He was distraught when the bike turned up missing later. When school resumed, Danny saw his bike with a coat of black paint. As he ran to the bike, Danny saw a tough boy get on it.
text_b_pos: Danny was too scared to confront the boy about his stolen bike.
text_b_neg: Danny was happy that he found his bike.

text_a: Dorothy enjoyed taking care of her son. Her son was disabled due to a car accident. She did everything for him and did it with a smile. Then one day her son Randy passed away.
text_b_pos: Dorothy drove away with her car.
text_b_neg: Dorothy was sad and happy at the same time since Randy did not suffer anymore.

text_a: Matthew had a very bad cough. He made an appointment at the doctor's office for later that day. The doctor listened to his heartbeat and lungs. The doctor told Matthew he needed to stop smoking.
text_b_pos: Matthew has never touched a cigarette since.
text_b_neg: Matthew has a strong heart.

text_a: AJ played a game of baseball with his friends. In the beginning, he was winning by a large lead. Later in the game, his lead began to fall. Eventually, his team lost the game by a wide margin.
text_b_pos: A good time was had by everybody.
text_b_neg: He was disappointed they managed to squander their lead.

text_a: Tom broke up with his long-time girlfriend. In the following weeks, Tom began feeling lonely. Tom's friends suggesting getting a pet. Tom went to a kennel and got a really friendly puppy.
text_b_pos: The puppy ran away from Tom.
text_b_neg: Tom enjoyed the company of his new puppy.

text_a: Blake was playing a game on his computer. He was having trouble beating the game. Blake got frustrated and quit the game. He tried playing again later when he was more relaxed.
text_b_pos: This time, he succeeded at his first attempt.
text_b_neg: Blake decided to go for a walk.

text_a: A guy I like finally asked me out on a date. The date went well and I was excited for him to kiss me in the car. When we get home, he tries to do that. Instead, he grabs my neck to pull him toward him.
text_b_pos: That really put me off.
text_b_neg: He brought chocolate for our next date.

text_a: Anna was trying to reach a box of baking soda. Unfortunately, it was on the top shelf. She pulled out the kitchen stool and took a step. The stool wobbled under her as she reached for the box.
text_b_pos: She climbed down from the stool because she was not interested in the box anymore.
text_b_neg: But she found her balance and was able to get the box.

text_a: My son, Sam, was upstairs making all types of racket. I was downstairs when I saw Sam jump off the balcony. I ran towards him and caught my beloved child in mid-air. I asked him why on earth would he jump off the balcony.
text_b_pos: He explained one of his rackets dropped off the balcony.
text_b_neg: Sam wanted to make more rackets.

text_a: Hector had a pet monkey named Chimples. Chimples loved to throw things. One day, Hector signed up Chimples for his little league team. Chimples threw the ball faster than any human pitcher.
text_b_pos: Chimples likes to eat bananas.
text_b_neg: Thanks to Chimples, Hector's team won the league.

text_a: Joey was trying to do laundry this weekend but his machine was broke. He had a very important date on Monday and couldn't be dirty. Joey racked his brain to come up with a solution. He filled up his bathtub with water and scrubbed his clothes by hand.
text_b_pos: He mailed his landlord to fix the washing machine.
text_b_neg: The clothes got dirtier the more he scrubbed.

text_a: John walked outside one weekend morning. He noticed that his yard was incredibly sloppy and overgrown. John went to his shed and pulled out his lawn mower. After starting it up, John began to mow his lawn.
text_b_pos: John was happy with the result.
text_b_neg: John fixed the lawn mower.

text_a: Sam was going on a trip to the beach. His friend Gordy was supposed to be going with him. Gordy didn't have enough money to go on the trip. Sam had to go to the beach alone.
text_b_pos: Gordy had an awesome time.
text_b_neg: Sam met an awesome friend there.

text_a: Allie found out her neighbor was sick. So she decided to make her a pie. When she was done she brought it over to her. Allie's neighbor ended up loving it.
text_b_pos: They became friends and had coffee together regularly.
text_b_neg: Her neighbor hated her.

text_a: Cal turned off the water knobs in his shower. The shower head continued to drip. Cal really yanked the knobs, turning them as hard as he could. Which of course ended up in him breaking both of them!
text_b_pos: The water wouldn't stop running and he had to call a plumber.
text_b_neg: Cal decided to spend the rest of the day showering.

text_a: Bobby had many older siblings. She envied them going to school. She was so happy when they bought her school supplies too! On the first day of school she waited with her siblings for the bus.
text_b_pos: They entered the bus and her siblings made jokes about her.
text_b_neg: However, the bus never arrived.

text_a: Jill gets a call from her brother asking her if she's ready. She has no idea what he is talking about. She realizes that she forgot their parents' 30th Anniversary party. She rushes to get ready.
text_b_pos: She finally showed up at the party on time.
text_b_neg: She refused to attend the party.

text_a: New neighbors moved in last week. They seem nice. I asked them if they would like to share internet. They agreed and gave me their wifi password.
text_b_pos: I'm using their wifi for illegal activities.
text_b_neg: I gave them a nice present in exchange.

text_a: Mike always loved to go fishing. One day, he went to the lake and set his gear up. He waited patiently for a fish to nibble his line. He finally felt a tug and snapped his fishing pole to hook the fish!
text_b_pos: He caught a rabbit.
text_b_neg: It turned out to be an old boot.

text_a: Alexia was planning a road trip with her friends. Her father didn't want her to be without protection. He insisted on giving her a gun and training her in its use. Alexia was nervous handling it, but eventually became proficient.
text_b_pos: Alexia luckily never used the gun.
text_b_neg: Alexia bought a new car.

text_a: My husband and I moved to Florida one year ago this December. When we moved, we had all sorts of complications getting here. The battery went dead on the Uhaul when we were leaving. While I was pulling our truck behind our SUV, I had a tire blow out.
text_b_pos: I felt relly bad.
text_b_neg: I liked that day.

text_a: Susan sees a pretty girl around town. She is too afraid to talk to her. She decides to follow her around town. The girl notices that Susan is following her.
text_b_pos: The girl went to a mall for shopping.
text_b_neg: She starts to play hide and seek with Susan.

text_a: Carol was trying to clean up around the apartment. She tried to vacuum. Unfortunately it broke halfway through. Carol didn't know how to fix it.
text_b_pos: She then took the broom and cleaned the flat with it.
text_b_neg: Thank to her abilities in the field, she was able to repair it.

text_a: Jack was driving up and down the neighborhood street. He was looking for Olive Avenue. It was clearly on the map, but he could not find it on the street. He waved a woman down and asked her for help.
text_b_pos: She did not know the way either.
text_b_neg: Jack loves to eat olives.

text_a: Leah was making a glass of lemonade. She had squeezed the fruit and just needed her sugar. As she scooped some sugar up in a spoon, she noticed a black dot. Upon further inspection she found dozens of ants in her sugar.
text_b_pos: She put the sugar into her juice and drank it with pleasure.
text_b_neg: She screamed and threw the sugar away.

text_a: Mallory wondered why she pays so much for cable television. She is always at work and barely even watches television. She found out about how cheap Netflix is through a friend. Also Netflix had a bunch of shows the Mallory likes to watch.
text_b_pos: She kept her cable television.
text_b_neg: She cancelled her cable television.

text_a: Jordan had begun playing football at age 8. He was a star player and continued to be one in high school. He hoped to go pro but injured his leg badly junior year. He thought his dreams were ruined and he'd never have a sports career.
text_b_pos: Jordan was happy because he rather wanted to sing.
text_b_neg: After his surgery Jordan worked hard to come back.

text_a: One day Yolanda went to Central Park. First she ate lunch on the grass. Then she walked around a bit. Finally she went to Central Park Zoo.
text_b_pos: Yolanda was very good in school.
text_b_neg: She enjoyed the visit.

text_a: Charles went to see his cousin, Man, in a karate tournament. In the championship round, the opponent made an illegal move. He broke Man's leg and Man had to forfeit. Therefore Charles trained for a year as a kickboxer.
text_b_pos: He beat the same opponent the following year.
text_b_neg: Charles beat Man the following year.

text_a: Sally had a collection of pretty rocks. She cherished this collection and added to it daily. One day her brother Mac stole her whole collection. Sally told her mother, who then confronted Mac about it.
text_b_pos: Mac apologized to Sally and returned the collection.
text_b_neg: Sally didn't care about rocks.

text_a: The family arrived at the port to take their cruise. They were so excited! At their first port, they got terribly lost. They missed the cruise leaving.
text_b_pos: The family was very sad.
text_b_neg: The family bought a new cruise ship.

text_a: The sun was shining brightly when I got to work yesterday. A few minutes later I heard thunder! Before long it was raining hard, with lots of thunder and lightning. Lightning struck nearby and caused our power to go off.
text_b_pos: Since it was sunny outside, there was no need of artificial lights.
text_b_neg: We had no light until the thunderstorm passed.

text_a: Someone knocked on the door. I heard my aunt's voice. Therefore, I decided to jump in my bed. My mom wasn't aware that I pretended to go to sleep.
text_b_pos: My mom nevertheless came in my room to inform that my aunt arrived so my whole plan did not work.
text_b_neg: The next day I went swimming near the beach.

text_a: Kyle always tried to recycle. His friends never cared. He would always do it for them He would stay after parties collecting cans.
text_b_pos: Kyle wants to save planet earth.
text_b_neg: Kyle throws trash on the beach.

text_a: Harold was asked to go hunting. His dad asked him to go. He decided he didn't want to. He told his dad he didn't want to hunt quail.
text_b_pos: Harold bought some fish at the supermarket.
text_b_neg: His father was angry.

text_a: Courtney loved going to the waterpark. Water slides were her favorite thing to do! She went down each slide a dozen times. When she was tired, she sat down and had a popsicle.
text_b_pos: Courtney was afraid of the water.
text_b_neg: It was a great day for her.

text_a: Tom was a smoker. He noticed he would always lose lighters. After a while he decided to do something about it. He bought a chain to attach his lighters to his belt.
text_b_pos: Tom stopped losing his lighters.
text_b_neg: Tom lost his lighters more frequently.

text_a: My town has really weird traditions. It is a small town so things don't really change. There is something that is new this year. An all out puppy parade instead of the traditional Christmas parade.
text_b_pos: The puppies will wear small Santa outfits for the occasion.
text_b_neg: It will be a weird July.

text_a: I bought a new puppy. I wanted the puppy to sleep in a cage at night. When I put it in the cage, he howled loudly. He kept me up at night.
text_b_pos: I gave him more space from then on.
text_b_neg: I put him into a shoe box to shut him up.

text_a: James was hosting some friends. He was going to have a dinner party. The friends all brought bottles of wine. They all ate and drank into the night.
text_b_pos: The friends never spoke to James again.
text_b_neg: The friends thanked James for the fantastic night when they left.

text_a: My husband tried to cut his beard off. When he was halfway done, the battery died on his clippers. He had half a beard hanging and no way of charging them. He had to go to the store to buy a new charger.
text_b_pos: In the store everyone was smiling at my husband as he looked funny.
text_b_neg: My husband won the second place in a beard competition.

text_a: Dan finished watching the Stepford Wives and was inspired. He kidnapped a woman from a dark street. He lobotomized her while she cried and begged for him to stop. Dan's plan went absolutely perfectly.
text_b_pos: She became his wife and they were happy together.
text_b_neg: In the end he killed her and nobody ever found out.

text_a: My favorite food is pizza. I enjoy pasta and ravioli, but I will always choose pizza over them. My family thinks I just enjoy all Italian food. They are wrong because I do not like baked ziti.
text_b_pos: Absolutely nothing beats a slice of pizza.
text_b_neg: Maybe ziti isn't that bad after all.

text_a: Charlie went into the woods to find some insects. He brought his net to catch them with. After an hour he still hadn't found any interesting bugs. Then he found a praying mantis up in a tree!
text_b_pos: He was happy.
text_b_neg: He did not care and left.

text_a: Michigan was an underdog in the basketball game against Notre Dame. Notre Dame was over confident they would win. When the game started, Michigan looked ready, Notre Dame did not. At halftime Michigan was down by 5 points.
text_b_pos: Notre Dame lost the game.
text_b_neg: Michigan lost the game.

text_a: My brothers daughter was at the party. She's about twice as big as I remember. When I went up to her and said hello she didn't recognize me. I was very saddened by this but don't blame her.
text_b_pos: After all it had been 10 years since we last met.
text_b_neg: I called my brother and said I never want to see him again.

text_a: Tom was very hungry. He knew about a special event in town. He drove to it. It was a market of shops, with sellers of many items and foods.
text_b_pos: Tom bought something to eat.
text_b_neg: Tom really did not want any food right now.

text_a: Kelsi got some new heels yesterday. Today she decided to wear them. She was running down the stairs when her heel broke. Kelsi was very disappointed.
text_b_pos: Therefore, she bought many heels today.
text_b_neg: She did not want to wear heels anymore today.

text_a: Tina had just turned forty. She examined herself in the mirror and thought she looked okay. Then she spotted something terrible. She had her very first gray hair!
text_b_pos: She was bald.
text_b_neg: She plucked out that hair.

text_a: I was craving tacos really badly. After work, I picked up the ingredients and went home. When I got home, I began preparing the meal. After an hour of work, my tacos were done.
text_b_pos: I had gotten really hungry by then.
text_b_neg: Luckily, I still had some leftovers in the fridge.

text_a: Gordon was a soldier. He was stationed overseas. Gordon was involved in a gunfight. He was shot several times and lost the use of his arms.
text_b_pos: He joined another gunfight.
text_b_neg: He was sent to the health care center.

text_a: The skeleton had laid in the tomb for thousands of Year's. It was extremely brittle and must be handled with care. The archaeologist knew this as he skillfully moved the bones. One false move and the find would be destroyed.
text_b_pos: The archeologist preferred Egyptology.
text_b_neg: He handled the situation well and safely removed the skeleton from the tomb.

text_a: The little bunny was new in the world. He was just trying to figure out his way. He hopped around looking for food. He played in the sun all day.
text_b_pos: The rabbit died in a trap.
text_b_neg: He started to make friends as he discovered his environment.

text_a: Scott had a big race on Tuesday. But Scott's leg was very tight and sore. Scott's mom told him to ice it while resting it. Scott did this until Tuesday.
text_b_pos: Scott's leg got much better.
text_b_neg: Scott's leg had to be amputated.

text_a: Will wasn't afraid of pain. So when he started to learn how to skateboard, he took many risks. One day, he tried to jump off a ramp without a helmet. And he nearly hit his head on the ground.
text_b_pos: But his jump was successfully.
text_b_neg: Will created a school for skateboard talents.

text_a: Lacy was walking a cemetery in the country. She had got lost while navigating the huge area. She decided to follow the trails to see where they would take her. After following the trails she ended up at her car.
text_b_pos: She got on her car and drove away.
text_b_neg: She went back to the cemetery.

text_a: Nala wanted to play volleyball. She tried out for her school's team. Her tryout went fairly well. Soon the captain called Nala with good news.
text_b_pos: Nala decided never to play volleyball again.
text_b_neg: Nala was to join her school team from next week.

text_a: Eli was doing an interpretative dance. A famous instructor was visiting the studio. He made fun of Eli's dancing. Eli's confidence was shot and he quit dancing.
text_b_pos: Luckily, that instructor had shown him better ways to spend his time.
text_b_neg: That instructor had been really mean to him.

text_a: It was below zero outside. Marty was feeling very cold! So, Marty decided to light a fire in his fireplace. Marty sat next to his fire in his fireplace.
text_b_pos: Marty was warm for the rest of the day.
text_b_neg: Marty felt to warm and opened the window.

text_a: Maisie was supposed to take pictures with her family. She was trying to keep up but felt really sick. Her mom had only booked the photographer for one day though. Maisie was forced to try to hold still for a few more pictures.
text_b_pos: Maisie had to throw up.
text_b_neg: The photograph took beautiful pictures.

text_a: It was time for the Holidazzle Christmas Parade downtown. Jane took her kids downtown to see the parade. They waved to all the people on the floats. The children cheered when the final float with Santa drove by.
text_b_pos: The children had a lot of fun.
text_b_neg: The children didn't enjoy the day.

text_a: John was driving to work one day. He was pulled over. John wasn't sure why. The cop told him he was speeding.
text_b_pos: John started to argue with the cop because he thought he was driving slowly.

text_a: My daughter's college friend visited her yesterday. They went to school in Boston but live in NYC. The friend brought his six month old to visit. My daughter's two year old played with the baby.
text_b_pos: They agreed that they both disliked children.
text_b_neg: They discussed a lot about being a good mother.

text_a: Bob wanted to buy a new book. He didn't have the money. Bob found a ten dollar bill on the ground. He picked it up.
text_b_pos: Bob spent the money at a fast food joint.
text_b_neg: He went straight to the book store with it.

text_a: Victor was a retired soldier. One night, he told his grandson stories about his experiences. His grandson was in awe of his tales of battle. Victor could see that his stories were making him excited and anxious.
text_b_pos: Victor explained  him that war is terrible.
text_b_neg: Victore became a soldier again and fougth for his country.

text_a: Max was working as a clerk at a store. A customer gave him a counterfeit bill. Max and his boss discovered it at the end of the day. Max's boss showed Max how to use the counterfeit pen.
text_b_pos: Max stopped working in the store.
text_b_neg: Max was angry at the customer.

text_a: Joyce walked outside to walk her dog one night. She smelled smoke in the air. She saw flames from down the street. Joyce ran back into her house.
text_b_pos: She called her parents.
text_b_neg: She called the fire department.

text_a: Sarah was binge watching a new show. She wanted to see all of the first season. Unfortunately she fell asleep in the middle of it. When she woke up she got lots of spoilers.
text_b_pos: She was very disappointed that she fell asleep.
text_b_neg: She was happy she missed the show.

text_a: Jane baked a cake for her boyfriend's birthday. She tried hard to make it come out good. Unfortunately she was unable to. The cake still tasted good.
text_b_pos: Her boyfriend felt happy with the birthday cake.
text_b_neg: She threw the cake away.

text_a: Henry had a first class ticket to Saudi Arabia. He got on the plane and prepared to see what it would be like. He was handed a glass of champagne. He reclined in his leather seat and ate lobster.
text_b_pos: He didn't enjoy his flight.
text_b_neg: Henry loves to fly first class.

text_a: I had to buy dental insurance out of pocket. I tried to use my insurance to pay for a crown. No one told me there was a year waiting period. Now I owe my dentist $500.
text_b_pos: I was happy to pay the bill.
text_b_neg: I will have to take a loan.

text_a: Tina was pregnant. She wasn't expecting a baby shower however. But her sister Stacy had been planning one. When she found out she was so excited.
text_b_pos: She was glad that the baby stayed in the family.
text_b_neg: Her sister promised to take care of her baby, while she continues her studies.

text_a: Amy wanted to finish her book. It was almost time to return it to the library. Amy decided to pretend to be sick to buy time. Her mother was skeptical of her illness.
text_b_pos: Her mother was happy about what Amy did.
text_b_neg: Her mother quickly found out that Amy was not sick and told her never to do that again

text_a: In a house on a hill there was a house littered with roaches. Along the walls the floors the ceiling everywhere. No one lived there, until a new family bought the house. They had it cleaned and fumigated getting rid of every bug.
text_b_pos: The infestation was gone.
text_b_neg: Ants stole food from the kitchen.

text_a: John wanted to improve his health. He began reading online about health. He learned that eating some raw vegetables is good. He went shopping at the grocery store and bought raw vegetables.
text_b_pos: Now he just needed to learn how to prepare a tasty meal with them.
text_b_neg: He also bought some hamburgers and fries.

text_a: Jimmy wanted to get a new tattoo. He didn't know want to get, though. He looked through some tattoo magazines. He found one that was perfect for him.
text_b_pos: The studio did not make the tattoo because he was too young though.
text_b_neg: Jimmy decided that tattoos are not his thing.

text_a: Jenny's elementary school was holding a carnival and raffle. Jenny saw that one of the prizes for the raffle was a teddy bear. Jenny really wanted the teddy bear being offered for the raffle prize. Jenny spent all of her money on raffle tickets so she could win.
text_b_pos: Jenny was immensely happy to discover she had won the sweet duck.
text_b_neg: Despite her efforts Jenny couldn't obtain the desired prize.

text_a: Caleb was diagnosed with Sensory Processing Disorder. He was freaking out over sensory items and sounds. He fell to his knees at the loud roar of a motorcycle, covering ears. He ran to me for comfort afterward.
text_b_pos: I gave him a hug to comfort him.
text_b_neg: I told him to get over it.

text_a: Dan led a group of students in protest of the school dress code. The principal said anyone defying the code would be suspended. The students rallied around Dan, who pledged to keep fighting. Hearing of the protest, Dan's parents gave their son an ultimatum.
text_b_pos: Dan decided to stop fighting.
text_b_neg: Dan became a teacher at the school.

text_a: Mollie was coloring her hair the day before prom. She needed it to stay on for ten minutes for strawberry blonde. But she fell asleep for an hour. When she woke up she washed the color out as quickly as she could.
text_b_pos: She started crying because her hair was ruined for prom.
text_b_neg: Her hair was a strawberry blonde.

text_a: Jack went to the beach to work on his tan. He only planned to stay for an hour so he skipped the lotion. He fell asleep out in the sun. He woke up with a horrible sunburn.
text_b_pos: Jack decided to never skip the lotion again.
text_b_neg: Jack loved the color of his skin.

text_a: Jace's hair had grown so long, that he was ready for a haircut. At the salon, the cosmetologist put a colorful cover over Jace. She began to cut his hair, and he sat very still. After she finished cutting his hair, she styled it.
text_b_pos: Jace was bald.
text_b_neg: Jace loved his new hair.

text_a: It is Shaun's fiftieth birthday in a few days. Shaun's wife plans a surprise party for him for Friday. She told him he had to be home early to meet the cable guy. Shaun left work early and arrived home at four o'clock.
text_b_pos: He then greeted the cable guy at his front door.
text_b_neg: He was very suprised to see his wife with a party hat.

text_a: James goes to the park every day. But on Monday he couldn't go because he was sick. So he spent the day sitting next to the window. He doesn't like to be inside.
text_b_pos: He prefers being inside.
text_b_neg: He prefers being outside.

text_a: Edward was an excellent football player at his university. Scouts from several NFL teams came to his games. One team offered him a very lucrative contract. It was a dream come true for Edward.
text_b_pos: He was happy to accept the contract.
text_b_neg: He rejected the contract.

text_a: Henry invited his family over for a home cooked meal. The only problem was that Henry can't cook at all. He ordered food and just threw away all the packaging. He served it and passed it off as his own food.
text_b_pos: When trying his creation Henry realized he had used too much salt.
text_b_neg: But after a few drinks Henry couldn't hide the truth anymore.

text_a: Don decided he would appear smarter if he spoke a lot less. Don started speaking only very rarely or when asked a question. Pretty soon, people began commenting about how smart Don is. One day Don was forced to take an IQ test for school.
text_b_pos: Don was good at history.
text_b_neg: He didn't get a good score.

text_a: Andrew played catch with his son in their backyard. He threw the ball forcefully overhead. To his surprise, it went much farther than he expected. His son marveled at his father's strength.
text_b_pos: His son could throw the ball further.
text_b_neg: One day, he said, I want to be like you.

text_a: Berry was on his way home from work. Rain was pouring he could hardly see anything. The next thing you know Berry see's headlights. Berry crashes into a semi truck on the interstate.
text_b_pos: Berry ends up in the hospital.
text_b_neg: Berry is happy he had an accident.

text_a: Jason ate steak in the morning, and pancakes during dinner. He lived this way to prove the world that he didn't care. He didn't care and he never shared the real reason why. He continued eating this way until his death later in life.
text_b_pos: His example made the anti-veggie movement skyrocket!
text_b_neg: He died of a heart attack.

text_a: Dana took a trip to Los Angeles. Dana was a big Tom Cruise fan. She wandered the hot spots, hoping to spot Tom Cruise. After several days she thought she actually saw him.
text_b_pos: She ran over to him and asked to take a picture with him.
text_b_neg: Dana hit him with her car.

text_a: Bob borrows some money from a loan shark to pay off another debt. But when it comes time to pay he doesn't have the money. Out of desperation he robs a gas station. He gets the money to pay the loan shark.
text_b_pos: Bob lives happily ever after.
text_b_neg: However, the robbery comes out, and Bob goes to jail.

text_a: Tom had a crush on his friend. He decided to let her know. She was flattered by it. Unfortunately she just liked Tom as a friend.
text_b_pos: He was releaved.
text_b_neg: He was disappointed.

text_a: Tom had an upcoming test. He studied very hard for the test. The night before the test, he forgot to set his alarm clock. By the time he woke up, the test was already over.
text_b_pos: Tom was very upset that all the studying didn't pay off
text_b_neg: Tom hurried to the bus and made it in time

text_a: Francisco was playing soccer at a field beside his house. A man drove up and asked if he needed a ride back home. Francisco said it was ok and started walking down the sidewalk. The man insisted that he get in.
text_b_pos: Francisco refused the man once again with polite.
text_b_neg: Francisco won the soccer game.

text_a: Cora and her friends were on a day trip. They decided to head to the beach. There, they all stripped down to their bathing suits. They hurried to splash and play in the water.
text_b_pos: Cora had a nice afternoon with her friends.
text_b_neg: Cora wanted to go home.

text_a: Peggy made a wish on a falling star. She wished that she could get a certain boy to notice her. Peggy forgot about the wish and went to school. She tripped on the step, ripped her jeans, and looked up.
text_b_pos: Her prince charming gave her a hand.
text_b_neg: She washed her jeans.

text_a: Last week, Alan was very excited. He was excited as he was going on a fishing trip. He had hired out what he thought was a large boat, to go with friends. However, when Alan got to the docks, the boat was actually very small.
text_b_pos: So they needed to find a bigger boat to fit all of them.
text_b_neg: But that didn't matter as he wanted to go alone anyway.

text_a: Lenny was baking cookies. But he was disappointed in how they turned out. They were paper thin and crumbly. He decided to mix them with vanilla ice cream.
text_b_pos: He threw away the ice cream and cookies.
text_b_neg: He also bought extra raspberries for the ice cream.

text_a: Gina was taking a weekend trip with her family. She booked a hotel in advance and arrived that night at the hotel. Her room was on the 18th floor of the building. She was afraid of heights but she had little choice for the room.
text_b_pos: So Gina spent the whole night without sleeping.
text_b_neg: Gina enjoyed the whole night in front of the TV.

text_a: I was at work when it started snowing. The day crew started calling in immediately. By the time my shift ended we had over a foot of snow. I volunteered to work over.
text_b_pos: I went home immediately.
text_b_neg: We worked hard to clean the snow.

text_a: Fernandez was with his family on vacation. It was predicted that it would snow heavily soon. His wife told him to leave for home. But Fernandez wanted to stay.
text_b_pos: He tried to convince his wife to leave the following day.
text_b_neg: His wife was happy to go alone.

text_a: One day, Rachelle's heart stopped pumping. Her roommate was there and immediately called 911. Luckily, a cop arrived quickly and started CPR to help her heart. The paramedics decided to Medivac her to a hospital.
text_b_pos: After a few minutes Rachelle woke up again.
text_b_neg: Rachelle never had a heart attack.

text_a: Last week my friends and I went to a trampoline park. As soon as we got there, I ran for the nearest trampoline. I started bouncing and having fun. Yet unfortunately my knees became all rough from falling.
text_b_pos: I did not stay long and soon went home.
text_b_neg: It made me smile.

text_a: Jeremy went to the mall to buy a shirt. When Jeremy got to the mall, he stopped in Target. He looked at the section for electronics. Target was having a sale on cell phones.
text_b_pos: He found a cell phone that he would like to buy.
text_b_neg: He took the cell phones with him.

text_a: Bob studied hard in high school to get good grades. Bob applied to a good college. Bob got accepted to the college. In college Bob studied hard to meet the requirements.
text_b_pos: He didn't care about grades.
text_b_neg: He got a burnout.

text_a: Gina took a left onto a side street from the main street. She drove slowly so she didn't slide on the ice. She drove for half a block to make a u-turn on the next street. Gina made her u-turn and headed back to the main street.
text_b_pos: Gina started sliding on the slippery road and died in an accident.
text_b_neg: Gina drove home safely.

text_a: Jay was going to buy fast food. He couldn't find his keys to the car. He looked everywhere in his apartment. Eventually he got so frustrated that he ordered pizza instead.
text_b_pos: Right after, he found his keys.
text_b_neg: Jay picked up the pizza by car.

text_a: Johnny had a vivid imagination. He always thought about new characters and different stories. Johnny took a creative writing class and began to write novels. Johnny used his incredible imagination to write interesting books.
text_b_pos: He became a bestselling author and quit his job.
text_b_neg: Johnny blamed the coach for being late often.

text_a: Joe was excited to get his first hunting rifle. He asked his brother to take him hunting. Joe and his brother got their hunting gear together. They headed off for the woods.
text_b_pos: Joe shot his first animal on that day.
text_b_neg: Joe returned the gun to pay for his bills.

text_a: Opal wanted to buy her first guitar. She had saved up money from her summer job. Her boyfriend took her to the guitar shop. He helped her find one that was in her price range.
text_b_pos: Opal bought the most expensive guitar she could find.
text_b_neg: Opal took guitar lessons to learn playing the guitar.

text_a: Beatrice always drinks decaf coffee. This morning, she accidentally brewed regular coffee. Beatrice drank five cups of coffee throughout the morning. She was more productive than ever!
text_b_pos: She started cursing people in the office.
text_b_neg: She didn't fall asleep till 6 AM.

text_a: Alex wasn't allowed to watch TV. One Friday night he spent the night at his friend Rob's house. The next morning they watched cartoons. Alex had no idea they played cartoons 4 hours on Saturdays.
text_b_pos: Alex got all dizzy from watching that much TV.
text_b_neg: Alex' parents gave him his own TV soon after.

text_a: Gina and her friends were cleaning up their picnic. Her sister spilled soda. She should have cleaned it up. She only picked up the cup.
text_b_pos: Gina gave her sister a big hug.
text_b_neg: Gina was mad at her sister.

text_a: I was petting my cat yesterday. It tried to scratch my hand. I told it not to. It tried to do it again.
text_b_pos: I gave the cat away.
text_b_neg: The cat scratched me again.

text_a: The neighbors were listening to music. It was very loud. I knocked on their door. They could not hear me.
text_b_pos: I went back home for sleep.
text_b_neg: I called the police for help.

text_a: Lucy's grandpa was away for the day. She always wanted to explore his Den. She crept into the den when grandma wasn't looking. She went through his desk, and its drawers.
text_b_pos: She decided to go outside to play.
text_b_neg: She discovered her birthday gift he wanted to giver her next week.

text_a: When Jill is six a firefighter saves her from a burning house Jill goes on to have a normal childhood and becomes a diagnostician. A patient comes to her with an issue other doctors can't diagnose. She correctly diagnosed lung cancer in time to save his life.
text_b_pos: The patient dies from cancer.
text_b_neg: Thus, the firefighter has saved two lives.

text_a: Today is Gail's 50th Birthday. Her friends have been planning a surprise party for weeks. Gail had no idea that her friends planned a party. When she walked into the room it was dark and quiet.
text_b_pos: Suddenly the light went on and everyone shouted Happy Birthday!
text_b_neg: Gail went to the TV and watched a film by herself.

text_a: I began to do a few leg stretches. The mat I was resting on slipped. My leg ended up being overstretched. I had to call my friend.
text_b_pos: I didn't worry too much, since I didn't get hurt.
text_b_neg: He took me to the doctor because my leg hurt.

text_a: Lisa had never flown. She was always afraid to fly because her uncle died on a plane. One year her family was taking a trip to Germany. She was reluctant to take the trip, but her family made her feel safe.
text_b_pos: She did not go to Germany.
text_b_neg: She learned that flying is actually very safe.

text_a: It was my birthday on Saturday. One of my friends gave me a birthday card and some lotto tickets. I scratched them off and won ten dollars. I really needed the money since I was broke.
text_b_pos: I threw the lotto tickets at my friend.
text_b_neg: I used the money to buy more lotto tickets.

text_a: Zeke had a dog. The dog loved to play catch. One day, the dog's favorite ball got lost. The dog was sad.
text_b_pos: Zeke went to buy a replacement ball for his dog.
text_b_neg: The dog started to play with a stick.

text_a: Hank was at his high school basketball match. During half time, someone from the other team offered him candy. Hank gladly accepted the candy. But he started feeling bad when the game resumed.
text_b_pos: After the game he even had to go to the doctor.
text_b_neg: That's why he played the best game of his life.

text_a: Sara needed a prescription. She went up to the counter. The pharmacist asked for her name and birthday. She gave him the info.
text_b_pos: She bought what she needed.
text_b_neg: She went home without buying anything.

text_a: The boy moved to the front. The teacher noticed. She talked to the boy after class. He was having trouble following her.
text_b_pos: He understood everything she said.
text_b_neg: He was very confused afterwards.

text_a: Sally is bored at home. Her husband is going to go fishing with his buddies. Her husband invites Sally to go fishing. Sally accepts the invitation.
text_b_pos: Sally is looking forward to go fishing
text_b_neg: Sally wants to stay at home

text_a: Bill watched a movie about sailing. He thought that would be fun. He researched sailing extensively. He made it his life's goal to buy a sailboat.
text_b_pos: Bill bought a sailboat once he retired.
text_b_neg: Bill hated the sea.

text_a: Jill was shopping at the mall with her friend. The two decided that she needed a new sweater. Jill passes by her favorite store. She goes through all the sweaters.
text_b_pos: Jill had too many sweaters already.
text_b_neg: Jill did not find a sweater she liked.

text_a: Tyler is afraid of snakes. His friends want to help him. His friends take him to a pet store. They make him pet the snake.
text_b_pos: The snake transforms into a cat.
text_b_neg: The snake murders him.

text_a: Emma was invited to play Bingo with her friends. It was a $25 entry fee but the prize was $1000! Emma felt sure she could win, so she paid the fee. But someone else ended up winning, and Emma was unhappy.
text_b_pos: She decided to never play Bingo again.
text_b_neg: She bought herself a nice present with the money she won.

text_a: Tom didn't have a lot of pants. He decided to buy a new pair. He went to different stores. Tom tried various pairs.
text_b_pos: He ate a pizza.
text_b_neg: At the end he did not buy anything.

text_a: John, the CEO of the company, got up. He was giving a speech to the company. He stood behind the lectern and delivered his speech. It was a very powerful speech.
text_b_pos: His speech was met with boos and hisses.
text_b_neg: His speech won a great applause.

text_a: Dan wanted to watch Sia's concert from Coachella. The only site with the video was in streaming format. It wouldn't let Dan download it to watch. Dan looked at the network requests to find the actual video link.
text_b_pos: He did not like Sia's music anyways.
text_b_neg: Now he finally was able to download the video.

text_a: Meagan went out with her friends. She put her phone on the top of the car. The car sped down the highway. The phone fell off.
text_b_pos: The screen was all shattered when she picked it up.
text_b_neg: They had a great night out.

text_a: I hated garlic. Then, my friend recommended that I try roasted garlic. I was wary but I decided to try it. Alas, I burnt the garlic during the roasting.
text_b_pos: That tasted even worse than raw garlic.
text_b_neg: Now I've grown to like garlic.

text_a: Tim loved playing outdoors. He would always get muddy. He always dragged mud in his home. He quickly became annoyed with cleaning the mud in his home.
text_b_pos: So, Tim stopped playing outside.
text_b_neg: Tim took a mud bath.

text_a: Ann went to the parade with her son. They watched the floats pass by. Then marchers came by, playing drums. Some of them even threw candy!
text_b_pos: The boy did not like that he was taken there.
text_b_neg: Ann's son was very excited and was smiling.

text_a: Mike had a very stressful job. He needed a vacation. So he took one. He headed to the sunny beaches of mexico.
text_b_pos: Mike missed his job's action while laying on the beach.
text_b_neg: After his rest Mike came back to work motivated and free of stress.

text_a: Jack began feeling heart palpitations. He went to the doctor to get his heart tested. Jack's doctor told him his heart was just fine. Jack did learn, however, that he had high blood pressure.
text_b_pos: So he decided to abandon his old life and start a new calm one on a deserted island.
text_b_neg: People told him this was because he was having too much stress.

text_a: David wasn't confident he would land the job. First, he was black and second he'd been out of work for a six months. He applied for a job at an SEO firm. They called him back after one month.
text_b_pos: He excelled at the interview and got the job
text_b_neg: He was irritated that they called him.

text_a: Nate had the summer off before college. He wanted to have a lot of new, fun experiences. So he took a job with a traveling carnival. He saw new places and made lots of friends.
text_b_pos: He was eaten by an elephant.
text_b_neg: After half a year he quit the carnival and became a lawyer.

text_a: I went to take the trash to the curb. The bag was very heavy, and started stretching. Halfway down the driveway, the bag broke. Trash spilled out all over.
text_b_pos: I had to get a broom and clean up.
text_b_neg: I was happy and drank a coke right beside the curb.

text_a: Fred took his family to the local Mexican restaurant. They thought the food tasted a bit off. Fred's family fought over the bathroom the rest of the night. The news had an item about the restaurant the next day.
text_b_pos: They never went back to that place.
text_b_neg: They really enjoyed their meals that night.

text_a: I like to ride my bike to work. Sometime I will try and use my phone while riding. Today I almost got hit by a car because I was trying to use my phone. It was very scary and changed how I look at riding my bike.
text_b_pos: Tomorrow I will call my mother while riding.
text_b_neg: I will be more careful riding my bike in the future.

text_a: Kate and 3 friends were going on a road trip. Things had started off rocky. But now it was time to leave. Kate started to get excited about the trip.
text_b_pos: Kate didn't want to leave home.
text_b_neg: Kate bought lots of beer for the road.

text_a: David kept telling Kenny he was a better ball player. Kenny completely disagreed. David kept making comments, and Kenny finally challenged him. The game went on for hours.
text_b_pos: Kevin finally proved to be the better player.
text_b_neg: David and Kevin celebrated their victory.

text_a: John got hired at a circle k. He was working the night shift. Someone came in to rob him. He gave them all the beer in stock.
text_b_pos: He drank beer together with the robber.
text_b_neg: He finally got a chance to call the police.

text_a: Gina loved Easter morning. She loved finding the basket that the bunny had brought. She always hoped it would be filled with candy and such. This time it was filled with all of her favorite things.
text_b_pos: Gina wished it would have been Christmas instead.
text_b_neg: Gina couldn't have been happier.

text_a: Mom bought a box of Little Debbie cookie snacks. The box had a little window you could poke your finger through. I sneaked several cookies through that window and gobbled them up. Mom later asked me how I thought the box was three cookies short.
text_b_pos: She was happy I took the cookies and gave me more.
text_b_neg: She patched the window so I couldn't steal more cookies.

text_a: Matt and Kelly attended the same geometry class. They were very competitive about their place in class. Matt studied very hard to get better grades than Elly. During their next test Matt knew all the answers.
text_b_pos: Matt felt proud of himself.
text_b_neg: Matt was criticized by his teacher.

text_a: Lexi decided to join Habitat for Humanity. She immediately got to work on a small house. It took weeks to finish the place. When they finally finished, they gave the keys to a family in need.
text_b_pos: The family lived there happily.
text_b_neg: They all died.

text_a: Andrew decided to propose to Liz. He wanted to take her to dinner on Valentine's day. He made reservations at their favorite restaurant. When they arrived he proposed to Liz.
text_b_pos: Liz did not respond, walked away and was never seen again.
text_b_neg: Liz told him that she is not ready yet.

text_a: Billy wanted to meet his friends out for a trip to the bar. He called them all up individually. Once he spoke to them, he began to get ready. It didn't take long to get ready.
text_b_pos: It took him a long time to get ready.
text_b_neg: He met his friends at the bar.

text_a: Joyce and Anne started a design firm. They were struggling to get clients. A wealthy businessman hired them to redo his whole home. They did a great job and he referred them to all of his friends.
text_b_pos: Their business was a great success afterwards.
text_b_neg: They shut down their business and started living under the bridge.

text_a: I decided to take a long bubble bath. I bought some bubble bath from the store. It was a kid's brand, but I liked the gum smell. I used a lot in my tub.
text_b_pos: The smell was not good.
text_b_neg: I would buy more of it next time.

text_a: Greg approached Gina while she was trying to go to class. Since her friends were around, she felt embarrassed. She pretended that she didn't know Gary. Although he was confused, he still tried to get her attention.
text_b_pos: Gina told him to bring her an ice cream.
text_b_neg: Gina appreciated this.

text_a: Mike made a lot of money from a successful business. After putting some money towards savings, he decided to gamble some. Mike took thousands of dollars and then flew to Las Vegas. Mike went on a gambling spree and then lost a lot of his money.
text_b_pos: Mike wanted to come back to Las Vegas again.
text_b_neg: Mike was glad that he had saved some money.

text_a: Tim wanted to run in a marathon. He practised everyday after school. He got a lot better. He broke his leg the day before the race.
text_b_pos: He won the champion in the marathon.
text_b_neg: He was really upset about it.

text_a: Joyce wanted to get a dog. After researching she decided that she would adopt a rescue. She scouted several adoption agencies. When she went to the agency she bonded with a white puppy.
text_b_pos: Joyce wanted to get a cat.
text_b_neg: Joyce adopted the white puppy from the agency.

text_a: Rob got a starring role in a new sitcom. The writing was terrible, so it was cancelled quickly. Rob's reputation was ruined. He never worked in Hollywood again.
text_b_pos: Rob became a director.
text_b_neg: Rob became an engineer.

text_a: Emilia loved romantic movies. She could always be seen crying at the end of them. Her boyfriend Sam did not enjoy the movies. At the end of one of these movies, Sam rolled his eyes and yawned.
text_b_pos: Emilia broke up with Sam because of this.
text_b_neg: Sam enjoyed the movies with Emilia.

text_a: Mark is a first year doctor. He works at a hospital and it is very fast paced. He sometimes gets overwhelmed and cannot concentrate. He reaches out to a veteran doctor for some advice and guidance.
text_b_pos: The veteran doctor gives him good advice how to handle the situation.
text_b_neg: The veteran doctor tells Mark not to bother him.

text_a: Jen was feeling homesick. She took out a photo of her childhood home. She felt a little better. She thought of the great times she'd had there.
text_b_pos: Jen went to the swimming pool later this day.
text_b_neg: Jen decided to call a childhood friend and do a reunion for the good old times.

text_b_neg: Now her mother loved the day even more.

text_b_pos: The coffee smelled delicious.
text_b_neg: Morgan hates coffee.

text_a: My friends invited me to the lake. They wanted to make burgers and swim. I brought beer and we all hung out and had fun. We grilled the burgers and talked.

text_b_neg: Upon finishing the paper, Lacy went immediately to bed.

text_b_pos: I spent most of the time texting my friends.
text_b_neg: It was one of the most beautiful places I had ever seen.

text_a: Bill had a very important meeting in Washington DC. He left extra early to make sure he arrived on time. Traffic was awful on the interstate. He got on the metro and the train was delayed.
text_b_pos: Jon arrived late to his meeting.
text_b_neg: Jon slept in the train.

text_a: Ralph always wanted a Cadillac. He worked hard and saved his money. Ralph saved enough to buy the Cadillac that he wanted. He drove it home, but it wouldn't fit in his garage.
text_b_pos: Ralph likes trains so he decided to book a train trip.
text_b_neg: Ralph had to park the car outside the house.

text_b_pos: Lorrie went happily to sleep.
text_b_neg: Lorrie got divorced in the next couple days.

text_a: Allie loved shopping. She went and got a birthday gift. It was her sister's birthday. Her sister wanted a gift card.
text_b_pos: Her sister was happy that Allie got her a credit card.
text_b_neg: Allie bought her a gift card to her favourite candy store.

text_b_neg: From that day onwards, Chrissy loved cleaning day.

text_a: Tim was really good at archery. He was encouraged to join competitions. The first one he joined he won easily. Tim continued on to bigger competitions.
text_b_pos: Tim decided he didn't like archery any more.

text_a: Jim was playing video games His controller ran out of batteries. Jim went to the store to buy some more. At the store Jim got distracted with impulse buys.

text_a: Tim had been with Kathy for a year. He really loved her. He wanted to marry her. Tim asked for her hand in marriage.
text_b_pos: Tim was gay.
text_b_neg: She said yes.

text_b_neg: Tom wasn't so sure they should get engaged.

text_b_neg: I am nipping for the loo.

text_b_neg: Kim was disappointed that the school was canceled.

text_b_neg: She saw how Tom had been struggling but was happy to support him.

text_b_pos: Ed bought a cake.

text_b_pos: Jason went swimming.

text_b_pos: She went in and bought a bagel.
text_b_neg: She camped in front of the store until it opened.

text_b_neg: The mother lied as it's not allowed to have elephants on the circus.

text_a: Greg asked Mike if he could do the laundry. The  Mike didn't know what he was doing. He mixed all the colors and ruined the clothes.

text_b_pos: The owner visits Bruce in the afternoon.
text_b_neg: The owner agrees and Bruce buys the house.

text_a: Shauna walked through a clothing store. She passed a few shirts and cardigans. Nothing really stood out to her. She made her way to the denim section.
text_b_pos: She found a really nice pair of jeans.
text_b_neg: Finally the bus arrived.

text_a: Nina went to the grocery store. But when she got there, she realized she'd forgotten her list. She tried to remember what was on it. But when she got home and checked the list, she sighed.
text_b_pos: She got all of them.
text_b_neg: She forgot about most of the items on the list.

text_a: Allie was driving only five miles above the limit. All the sudden she got pulled over. When she saw the cop she was awestruck. He was very beautiful.
text_b_pos: She asked for his number.
text_b_neg: She refused to speak to the officer.

text_b_pos: Delia always wore red dresses.
text_b_neg: It contained a dress that fit Delia perfectly.

text_b_pos: Lars told Milly she looked unattractive.

text_b_pos: Jim and Marcella couldn't contain their excitement as they went to welcome the boy.
text_b_neg: Jim and Marcella told the boy that they didn't want him.

text_b_pos: Dan was happy to hear his efforts had paid off.
text_b_neg: Disappointed, Dan decided to study even harder.

text_b_pos: Joey returned the phone to the shop.

text_a: Kaitlyn loved sewing. She made bandanas for her two dogs. Everyone loved Kaitlyn's bandanas. They wanted Kaitlyn to make bandanas for their pets.
text_b_pos: Kaitlyn loved dogs.
text_b_neg: Soon Kaitlyn started a small business with making bandanas.

text_a: Julia wanted to go out with Ron, the football team quarterback. He was single, but handsome and intimidating! Finally she worked up enough nerve to ask Ron out on a date. To her surprise, Ron said yes to her offer!
text_b_pos: Ron meant to say no.
text_b_neg: They really enjoyed their date!

text_b_neg: I couldn't be more happy to have arrived at such a healthy infrastructure.

text_b_pos: Peter was still able to see Alice in Chains.
text_b_neg: Peter played five hours of tennis.

text_b_pos: He was so happy to be in this park in Florida.

text_a: Tom was good at playing darts. He played all the time at a local bar. One day he was playing without paying attention. He let a dart go towards the board carelessly.

text_b_pos: but she gained weight.

text_b_neg: Bradley felt bad for eavesdropping.

text_b_pos: It was hard to see the TV clearly without his glasses.

text_b_pos: With her teeth fixed, Mae couldn't stop smiling.

text_a: Mike loved to run. He wanted a pair of running shoes. The pair he wanted was very expensive. Mike waited until the store had their semi annual sale.

text_b_neg: He bought an ice cream with the money.

text_b_pos: The interviewer is impressed and Frank gets the job.

text_b_pos: Myron decided to keep his hairstyle.

text_b_neg: Randy died in the accident.

text_a: Anna pulled the jug of Kool Aid out of the fridge. Then she shook it to mix it before pouring a glass. But the last user had not secured the cap. The jug opened and spilled everywhere!

text_b_neg: She had to clean the mess.

text_a: Tim turns his girlfriend's favorite blanket pink in the laundry. He replaces it and hopes that she won't notice. But she does notice that the new blanket is not hers. The old blanket has sentimental value to her.

text_a: Val saw Ali go to the bathroom. Val and her friend Kris followed her. Ali froze when she saw Val. Val was going to pummel this brat.

text_a: On the way home from a rafting trip, I began to feel sick. The pain just got worse the longer we drove. After arriving home and a painful night, I went to the hospital. The doctor examined and diagnosed me with appendicitis.
text_b_pos: I had surgery later that day.
text_b_neg: I left the hospital and got back into the car.

text_a: Bob bought a new hot tub. He invited all of his friends over to try it. Five people all got into the tiny hot tub. They stayed in the hot tub all day.
text_b_pos: They had easily enough space.
text_b_neg: Bob wished he had a larger hot tub.

text_a: John had tried a new food on vacation. They were serving rattlesnake. It was a bit odd looking. It was very expensive.
text_b_pos: John did not like it.
text_b_neg: Rattlesnakes are dangerous animals.

text_a: Jan was ready to get her driver's license. She had practiced a lot, but she was still nervous. She went to the DMV office and handed in her paperwork. She got in the car to take her road test.
text_b_pos: She passed the test and got her license finally.
text_b_neg: She got off the car.

text_a: Jane loved to read. Her mother gave her a book for her birthday. She spent the whole day reading. She fell in love with the story.
text_b_pos: Jane was bored and thought about doing something else.
text_b_neg: Jane couldn't stop reading until she finished the book.

text_a: Some kids set off fireworks on a mesa. The grass on the mesa burned. The fire came close to some houses. Firefighters put out the fire.
text_b_pos: Firefighters praised the kids.
text_b_neg: The kids were punished by their parents

text_a: The kids were sick of school. Their mom agreed to take them on a vacation. They decided on the beach. They loaded up the car and headed to FLorida.
text_b_pos: The kids were finally happy.
text_b_neg: Their mom is a good driver.

text_a: Rick hadn't left his home for a couple days. He decided that he needed to go out one morning. When he opened the door, he was quite surprised. The leaves of the trees had changed colors.
text_b_pos: The leaves caught fire immediately.
text_b_neg: He saw that autumn was here.

text_a: Ron liked to go fishing. He bought a new tackle box to hold his supplies. He loaded it up with bobbers and lures. He set out to catch some fish.
text_b_pos: He didn't manage to catch a single one.
text_b_neg: He finally caught the rabbit!

text_a: Matty raced home from school. Her favorite program was set to start at 4 pm. At 4:01 pm, the television was on. Matty settled on the couch  with her snacks and the remote control.
text_b_pos: She enjoyed watching the show.
text_b_neg: Matty turned of the TV since she did not like the show

text_a: Sal was attending a wedding. He wore a suit to the wedding. He spilled a bit of food on his suit. Sal couldn't get the food off of his suit.
text_b_pos: Sal had ruined his only good suit.
text_b_neg: Sal danced with a lot of girls at that wedding.

text_a: Tom had a pet bird. Every time he opened the cage it would try to fly away. Tom never opened it anymore. One day the bird had flown away.
text_b_pos: Tom felt really sad about it.
text_b_neg: Tom was very surprised since his pet never tried to escape before.

text_a: Dory was eating ice cream. She dropped some of it all over her shirt. Dory had to figure out a way to clean it off. She threw the stained shirt into the washing machine.
text_b_pos: Dory bought a new shirt.
text_b_neg: She hung the shirt out to dry.

text_a: Tom bought a foreclosed townhouse. It was very cheap and Tom was a handyman. He fixed up the place real nice all by himself for very cheap. Within a year Tom put the house on the market.
text_b_pos: He called a demolition crew the next day.
text_b_neg: He sold it at a significant profit.

text_a: I have an uncomfortable cyst in my armpit and a sprained ankle. Both are on the right side of my body. It causes me to hobble around the house like I'm crippled. My boyfriend thinks it's hilarious.
text_b_pos: I decide not to go out of the house any more.
text_b_neg: I feel sad the he is not more understanding.
